alt: Image may contain: 1 person, outdoor and nature
firstComment:
Throwback Thursday❤

Think back when you last time scrolled your old photos, droolled in your old memories..With fast paced life we never get time to cherish those old memories again..But with #stayathome time you can probably get some moment to revisit those old time spent with your family and friends.

Looking at old photos is a way to revisit an experience we once had and doing so increases our sense of purpose and overall wellbeing.

It will help you many ways in your self care journey. It allows you to reconnect, see past successes, makes you grateful for the poeople in your life & it reminds you how far you have come or how much you have grown.

So if you are getting bored sometime or getting stressed from #socialdistancing situation dont forget to look beyond that bubble bath and scented candle. One of the best form of Self Care may be just right there in your camera roll.

#selfcarethread #throwbackthursday #memoriesforlife❤️

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, living room and indoor
firstComment:
𝟓 𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬 𝐈’𝐦 𝐃𝐨𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝗪𝐡𝐢𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐨𝐜𝐢𝐚𝐥 𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐭𝐚𝐧𝐜𝐢𝐧𝐠⁣
⁣
𝐑𝐄𝐋𝐀𝐗𝐈𝐍𝐆: Every part of me wants to get a head start on all the work I’m going to have to do in the upcoming weeks to adapt to a new lifestyle (especially centred around my two teaching jobs) but this IS technically my March Break so I’m trying to fully embrace this vacation time as much as possible.⁣
⁣
𝐂𝐎𝐎𝐊𝐈𝐍𝐆: With all this time and extra food in my fridge and pantry, I’m cooking up some delicious meals. Cooking has become such a great stress relief for me this past decade so it’s a nice comfort.⁣
⁣
𝐂𝐎𝐍𝐍𝐄𝐂𝐓𝐈𝐍𝐆: Whether it’s talking to people for long periods of time on the phone (something I NEVER do) or texting a friend I haven’t had the chance to chat with in so long because we’ve just been so “busy”, I’ve been making a real effort to connect with others way more than I used to. I’m also spending more time outdoors in nature, which is allowing a fantastic reconnect there as well. Oh, and so much more intentional fur baby quality time 💕⁣
⁣
𝗪𝐑𝐈𝐓𝐈𝐍𝐆: You may not know this, but the number one thing on my bucket list has always been to write a book. I’ve been writing since I was about 10 and I had been using the “busy” excuse for why I hadn’t been writing lately. Well, now I’ve got the time and the words are flowing nicely.⁣
⁣
𝐌𝐎𝐕𝐈𝐍𝐆 𝐌𝐘 𝐁𝐎𝐃𝐘: Harvard came out with an article this past week about how yoga (along with meditation and breath work) could help ease stress and anxiety during these uncertain times. I highly agree, although I didn’t need Harvard to tell me. I feel it every single day when I roll out my mat. I’m so so grateful that I have the 3-Day Yoga Retreat to guide my practice every morning. ⁣
⁣
On that note, the mat is calling!

alt: Photo by Well Within Chiropractic in Well Within Chiropractic.
firstComment:
Sometimes life feels like the rug has been pulled right out r from underneath your feet hey?!?!?!
.
Each day will show us how big our GAP is ... general adaptive potential. Otherwise known as how to roll with the punches without getting hurt (signs and symptoms).
.
Things we will be doing in our house to make the best out of a crazy situation:
.
❤️ time-outs ... one hour of alone time for each member of the family with no electronics (may feel like a punishment to the boys but it will be heaven to me lol)!
❤️regular schedule ... up at the same time and bed to the same time. I crave routine.
❤️ new recipe every day.. being willing to try new things.
❤️ train every day ... so happy for a home gym although I am unreasonably upset over my usual gym being closed 🤷🏻‍♀️😂
❤️ get adjusted .... I have a table at home and a chiropractor 👨🏻‍⚕️ 😂.
❤️ puppy snuggles and long hikes outside.
❤️ read ... so many books and loads of time.
.
We will keep it simple. I am not looking for a mother of the year award... I'm not going to put more pressure on myself than already exists. Do you know what I mean?
.
I think we all need a strategy of sorts? What are you doing in your house?
.
FYI ... I'm here virtually for you in anyway I can be! I will post workouts, recipes and health tips everyday. Please don't hesitate to message me if you have questions, concerns or just want to talk ❤️
.

alt: Photo shared by Tomekk on March 19, 2020 tagging @instagram.
firstComment:
🙌🙌 Intervallfasten🙌🙌 Das Kurzzeitfasten – auch Intervallfasten oder intermittierendes Fasten genannt , wird derzeit als neuer Gesundheitstrend in den Medien gefeiert.  Regelmäßige Essenspausen🕛🕛 gönnen dem Organismus Ruhephasen, in denen er keine Mahlzeit verarbeiten muss. Der Stoffwechsel wird angekurbelt, Fettreserven können abgebaut werden und in den Zellen kommen tiefgreifende Regenerierungsprozesse in Gang.
Doch nicht nur die gesundheitlichen Aspekte überzeugen: Mit Kurzzeitfasten fällt auch das Abnehmen oftmals leichter als mit anderen Diätmethoden 💥💥Wirkungen💥💥 Längere Phasen ohne Kalorienzufuhr wirken sich positiv auf den Stoffwechsel aus. Der Insulinspiegel sinkt, der Körper muss auf seine Energiereserven zurückgreifen und die Fettverbrennung ankurbeln, was nicht nur Übergewichtigen zu Gute kommt. Denn auf diese Weise schmilzt auch das viszerale Fett (die inneren Organe im Bauchraum umhüllendes Fett), das ein erhöhtes Risiko für Herzkreislaufkrankheiten, Schlaganfälle und Diabetes vom Typ II darstellt. Auch die Leber baut bei Nahrungsentzug Fett um und verwandelt dieses in sogenannte Ketonkörper, welche in allen möglichen Organen, einschließlich des Gehirns, zur Energiegewinnung verwendet werden.

Ein weiterer Effekt ist die sogenannte Autophagie, eine Art „Müllabfuhr“ in den Zellen.

Wenn Zellen altern, sammeln sich in ihnen beschädigte Proteine an. Bei der Autophagie zersetzen die Zellen ihre überalterten oder defekten Bestandteile und gewinnen dadurch Energie. Sie reinigen und verjüngen sich quasi selbst, indem sie den Abfall herausschleusen.

Im Einzelnen hat Fasten bzw. Kurzzeitfasten folgende positive Auswirkungen auf die Gesundheit:

Verbesserung der Zellregeneration

Verlangsamung des Alterungsprozesses

Reduzierung entzündlicher Prozesse

Regulierung bei Bluthochdruck

Schmerzlinderung bei Arthrose

Zur Vorbeugung für Diabetes Typ II

Verbesserung der Blutwerte

firstComment:
If you had one wish what would it be? .
Mine would be more time being present with my kids...
.
.
After waking up this morning and reflecting on yesterday’s news of schools closure I’ve realised that, actually, we can choose to look at it as though we have been gifted time. .
.
We have to seek out the positives of the situation we face. So, don’t stress about providing school work for your kids. The teachers will be putting something in place eventually... or even if not, don’t stress. The kids are still learning tonnes now any socially, morally, spiritually. .
.
My advice is:
Get up early as usual and get ready for the day
Adopt a regular yoga / meditation practice. 
Spend time reading 
Read, read, read 
Play
Dance
Sing
Yoga
Go into the garden 
Watch Netflix 
Make silly videos - for yourself not for Instagram. 
Make memories. .
.
The world has never seen anything like this before, so nobody knows what to do. So keep calm. Spent time with your loved ones. We are in this together 💛✨
.
.
.
.
. .
.
.
.

alt: Photo by Chanel Botes on March 19, 2020.
firstComment:
Did you know that your beloved essential oil doesn’t actually come out of that large center hole? ... 🤯 That’s just for air flow! You see that teeny tiny pinprick off to the side? 🔍 THAT’s where the oil comes from. Once again... 🤯
.
.
So next time when you’re refilling your diffuser or roll-on bottles, or otherwise testing your patience while attempting to get the right amount of drops out (I see you, Mr. Vetiver 👀), try holding the bottle at an angle with the pinprick at the bottom to increase the flow for thicker oils, or the pinprick at the top to decrease the flow for thinner oils. So much easier to control 👌🏻

firstComment:
If you're working from home over this period here are some tips for you for your desk step up. 
As tempting as it to sit on your sofa/bed like in the images, avoid doing it for long periods. 
Sit at a desk or dining table. It's better for you and you'll reduce your risk of aches and pain

Aim to make your laptop eye level, so use books under your lap top or anything to bring it to eye level if possible. 
Find the most supportive chair at home to sit on. 
Use a pillow for back support 
Make sure your elbows are resting on the table 
Make sure your knees are at 90 degrees when sitting and feet on the ground

Make sure you get up regularly every 30m to 40mins to help you avoid aches and pain🙌

alt: Photo by Stacy Heckenberg Nutritionist on March 19, 2020.
firstComment:
🌝 S L E E P 🌝

Sleep plays a vital role in both physical and mental health. It’s also important for
✴️Immune function
✴️Metabolism
✴️Memory
✴️Learning
✴️Detoxification
✴️Optimal wellbeing

Why do so many people struggle to get a good night’s sleep? Busy lives, hectic jobs, stress, environment, lifestyle and diet all contribute to how well you sleep
⏺Stress and poor diet may impair your ability to sleep, while irregular sleep patterns can leave you with low energy levels throughout the day. Sleep deprivation can trigger an immune response similar to the stress response
⏺Setting a sleep/wake schedule will reset your circadian rhythm and increase your energy and concentration. When you wake up in the morning allow the natural light to come in and get as much exposure to natural sunlight throughout the day as possible. This will help to reset your body, encouraging production of serotonin which then converts to melatonin to help you to get a good night’s sleep
✳️Tips on how to improve your sleep hygiene ➡️Make a routine of your bed time & wake time
➡️Turn off all screens 30-60 minutes before bed
➡️Keep your bedroom temperature around 20*C, make sure it is quiet and dark
➡️Reduce your caffeine intake. Swap coffee for herbal teas.
➡️Get some sunshine early in the day to enhance your circadian rhythm
➡️Use a Blue Light Filter App on your phone or tablet, especially if you read at night
➡️Avoid alcohol, sugar, and nicotine
➡️Try not to nap during the day
➡️Take a bath with some epsom salts 1-2 hours before bed

This week I’ve been exploring and sharing alternative methods to help fortify our immune systems in light of the coronavirus outbreak. ⁣
⁣
Studies have shown that regular massage can help boost your immune system by strengthening elements of your body that contribute to immunity. With that being said, I would also like to explain that having a massage when you’re ill is not advisable and can do more harm than good. Massage works well for prevention when it comes to illnesses such as a cold and flu. ⁣
⁣
However, as a treatment method it may be counterproductive.  I hope the above post and previous posts will provide some useful knowledge to you all as we weather this storm. #laurastouch #lauras_touch

firstComment:
Wʜᴀᴛ ɪғ ᴡᴇ sᴛᴀʀᴛ sᴇᴇɪɴɢ ᴛʜᴇ ɢᴏᴏᴅ ᴇᴠᴇɴ ᴅᴜʀɪɴɢ ᴅɪғғɪᴄᴜʟᴛ ᴛɪᴍᴇs?

The last few days have been difficult, the world has never seen a situation like this before, at least not as far as I remember 🤔

People are worried, they're scared - myself included ✋🏾- but we are all together in this. And how strange this is? The fact that for the very first time the entire world is collapsing with NO person left out. 
_____________________________________________________________
White, black, yellow, fat, skinny, gay, rich, poor, old, young, woman, man, I can keep going with all differences of human specie. There's nobody who's not somehow being affected. 
_____________________________________________________________
We can still be ignorant, ambitious, selfish and just watch all that is happening and then continue living our lives as it was before or we might wanna start questioning the "what's", the "why's" and the "how's" for chaotic situations like this to be happening over and over again. 
_____________________________________________________________
What if the world is not only about me? What if I start caring for others and genuinely help them? What if I'm so corrupted that I'm not even seeing things clearly anymore and all I care about is a bunch of 'things', money, fame, popularity, appearance, business, time, rush, etc? What if I can take all that's happening as a lesson? Why is it happening? Why was I sent to work from home with my family members? Why did I lose mu job? Why did I lose so much money? How can I overcome the chaos inside my mind? How can I be more self conscious? How can I change my life?
_____________________________________________________________
Let's all take some time to think about this questions, you might wanna right your answers down on a piece of paper or just answer them mentally. 
_____________________________________________________________
Oh, and the nice pic of me wearing my bikini in Bali is to get your attention. Today I heard something from a person I love that really made me think about writing this message to you guys. (please see the rest on the comments, run out of characters)

firstComment:
Fats and Cholesterol

When it comes to dietary fat, what matters most is the type of fat you eat. Contrary to past dietary advice promoting low-fat diets, newer research shows that healthy fats are necessary and beneficial for health. •	When food manufacturers reduce fat, they often replace it with carbohydrates from sugar, refined grains, or other starches. Our bodies digest these refined carbohydrates and starches very quickly, affecting blood sugar and insulin levels and possibly resulting in weight gain and disease. •	Findings from the Nurses’ Health Study and the Health Professionals Follow-up Study show that no link between the overall percentage of calories from fat and any important health outcome, including cancer, heart disease, and weight gain. ⁃	Rather than adopting a low-fat diet, it’s more important to focus on eating beneficial “good” fats and avoiding harmful “bad” fats. Fat is an important part of a healthy diet. Choose foods with “good” unsaturated fats, limit foods high in saturated fat, and avoid “bad” trans fat.

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'whole foods good moods'
firstComment:
🌽🥑🥕🍋🍒🥝🥒🍎⁠
⁠
The last post already highlighted the close connection between the brain and the gut. As much as you can soothe your gut by calming down your nervous system, you can shape your energy and mood by making more gut-loving food choices. ⁠
⁠
Two of the biggest gut health disruptors are sugar and processed foods as they alter the microbiome and diminish the variety of the good gut bacteria. These will communicate with your brain to signal that things are splendid below the naval and energy and mood can go up. If too much sugar and processed foods have been crashing the party for too long, the bad gut bacteria will take over and you'll feel the effects.⁠
⁠
It does not mean that you will never be able to have candy or chocolate again or that that frozen pizza's are forever crossed off the grocery list - it simply means being mindful of the frequency of these foods in your daily nutrition and reducing these things, especially if you've snacked on mindlessly without even registering what goes into your mouth.⁠
⁠
What are the more gut-loving food choices then?⁠
⁠
⭐ whole foods are key, meaning a lot of fresh produce in your daily diet, eg fresh vegetables and fruit⁠
⭐ try to give plants the main stage on your plate, especially the leafy green ones: always choose a veggie side when you're ordering food or cooking at home. These are prebiotics, meaning they will provide the food for your good gut bacteria⁠
⭐ try to choose the unprocessed form: if you have the choice between fries and potatoes ➡️ choose the potato, if you have to pick between noodles or rice ➡️ rice will be most likely lesser processed⁠
⁠
Check out the last post on how to help reduce gut issues like bloating and constipation in times of stress, if you missed it 📩⁠

firstComment:
A Homestay Wellness Tip
Drink Beta - carotene, immunity -boosting juice.
At this time it's become more than important to stay mindful of what we eat and drink.
Each day, I'm preparing new juices that are filled with vibrant and fresh ingredients.
One of my mum's favourite is this fresh Tomato - Carrot juice.
I prefer to first peel and steam both the tomato and carrot. Although washing reduces all microbes, they can still stay in the vegetables, so prefer not to take a chance and compromise your health.
Blend the two together, mash and strain it.
Then add fresh ginger, organic turmeric powder and squeeze some fresh lemon juice.
This juice has a high concentration of antioxidants vitamin C and vitamin A. It can help to keep off infections and enhances immune functions due to the high concentration of Beta - carotene.
I hope you enjoy this drink too. Do post your comments here.
Love & Light - Lovina

firstComment:
REPOST: @plantifulfacts .
.
.
Our ideal pH is alkaline. You can test your pH levels regularly by using a piece of litmus paper in your saliva or urine first thing in the morning before eating or drinking anything.
-
By including pH balance in my approach to health and healing, through wellness and nutrition, I have seen repeatedly students bodies and minds rebuild on their own from all kinds of degenerative conditions.  I have found that addressing an over acidic system is fundamental to bringing the body back to vitality and homeostasis. As you will see it is key to balancing all other systems.
-
1. DIGESTIVE SYSTEM - Most digestive disorders, such as indigestion, nausea, bloating, gastric reflux, are symptoms caused by excess acid in the gastric region and not enough alkaline minerals in the intestinal tract.
-
2. CIRCULATORY SYSTEM - Acidity is the principal cause of heart disease.
-
3. IMMUNE SYSTEM - Acidic environments are breeding grounds for anaerobic pathogens whereas the high levels hydrogen of rich body fluids keep bad bacteria inactive.
-
4. RESPIRATORY SYSTEM - When the tissues and organs are overloaded by acidity the transport of oxygen is strangled.
-
5. SKELETAL SYSTEM - Arthritis is one of the most disabling diseases in developed countries. The word arthritis means "inflammation of the joint"
-
6. INTEGUMENTARY SYSTEM - Commonly know as the skin. When the body's pH is out of balance then the build up of acid causes inflammation and the skin is less able to function as a natural barrier against infection.
-
7. NERVOUS SYSTEM - Acidity weakens the nervous system by depriving it of energy.
-
8. EXCRETORY SYSTEM - This is also known as the urinary system. It is made up of multiple organs, the main one being the kidneys. The kidneys perform the task of filtering fluids and purifying our blood.
-
9. MUSCULAR SYSTEM - When acidity increases in the muscle cells, it disrupts the metabolism breakdown of glucose and oxygen to energy.
-
-

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, smoking and text
firstComment:
Today's universe presence delivered by:
Janice 🤘
.
After last night's moderately shit nights sleep, I found myself standing next to a real rough and tumble, nicotine scented older woman named Janice 🚬
We exchanged pleasantries and she ended up telling me how her mother recently died. Fast forward⏩ and I hear how Janice's mother was extremely strict and bullied her- but Janice thought she was just "old school".
.
Janice got pregnant at 18, and her mother sent her away so the neighbours wouldn't see and talk about it 😳, and told her she was not to see the baby after it was born and was for resume life and not tell anyone she gave birth.
10 years later she had another son... He drowned at the age of 2.
Janice's words were:
"It broke me. I lost my boy. I can't do it again". I said "How did you?" And she said:
"You just have to get on with it love, but you're just a bit sadder every day now"💔
.
👉Janice would have killed to have another night with her son like I had with Elyse last night. I have what she lost, and I don't know why.

alt: Photo by Emma G. Dunne on March 18, 2020.
firstComment:
Is this coming from a place of fear or a place of love?

A question that I have learnt to ask myself more and more over the past couple of years. It is a question that reveals what is driving thoughts, feelings, actions and behaviours. And it is a question that brings awareness to what is truly going on within.

It is okay to be fearful and to be scared. But when we allow this emotion to continuously take over our thoughts and actions, we become limit, restrict, and resist life. 
My invitation to you, particularly in this time of where fear may be felt more overtly than usual, to use this to really get to know how it feels, where it is in your body, how it shapes your thoughts and how it influences your actions. Allow it to be there, and then see if you can let it go, and embrace love and gratitude, even just for a moment. 
When we shift our perspective from fear to love, we allow for acceptance, calmness and peace. We can still take care and look after ourselves and others. But we can also truly live and flow with freedom. And I assert that is a much more enjoyable way to live. 
And please remember that if you feel you need help or support, do reach out - to loved ones, friends or a professional. I am more than happy to help 💛 .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, sitting and outdoor
firstComment:
Nearly one week in social isolation (at the advice of my OB) and it is amazing how quickly you miss the little things- exploring suburbs around you, the morning office coffee run, all-day direct sunshine (our backyard gets it right now for about 3 hrs a day), heading to the grocery store for a well-stocked item like tissues or household cleaner... the end of Covid-19 can’t come fast enough. . 
But regardless, it’s a nice time to remind ourselves that we can and do take things for granted in ‘normal’ life (I know I do): heading to well-stocked shops, buying whatever organic grass-fed item we want when we want (so damn fussy), heading to Barre with girlfriends, laughing mid-convo in an office meeting, a workplace office of your own (rather than the dining table at home), access to exceptional health care... Don’t get me wrong- I’m grappling with this flowing situation and the potential implications it may have for my pregnancy, family and friends, I’m anxious and incredibly worried but this scary time is a good reminder to focus on what’s really important and how lucky we are in our ‘normal’ daily lives. Sometimes it’s easy to forget, but as these little belly kicks get stronger, I’m constantly reminded of what should be my (and our) priorities. We can be loving, strong, compassionate, brave and stand together, regardless of how far apart we must stand physically. (And meanwhile, thank goodness for Skype, WhatsApp, email, the internet, food delivery, couriers and Australia Post!..and let’s be honest, if I wasn’t pregnant I’m sure I’d be thanking Dan Murphy’s/ Jimmy Brings too 😜)
.
Today may be scary, unpredictable and anxiety-inducing, but our future remains bright if we can all focus on those things really important to us, and try to remember the silver linings. I’m no expert in this scenario, but its how I’m trying to approach it. After all, I’m aware that I’m literally holding the future in my hands (and belly) 😘 #positivevibesonly .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

It’s cold here in New York and I’ve been told it’s getting colder in the coming weeks. I must say my skin has taken a bashing and it’s dry (and irritated) when I don’t usually get troublesome skin at all. It might be the weather but I’m convinced the chemicals and pollution do nothing but cause havoc on the skin and internally.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So how do I stay healthy?⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Drink water! (I’m dehydrated from travelling no doubt). I also use plant oils on my skin and very gentle natural products. Even my crazy bright lipstick is vegan and quality ingredients I’m ok with.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m shocked at the lack of knowledge around the chemicals people eat and put on to their body (and into it through their skin! It only takes 26secs for something on your skin to travel to your blood eeeeek!!!) If you can’t eat it, don’t put it on your body.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
And if you can eat it, make sure it’s clean and simple...made from plants and of the earth (eg. mineral makeup). Watch out for deodorants with more than a handful of ingredients too! They are nasty and mess up your lymphatic system and don’t help if you’d like to avoid cancer.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

One of our household chore tips 🏠 to stop spreading bacteria :

At home we usually clean our outdoor shoes every week (during weekends), especially me because I am working 5 days a week to maintain the cleanliness in our area, I usually put them in  one corner, we also have seperate slippers inside and outside of our house. Because shoes pick up sneaky bacteria which are then spread about your home when you wear shoes inside. According to study from the University of Arizona collected germs and microbes on footwear. The researchers found hundred  units of bacteria on the outside of the shoe, including E. coli, meningitis, diarhea, infections and more. And because of the lockdown/quarantine. I will put now my shoes in their designated boxes. It's time for my shoes to rest for a while.  How about you guys do you have some household chore tips to share ? ☺️ .

firstComment:
𝓦𝓱𝓪𝓽’𝓼 𝓾𝓹 𝓰𝓵𝓸𝔀 𝓾𝓹? ✨

I remember looking at myself in the mirror about six months after my son was born and feeling so torn. I was so grateful and my spirit was so full of joy with my son and my new title as a mom. I was so amazed at what my body had been able to do and create. 
But my body was also unrecognizable to me. I was the heaviest I had ever been aside from pregnancy. My clothes didn’t fit well. I was so self conscious and fatigued all the time.

I was convinced that this was just...ya know motherhood. I began settling for fatigue, pain, shame.

Then I became consumed with the thought of getting my “old body back.” What if...just what IF I could look like that again? That super fit high school/early college version of my body (swipe left). I could have that back right? Then I would feel worthy again, beautiful again, right? Nice try. ✨

𝓓𝓪𝓻𝓵𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓭𝓲𝓭𝓷’𝓽 𝔂𝓸𝓾 𝓴𝓷𝓸𝔀? 𝓨𝓸𝓾 𝓪𝓻𝓮 𝓼𝓸 𝓶𝓾𝓬𝓱 𝓶𝓸𝓻𝓮 𝓲𝓷𝓽𝓮𝓻𝓮𝓼𝓽𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓽𝓱𝓪𝓷 𝔂𝓸𝓾𝓻 𝓯𝓵𝓮𝓮𝓽𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓹𝓱𝔂𝓼𝓲𝓬𝓪𝓵 𝓫𝓮𝓪𝓾𝓽𝔂. ✨

Why would I want to go back? Why would I seek something which “once was” when right in front of me I had a reason to fight for a body AND soul that were holistically well. Why would I want to go back when it was THIS body that created life? THIS body and mind that now had gained inner strength and wisdom. I didn’t need to fight for what “once was.” I needed to fight for every present moment, to live purposefully, to honor my breath and choose wellness. Because my best is yet to come and no day is promised.

So bring on that mama glow. That heart full of wisdom, that fiery soul. Chains are broken. Life is beautiful. And I’m here 🙌🏻 for 🙌🏻 it🙌🏻.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, people standing, tree and outdoor
firstComment:
Do you obsess over the scale??⠀
I used to🙋🏼‍♀️🤦🏼‍♀️⠀
.⠀
In the past I would weigh myself every single day.. every morning, evening, sometimes 3-5x per day. It was horrible, if I didn’t like what I saw in the morning it would completely change my mood and I would be fighting the negative self talk for the rest do the day. I was obsessed with it.⠀
.⠀
I want you to know that the scale does not define you, and it isn’t the best way to track your results!⠀
.⠀
If you are currently weighting yourself daily and it is negatively impacting your day try taking a step back and weight yourself once a week, once every 2 weeks, or once a month and see if that helps. I personally barely weigh myself now because I know that is isn’t the best for my mental health and it doesn’t show my true progress. There are so many factors that go into why your weight might be fluctuating!⠀
.⠀
Focus on how you feel, how your clothes fit, take progress photos, and measurements!!. And most importantly- LOVE your body for everything it is and does for you!⠀
⠀
⠀
You are beautiful!🤍🤍

firstComment:
As I look at these pictures side by side, I am in absolute awe of God’s goodness and His promises.
⠀⠀
The picture on the left was taken about 6 months in to our wellness journey we started as a couple in 2019. Our wellness journey actually didn’t start solely as a physical wellness journey. We knew we both wanted to be more active, but our consistent actions to physical wellness didn’t start until right after that pic on the left was taken.
⠀⠀
In January 2019 our wellness journey actually started with Dave Ramsey’s Financial Peace course. 9 Sunday evenings we met with couples just like us who were sick and tired of being sick and tired. And we made a decision to change our mindset, change our habits, and change our legacy.

In the left pic, we felt overwhelmingly blessed. Josh had just started a new job, we were gaining momentum (FINALLY) in our debt snowball, and we were gaining confidence in our journey. We had no idea that just 5 months later we would take the pic on the left and we would be celebrating some awesome things.
.

1️⃣ the successful start of physical wellness journeys that turned into another source of income.
.

2️⃣ almost $25k of debt paid off (we hit that by Dec 2019! And most of it was done between these two pics).
.

3️⃣ regained confidence, spiritual wellness, and joy found in our willingness to say yes to opportunities the Lord placed at our feet (worship leaders, wellness coaches, social media advisors) and so much more.

You see...what we didn’t realize in Jan 2019 and even at the time the pic on the left was taken...is that when you say YES to wellness in one area of your life, the Lord does a pretty amazing job at revealing paths to wellness in ALL areas of our lives.
.

What areas of wellness are ready to say YES to this year? What areas of your life are you ready to see transformed by Lord’s grace and goodness? If you’re ready to #choosejoy this year, I’d love to chat with you mire about my own journey and help you find joy in yours!

Are you ready to be transformed? Say yes babe.

firstComment:
⠀
I have a lot of goals for the upcoming year, but these are a few things that I really want to prioritize in 2020. ⠀
⠀
This year was really about changing my relationship with food and learning not to turn to it for comfort. I feel like I’ve made really great strides with that and now I want to focus more on intentional weight loss.⠀
More focus on calorie deficit and more time at the gym to see what my body is capable of.⠀
⠀
I’m lucky enough that I have people in my life that are always asking to get together and I always put it off because I didn’t want them to see how much weight I had gained or I was afraid of going out and not fitting into a booth or even breaking furniture at a restaurant.  I don’t want to live in fear anymore and I want to see the people that want to see me! It’s nice that people want to get together with me and I want to take advantage of that.⠀
⠀
I hate dating - I always feel awkward and weird and uncomfortable, but it’s necessary if I don’t want to die alone. I started this page because I was so heartbroken after my relationship ended and I needed something to focus on other than my heart break, but I think I need to push myself to move on now.  I don’t know if the heart break ever really fully heals, but again - don’t want to die alone.⠀
⠀
I’m going to continue making monthly goals like I did this year because it was such a great way to focus on a few things at a time to build lasting changes. I don’t remember what month it was that I made a goal to dance every day, but I shake my booty around my house now so much more than I used to! The monthly goals were great for me.⠀
⠀
I really want next year to just be about pushing myself more, physically and emotionally, and really seeing what I’m capable of.

Holy crap! A lot of people are sick out there. What on earth is going on?! If you’re like “2020 is the year I refuse to get knocked down sick”, here’s some things we do to attempt to avoid all the garbage: + eat less sugar. I know, hilarious considering the time of year, but sugar will murder your immune system.
+ drink all the water. Half your body weight in ounces is a good rule of thumb. So you weigh 100lbs, drink 50oz water. You’ll be BFF with you toilet in no time!
+ oils. Guys, get on the wagon. Frank, Thieves, Lemon, Oregano, Clove, Cinnamon Bark are just a few of my immune system favs. The easiest way to use is with rollers that get rolled along the spine and bottoms of feet daily, and diffusing. Our house smells good and we’re getting great health benefits at the same time. Oils must be pure (hi, Young Living) and used consistently or it’s useless.
+ elderberry. I make a syrup infused with YL oils that I love and also order gummies for my kids. They go back and forth on the purple juice and I need to get it in their bodies. Gummies it is.
+ vitamin c. I swallow a YL horse pill and the kids take a YL chewable.
+ Inner Defense. This is my ride or die immune system supplement. It nips all the ish. I have half a bottle left and ordered two more and refuse to live in a house without it. It’s that good.
+ probiotics. Have you heard that your gut totals up 70% of your entire immune system? Feed it good bacteria. Again, YL over here. Me: Life9, kids: Mightypro.
+ wash your hands and use Thieves Hand Sanitizer when on the go.

It’s not a perfect system, because we do get sick, but it helps so much. We get sick less, way less. When we are sick, it’s much less sever and passes faster.

What are your stay healthy tricks?

firstComment:
2019: the year I cried a lot & didn’t accomplish my goals. Also one of my favourite years so far.

2019 had some major growth, and that only happens in discomfort. I chose to go off of my antidepressants and I experienced a lot of emotions. I also was vulnerable in a new way, as waves of anxiety and depression I hadn’t felt in a long time rushed in. I felt vulnerability as I said “I’m not okay and I don’t know what to do about it.” And it brought me closer to Joe & my family & friends who already cared and were just waiting for me to let them help me.

I needed to sit with some uncomfortable feelings. I learned that hustling to check another box and do everything and do it perfectly was actually paralyzing me and leading me to avoid my feelings. I learned it’s important to set goals for how I want to feel as well as what I want to do.

I’m ending 2019 content. Overwhelmed by the blessings around me I didn’t earn. I’m learning to be okay with not controlling everything. Growing in an understanding that I am enough, and  there is enough grace for my shortcomings.

2020 holds big things (like a WEDDING...what?!). I want to enjoy every minute along the way. There will be big goals and hard work. But those goals and hustle are coming from a place of joy & contentment. Not a fight to prove my worth.

Self doubt, fear, procrastination - I think we all experience those things but I let them control me for a long time and I’m ready to move on from that.

But it’s necessary for my growth that I really push myself to stop wallowing in these negative patterns and a new year is a great time to do that.

alt: Image may contain: plant and food
firstComment:
Avena ✨ 
A principio de año la avena era algo que no incluida en mis comidas nunca, cero se me antojaba y ni se me pasaba por la cabeza incluirla en mi alimentación. 
Hoy es mi desayuno favorito y siento que es la manera que tengo de desayunar algo que me sepa a postre jajaja ✨🥰.
Les comparto mi receta favorita 💕 •
Ingredientes : 
Las porciones dependen de lo que tú Nutriologa/o recomiende de acuerdo a objetivos •Avena
•1/2 de Leche vegetal
•1/2 de Agua • 1 cucharadita mini de aceite de coco
•1/2 Plátano
•Canela al gusto •Vainilla al gusto • 10 mitades de nuez • un chorrito de miel de agave o mil maple sin azúcar •
En una olla chiquita pones la avena + la leche ( yo generalmente pongo la mitad de la porción de leche que me corresponde para la otra mitad poder usarla para acompañar mi desayuno con un capuchino☕️) + 1/2 taza de agua + canela al gusto + chorrito de vainilla + plátano machacado. Revuelves todo esto y a fuego medio tapas la olla y conforme vaya tomando la consistencia que quieres ve moviendo un poco para que no se pegue la mezcla a la olla. Cuando la avena está en la consistencia que quieres le apagas al fuego y le pones una cucharadita de aceite de coco y revuelves bien todo ✨ •
Por otra parte puse una parte de la porción del plátano en un sartén con nueces , canela y vainilla a qué se caramelizara un poco y una vez que la avena está lista le puse esto como topping. 
Le puse un mini chorrito de miel de maple sin azúcar •

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'NSV Comfortably using a public bathroom and not having to contort my body to wipe'
firstComment:
Having to use a public bathroom at my largest size was challenging, frustrating, and quite honestly, humiliating. I’m a clean freak, and trying to make sure my body wasn’t accidentally sitting on or touching anything gross while also making sure everything was wiped and cleaned properly was an effort. ⠀
⠀
Any time I’ve had to use a public bathroom in the past few years, I’ve always tried my best to get the largest stall. The other night I went out for dinner and had to use their restroom. I went in, and the large stall was taken. So I had to use the small one. And I did - without any problem. I didn’t feel gross after, I didn’t have to twist my body all around to wipe, it was fine. It was a relief. ⠀
⠀
I used to dread having to use the bathroom at work. It was partly why I didn’t drink as much water as I should. Most of the stalls are tiny, the toilets are set weirdly low to the ground, and it’s just difficult to maneuver in. But the last few months, I haven’t had a problem. And that’s been a relief too.⠀
⠀
It’s not just about the before and after photos for me, although I love those. This journey is about regaining my self-respect and confidence and self-worth. I went to a real, raw, and vulnerable place to share this and it’s uncomfortable. But we grow outside our comfort zone. ⠀
Moving like the waves💜 How are you moving today? #wavelove #oceanbeach #wavesarethebest #oceanlover #freeflowing #howareyoumovingtoday #opentopossibilities #wellnessasone #wellnessjourney2019

alt: Photo by Amanda on December 22, 2019.
firstComment:
Happy weigh-in Sunday because I forgot to do it Friday! I’ve basically stayed at the same weight since thanksgiving, and that’s okay. ⠀
Normally my vacations and holidays revolve around food and I would literally try to stuff in as much as possible, because my thinking was that I had to get it all in and then start dieting in January. ⠀
⠀
For the past few weeks I haven’t been focused on losing weight but really just navigating through all the yummy treats and my schedule being weird and having dinners out with friends....and I’ve been doing okay. There were a few nights that I wanted to grab fast food and I forced myself to cook something I had at home, because I knew I would feel like crap if I ate from a drive-thru. ⠀
That’s probably the number one difference this year than in years past, I am consciously making an effort to eat as many meals at home, because I can control the ingredients and serving sizes. ⠀
⠀
It’s been all about the small changes for me this year!!!

alt: Image may contain: text
firstComment:
🥀Full disclosure...I’ve been falling in the trap of feeling more like a weed than a flower again lately 😕
.
I guess I’ve always considered myself a “feelings” person, and I’ve been letting some negative thought patterns push me back into my comfy corner of hiding and feeling insecure... like maybe I just don’t fit in the flower garden. 🤷🏼‍♀️
.
But... you know what? Who in the actual heck does?
.
Who gets to judge which flowers are “worthy” & which are the “weeds”? I’ve spent a million years chasing the praise of others...a deep, confusing need to be liked & accepted.
I’m not sure if that’s normal, but my normal can consist of second guessing what the ‘flowers’ are thinking... that often leaves me judging my own ‘weediness’
.
But... one part of getting old that’s been rather refreshing is saying
- who freaking cares what others think??? -
.
Sweet friends, my prayer for you is to learn this lesson a whole lot earlier than I did 🙏🏻
.
I say together 👉🏻let’s be the wildest, weediest flowers🌻, you & me... the ones that the perfect landscaped flowerbeds would never welcome♥️
.
We might not be for everyone; but we’ll always be for each other...and like any good weed patch, we can spread our love & acceptance right across the world 🙌🏻🌻🌷🌾🌱🦚
.
.
.
.
#weedsunite #selflove #flowerorweed #theydontknowaboutus #theiropinionisnoneofyourbusiness #prettyweeds #nestandflourish #wellnessjourney2019 #incourage #hopewriters #daughteroftheking #nojudgement #judgenot

alt: Photo by Shaina on December 15, 2019.
firstComment:
Say Hello to our 2019 Christmas tree. 👋🏼 .
We just moved into our new home this weekend and things have been chaotic. In the thick of all of it, hubby managed to pick up a small, pre-lit tree as I requested (usually we go for real). And Sharlett was inspired to decorate it in the basement while I was distracted & busy with life upstairs. .
I’m so inspired by her creativity and her class. 😍 Look closely and you’ll find measuring cups, fake cheese, Disney dress-up outfits, a baby hat tree-topper and a money-train around the base. 😆 .
How did she just know I would need this kind of tree to bring some Christmas spirit into my life this year? 💕 🌲 ✨ .
#christmastreedecorating #christmasspirit #christmastimeishere #wellnessjourney2019 #debtfreeliving #minimalistchristmas #simpleliving #mommasgirlforever

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and indoor
firstComment: I said NO thanks when I first heard about these workouts. I hate burpees and this trainer was like “here do 50,” and I was like noooooppeee bye ✌🏼💃🏻but then I hit a plateau, I figured whatever, I need something to challenge myself. I was skeptical, I was a hesitant, and I prefer weights over cardio, and even the smallest amount of cardio does NOT motivate me.... but here I am, on the final day of round 1. This may be the end of another program but for me it is the beginning of a new journey for my body. Tomorrow starts round 2, if you don’t challenge your body you won’t see the results you dream of. Put in the work and anything is possible.  Are you ready to focus on your own goals as we get ready to head into 2020?!

alt: Photo by Kira Andersen on December 14, 2019.
firstComment:
It felt so GOOD I wanted to cry. 
My word for 2019 is “change,” so I’ve been reflecting on that lately. 
I made a change to my schedule so I could rise early and read. I loved it. My days felt so much more calm and clear when I did. 
Then life happened and I know that keeping chronic illness from running my life takes careful management. So I had to put my health first and rising early to read, aside. 
But, the big hurdles are past and I’m up early today. It feels so good I wanted to cry. 
Do you like to read? What are you reading right now? (Audio books totally count as reading, IMO!) #risingearly #personaldevelopmentjunkie #growthmindset🌱 #readtogrow #wellnessjourney2019 #migrainewarrior #chronicillnesswarrior #changeyourmindset #getbackupagain #determination

alt: Image may contain: drink
firstComment:
Had to restock the bathrooms and kitchen with handsoap tonight. And in less than 5 minutes I had all sinks ready to go with Christmas Spirit ♥️
.
Here is what I used to make an 8oz bottle of foaming handsoap: •Foaming Hand Soap Dispenser- I am resuing ones I already have #recycle
•1/4 cup Unscented Liquid Castile Soap
•1/2 teaspoon Vitamin E Oil
•10-15 Drops Essential Oil… I am using the blend Christmas Spirit ♥️ you can substitute this with your favorite oil/oil combination - my regular favorite is the Thieves blend!
•1-2 Drops Orange Essential Oil (Optional)
•Approximately 6 oz. Distilled Water
.
In a glass bowl or container, add the Vitamin E oil and your essential oils. Stir to combine. Add in the Castile soap and gently stir. Pour this mixture into soap dispenser and then gradually pour in the distilled water. Gently swirl to combine and twist on your foaming pump. Voila! 
So stinkin' easy, no harsh chemicals or "fragrance", inexpensive 
I've had this container of Dr Bronner's for almost a year so far. Lasts FOREVER
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and closeup
firstComment:
The last month has been absolutely crazy traveling for work and living out of a suitcase a lot. .
.
I’m not going to lie. I am tired. It was hard to get up this morning to exercise and stay on track. But, I knew the amazing team of women that support me were going to get up and do it. So I made it down to the small hotel gym.
.
.
When I walked in, all of the treadmills were full. I remember the days not too long ago of being stressed about what time I needed to get down to the gym to make sure I got a treadmill when I was on the road.
.
.
This morning, I had a workout downloaded on my phone and found an open area. It was like having my own personal trainer lead me through an intense workout. Cardio, weights, balance, flexibility.  I got an all over workout and left the gym, and those same people were slogging away on the treadmills.
.
.
It took me months of dragging my feet to join this program. All of the self- limiting questions went through my head: will this work? Should I spend money on this?  Is this just a scam? I am so glad that I jumped in. There is no going back for me. .
.
Are you ready to do something different? You just have to take the first step.
.
.
#uplifttribe #roadtowellness #changestartswithyou #womeninspiringwomen #newstart2020 #wellnessjourney2019 #takethefirststep

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, people standing, selfie and phone
firstComment:
#Repost @katejordhamo
• • • • • •
Denver, Colorado

how many times have you heard someone say that success is a decision?⠀
⠀
that all you have to do is wake up, decide you are not going to fail, and boom — success.⠀
⠀
well let me tell you — “success is a decision” is total bullshit. it completely minimizes the fact that you’re going to have to put in some work if you want to see some results.⠀
⠀
here’s the thing — you can’t just wake up, decide you’re going to be successful, and then just expect success to flow. ⠀
⠀
you can’t decide you won’t fail, then do the bare minimum, and still expect results. ⠀
⠀
truthfully, one decisions isn’t going to fundamentally change your life. it’s making a ton of decisions consistently, every single day, to put in the work to get to your goals.⠀
⠀
so if you’re out there telling people you just decided to be successful — don’t minimize all of the hard work you put in to get to where you are! take some credit for all of that hustle, and let everyone know exactly how much consistent effort you put in to create the success they see today.⠀
⠀
because success is not a decision. it’s millions of decisions, over and over again, to keep moving towards that goal.
.
.
.
#successmindsets #everystepcounts #successisadecision #workforit💪 #dontwishforitworkforit #hardworkpaysoff💪 #keepgoingstrong #keepgoingkeepgrowing #settingintentions #mindsetmastery #youarestrongerthanyouknow #weightlossjourney2019 #weightlosstruggle #athomefitness #athomeworkouts #attitudeofgratitude💫

My journey hasn’t been perfect.
.
I honestly haven’t been nearly as consistent as I’d like to be throughout the last month but I have exercised more days than I haven’t!
.
This journey is about progress, not perfection. So don’t let the holidays, vacations, a fun night out, sickness or anything else make you feel like a failure or like you have to quit or start over and do it perfectly.
.
The only thing you have to let go of to be -healthier-fitter-stronger- is your excuses.

alt: Image may contain: food
firstComment:
Can I be honest? 
___
I haven’t followed a strict eating plan since I started my wellness journey this year. I have yet to master the art of meal prepping and when I do I don’t even feel like sticking to what I prepared. So the abs that I so dearly want have yet to show up. However, I have become much better at portion control which was not my strength in the past. So I allow myself grace in the process and continue on the journey that is on “my” chosen path and “my” chosen speed. 
___
With that said, tonight’s meal was a delightful stir fry vegan dish that I whipped up which was so satisfying! My kids had no complaints! Drop this emoji ->🍜 below if you want the recipe!

AUM  is the only three sounds that a human is capable of making without the tongue. All other sounds made with the tongue are simply a mixture of AUM for it is the root of all sounds. Each sound contains a specific vibrations when chanted, because the sound comes from the belly region, the vibration of the sound spreads through out your body and activates a part of your dimensional system. Therefore sound can activate your well being, health, and mental clarity. In addition the sound that comes out of your mouth also impacts you.  The moment you stop speaking your system changes because you’re no longer uttering harmful sounds. 
The eternal sound resides in you become aware of all that you say and begin to dismantle that habitual compulsive behavior of talking. Begin to care about all the things that you listen and how that music/ talking shows/ movies/ etc are affecting you on different levels. 
Make an effort to create a time during your every day when you do not speak for a length amount of time. What you experience can only be understood by those who do. -

alt: Dietitian teaching clients to make small changes that equal fat burn without making excuses about being busy all the time.
firstComment:
You don't need to overhaul your life to lose fat.👇👇👇
.
Every time I launch Metabolism Reset, I get messages saying, "I want to do this but I have xyz coming up/ I'm going on vacation, my friend's birthday party is in a week, etc." So....is next month going to be less busy somehow?  Does life ever NOT feel busy?
.
And what does being "busy" have to do with eating in a way that makes you feel good & supports a healthy metabolism?🤷‍♀️ Right now, guys.  THIS is the time you need to be taking care of your body...when you are overwhelmed and "busy". I get it.  You say this because every other program you have invested in requires you to:
👉cut out foods you enjoy or eat regularly
👉eat all your meals at home
👉follow a plan to a T & don't even think about cheating...
.
You don't have guidance on how to navigate holidays realistically, how to go on vacation & eat like a normal person or see progress without counting every morsel of food you eat.🤦‍♀️
.
I'm here to blow your mind.🤯
.
There are some really easy steps you can take every single day - regardless of whether you are at home in your underwear or on a 7-night Caribbean cruise - that will help you rev up your metabolism and help you attain the fat loss you are looking for.
.
1️⃣Include PROTEIN at each and every meal.  Protein is not as convenient as carbs but making it a priority at each meal can make a huge difference.  It helps you to feel full & actually revs up your metabolism.
.
2️⃣Preload your day with healthy fat.  Instead of your normal fruit smoothie, try adding some healthy fat like 1 Tbsp of almond butter or chia seeds.  Instead of your skinny latte, add some heavy cream.  Stay full longer and put your body in fat-burning mode.
.
3️⃣Stop skipping meals.  When you undereat, your body holds onto fat.  You need to EAT to burn fat.
.
Small, realistic habits = big FAT-BURNING changes that last for good. ⚡️Through Sunday, get $50 off Metabolism Reset. ⚡️We start January 6th but you get immediate access as soon as you sign up.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, people standing, shoes, tree, child and outdoor
firstComment:
Tofurkey Trot 2019 - ⠀
This was a big deal for me! I haven’t done an organized race in a long time. ⠀
⠀
For years I wasn’t healthy enough to run or even walk 3.1 miles. I was starving to death and an event like a simple Turkey Trot could have been deadly. ⠀
⠀
But the last few times I did organized races it was during a particularly difficult depressive episode. After high school I fell into a deep depression for many years. I slept a lot, gained a lot of weight and spent years unable to work or go to school because it was so bad. During that time my family was worried and tried to help by getting me to do 5k races during the holidays as family events. There was a lot of pressure from the more athletic members of my family and an attitude that exercise would cure my depression and help me lose weight. I internalized their pressure and only felt more shame for not being as fit or thin as they were. I was horribly ashamed of my body and being compared to the other women in my family only amplified that shame. I didn’t need forced exercise. I needed compassion and understanding. ⠀
⠀
Since then I have actively boycotted organized races. But this year I thought it was time to reclaim the Turkey Trot. Running has become an important part of my life in recovery and a huge source of joy! I didn’t run this morning to earn my dinner. I ran to get some fresh air, to move my body, and spend time with my stepmom, someone I love dearly and cherish my time with. ⠀
⠀
For the first time EVER I had FUN at the #TurkeyTrot2019 🍁🍂 ⠀
⠀
#SoGrateful ⠀
#VeganThanksgiving #TofurkeyTrot #TurkeyTrot #BoiseTurkeyTrot #Recovery #runnersofig #edrecovery #anorexiarecovery #thanksgiving2019🍁🍂

alt: Image may contain: text
firstComment:
Every offer or opportunity isn’t worth it. Or in the words of my mom - all money aint good money.

When you are in an interview, understand that you are interviewing the other party just as much as they are interviewing you. And that’s to see if the PARTNERSHIP would be a good fit for you both.

Whether the exchange is for a job opportunity, collaboration, dating - whatever. You should be evaluating.

Make a list of traits/conditions that are deal breakers for you. When you are presented with things that don’t align with your needs, it is ok to pass on the opportunity/person.

Don’t own any negative labels for yourself - especially from a person 
that thinks their schedule, time, or needs are the only ones that matter.

This scenario speaks more to the type of employer and leader this person is vs the patience of the people who stuck around.

What would you have done?? Drop a comment.

#wellnessjourney2019 #wellnesswednesday #occupationalwellness #interviewingtips #jobsearchtips #healthandwellnessjourney

alt: Image may contain: text and food
firstComment:
Canada’s Food Guide underwent some rather huge changes in 2019!
.
There were 3 major changes:
🌱
1) The first was removing the number of suggested portions and replacing them with how much space certain foods should occupy on your plate (fruits and vegetables comprising half the plate).
🌱
2) The second was removing one food group entirely and creating a combined section labeled ‘Proteins’ (which are comprised of primarily plant based proteins).
🌱
3)The third was to emphasize water💧as the drink of choice (removing fruit juices and milk entirely from the guide).
🌱
Along with these changes came a move to re-evaluate the conditions under which we prepare and consume our meals with an emphasis on preparing more home cooked meals eaten at the table with other people😊
🌱
Shoutout to Health Canada for applying these necessary changes to the outdated guide and for the bold move towards healthy living for all!
.
Thoughts?
.
.
.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, eyeglasses and closeup
firstComment:
It was an incredibly difficult morning.
.
.
I woke up and my anxiety was through the roof. I laid in bed for 3 hours feeling overwhelmed, behind and like there was a million things to do, with the overarching theme of failure.
.
On the verge of tears, I withdrew into the covers and tried to express to Matt what I was feeling, or why I was feeling it.
.
It’s a work from home day with very limited items on my to-do list, I get to stay home with Matt and Evie, the sun is shining and I’m not “failing” anything.
.
I had no rationale, and that made me feel even worse.
.
Matt was incredible, doing and suggesting everything he could think of to make me feel safe and capable. I finally asked him if he could make my pre-workout for me. He did, and brought it to me in bed so I could drink it down.
.
You see, committing to a full workout feels daunting some days. Even if only for 30 minutes. I don’t have a secret motivation super power.
.
I just drink my pre, and do the workout. Committing to drinking my pre is not so daunting - and once the pre is consumed, what good is it without doing the workout?
.
So I drank my pre, pulled myself out of bed, pushed play and I’m feeling better.
.
Am I saying working out “cured” my anxiety today? No, but I am saying it helped pull me out of a deep funk that, in the past, would have kept me bed-ridden all day long.
.
So if you’re having a rough day, if your mental health is keeping you down, if you just can’t give it your all for some reason...I hear you, I see you, I’m with you. And if all you did today was breathe, I’m so proud of you.
.
Thank you for listening. 💕

#wellnessjourney2019 #holisticwellness #justbreathe

alt: Image may contain: outdoor
firstComment:
Who’s with me and hate counting calories⁉️⁣
⁣
Did I get all my macros in for the day❓⁣
⁣
Do I have to stuff my face at night to meet my requirements❓⁣
⁣
It’s only 2pm and I ate all my allotted macros for the day❓⁣
⁣
Who else is over this bullshit?⁉️⁣
⁣
Comment with a thumbs up below.⁣
⁣
I’m drawing a line in the sand here and calling bullshit on the whole counting calories and calories in vs calories out.⁣
⁣
First off, if this is true. Go eat 2,500 calories of ice cream or McDonalds and see how you feel compared to 2,500 calories of organic meats, fruits and veggies. There’ll be a significant difference. ⁣
⁣
Secondly, Your body’s requirements fluctuates on a daily basis. You may need more calories one day and fewer the next. You may need more protein one day or more carbs another day. A set amount of protein, fats, and carbs for each day isn’t appropriate nor is it easy and fun to follow. ⁣
⁣
Third. Who wants to cut, weigh, cook, measure, etc ALL of your meals - that is nonsense and extremely time consuming!⁣
⁣
If you’re sick of counting calories or logging them on myfitnesspal comment with a thumbs up!⁣
⁣
I much rather eat healthy foods, listen to what my body is telling me, and not fret over counting calories. If you learn my approach, counting calories, measuring, and weighing all go out the window to allow more time for you to enjoy life. ⁣
⁣

firstComment:
A cold and grey day in New York is a perfect reason to grab 2 comforts, a good read and a hot drink. ⁣
⁣
I’m newly obsessed with Mushroom Cacao CHILL Reishi beverage from @fourstigmatic ☕️ It’s absolutely delish! There is evidence that suggests the effectiveness of the Reishi mushroom for immune system support, stress reduction and improved sleep. I added some steamed Macadamia milk from @milkadamia for some lovely latte richness. You must try this Macadamia milk...O-M-G!⁣
⁣
I’m reading about emotions and oils in the book Releasing Emotional Patterns with Essential Oils by Dr. Carolyn Mein. The concept of emotional cleansing with essential oils is FASCINATING! The concept is that we can access stuck emotions with essential oils since oils can access the limbic portion of the brain. The limbic system is the area of the brain most heavily implicated in emotions and memory. This releasing technique is thought to have been practiced by the ancient Egyptians. Mind-blown!! 🤯 I can tell you that I have first hand experience in using essential oils to support my emotions. Oils are absolutely amazing and have changed the way I live.⁣
⁣
I’m sinking deeper into my couch with these two comforts (well 3 including the Peace & Calming oil blend that I’m currently breathing in from my diffuser.) There may not be a better place to be at the moment. ⁣
⁣
All is good in my world.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and people standing
firstComment: I found the pic on the left from about 4 years ago. It was when I had first gotten into the 300’s and I was desperate to take it off. I joined a DietBet (which is why I’m on the scale) and I don’t think I ever signed in after that first day. I don’t know why, but once I hit 300 pounds, I just felt defeated. Like I was never going to be a normal, healthy, LIVABLE weight. Livable as in, enjoying my life and being able to actually participate in it. Not having to worry about running out of breath just going shopping, or that I won’t fit into a booth, or that I’ll break a chair, or not being able to take cooking classes because I can’t be on my feet that long (there’s a reason I’m taking so many now...because I CAN). There’s maybe 15 pounds between these pics and although you may not be able to see huge differences, I can see that my stomach is carrying so much less weight, which makes it so much more comfortable for me. My hips are slimming down, so I don’t bump into so many things anymore. I have more energy and I feel better, but most importantly, I have hope. I don’t know how to explain how it felt to not have hope, or to even realize as I’m writing this that I had lost hope for a long time. But now I feel hope again, and excitement for my life right now and for my future. It’s a great feeling.

alt: Image may contain: sky, ocean, outdoor, nature and water
firstComment:
How are you r e a l l y doing at bettering yourself ....? ⁣
⁣
You know, that goal you set to change your ways? To bust through old habits with a, “new year new me” attitude. ⁣
⁣
Well if you’re like me you’ll want to read this... 🙋🏻‍♀️ Here’s the 4 stages of self-development and ways to overcome your self-development hurdles. (swipe ⇨ + save for later)⁣
⁣
1. Attitude + Belief. ⁣
*tip: You need to want to change. Plain and simple, this comes from within. Try self-reflection exercises or envision yourself 10 years from now, do you like your trajectory? ⁣
⁣
2. Knowledge + Education. ⁣
*tip: You need to educate yourself on HOW you’re going to change. Find podcasts, instagram accounts, YouTube videos, research articles, workshops + classes that help give you the info on how and why you should change.⁣
⁣
💥 Here you run the risk of failure changing your beliefs. Don’t let failure turn into procrastination or rationalization like, “Oh I messed up, I’ll start again next Monday.” NO! Be aware of this risk, fight through. Get back on track right away.⁣
⁣
3. Practice + Support.⁣
*tip: You’ve made it this far. Now you need to keep implementing because practice makes permanent. To stay on track until you form a new habit you need a support system, an accountability partner or a coach with skills to keep you motivated. Or you need to be able to fight resistance and dig deep for a purpose that pushes you through.⁣
⁣
4. Skill + Habit.⁣
*tip: Once you’ve reached this milestone you’ve created a new habit. Keep it up and watch your mindset. At anytime you can fall back into your old comfort zone.⁣
⁣
Awareness is power, don’t let your beliefs pull you into old habits! 👏🏼👏🏼 YOU’VE GOT THIS. 👏🏼👏🏼 What are you working on right now?! Tell me below ↓ ⁣
⁣
-⁣
-⁣

alt: Image may contain: food
firstComment:
I feel like my blood is 90% wine and pie at this point. My body has been begging me for a salad but with all the holiday festivities and eating out I am really just proud of myself if I can get two servings of veggies in a day!

I always approach nutrition by addressing what foods/behaviors you add in rather than what you take out, but I think this concept is especially important around the holidays. This is not the time for cutting out Christmas cookies or grandmas famous lasagna, instead focus on adding in the foods that make you feel good!

For me, that is greens. I always have more energy, am more regular, and generally feel better if I am eating my greens. So, this time of year I try and sneak some in each day by throwing a handful of spinach/broccoli into a scramble in the morning or having a salad with/for lunch. Of coarse I can’t do this every day but I certainly feel better when I do.

Right now I am loving the combo of BBQ sauce and apples. This salad is crunchy kale mix topped with air fried tofu tossed in BBQ sauce, apples, pumpkin seeds, Craisins, gorgonzola, and ranch. This salad combo tastes great with a maple tahini dressing too if you prefer!

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'If life gives you lemons, don't settle for simply making lemonade make a glorious scene at a lemonade stand Elizabeth Gilbert'
firstComment:
My friend-
Let's talk about mess, shall we?
I am not a quiet, meek, neat person by nature. I used to strive to be that person.

While my general tidiness could still use some work, I am working on this ---> embracing the hot-mess of a woman that I am 💜
.
I have faced some challenges in life. I have always hid my head in shame. Buried my body in over-sized clothes. Ate my way through ice cream, aka emotions. Wandered aimlessly through retail-therapy. I refused to believe anyone who told me they loved me: I was trained to not believe it. It was always a trick. Or it was an excuse. Or it was an apology. But it was never really love. Not loving ME for ME.

I tried making lemonade. I tried fitting in. I tried conforming to what would be pleasing and therefore accepting and therefore worthy of  love . The love that I constantly reject, yet cannot live without. 
And then, it finally hit me.

I make a glorious scene at the lemonade stand. THAT. IS. ME. And ... guess what? There are folks out there who know this already about me! 
Huh? 
What? 
And .... they like me anyway. Just as I am. As long as I am true to me.

So. Embrace this mess with me. Be You. Make a scene. 🍋

#elizabethgilbert

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, closeup
firstComment:
So
I did a thing
A purple thing
I hit the 1 year mark from my surgery.
The 1 year mark from when the weight started creeping back
And I was just tired of feeling (& looking) “blah”
And it has nothing to do with what anyone else thinks or feels or looks
It has everything to do with what’s happened since 2016
The onslaught
The stress
The loss
The joy
Just. All. Of. It. 
And so last year, August 2017 when the physical pain was extraordinary and the emotional anguish was going to crush me, I chopped it all off. 
Started growing it out. Natural color. Just to shed what had been. What it was. What was tearing me up from the inside.
Let it breathe. Let me breathe. Let it go. 
I don’t want drama. I just want peace. I want to you to be happy and in peace. It’s easy. No games.
🧘‍♀️
So. We’re now heading into a new year, and I wanted to feel like Me again. And oddly, this feels more like my old self. The person who was fit and healthy and had everything all sorted out.
🤷‍♀️
So. I did a thing.
This is me. Ending the year of trying to find my way back to health and strength and stamina...and life.
Alive.

alt: Image may contain: 1 person
firstComment:
I’ve been reflecting on my second round through #80dayobsession and trying not to beat myself up. I did not finish this round to completion because of an injury. I met some of my goals but others fell by the wayside. But I just keep reminding myself that I am human, I am perfectly imperfect and I deserve some grace. If I’m failing, I’m failing forward, and I am always learning. Here’s what I learned this go round:
.
.
•working out 2X per day does not mean better results and ultimately leaves you run down and can lead to injury
•fitness is not linear! There are ups and downs, ebbs and flows to your journey.
•nutrition is 80% of the battle, you can’t outrun your poor nutrition! •NEVER underestimate the power of a rest day! •cellulite does not define how beautiful your 🍑 is 🤣
.
.
I am so ready to recommit to a new program! I’m ready for a fresh start, shorter workouts and newfound energy!! ⚡️Bring it on 2019!

looking for fun festive cocktail that isn’t loaded with sugar? i got just the thing - skinny pomegranate moscow mules💃🏻
⠀
look i love a vodka soda as much as the next girl, but lets be honest, they’re pretty boring, and definitely not festive🎄but add a little ginger beer, pomegranate seeds & a fun garnish and you have a seriously impressive holiday cocktail on your hands💃🏻
⠀
👉🏼DO IT
• add a spoonful of pomegrante seeds to your glass & muddle ⠀
• pour in 1.5 ounces vodka (I love @titosvodka), a splash of ginger beer, a generous squeeze of lime & lemon
• add ice and fill the glass the rest of the way with soda water ⠀
• garnish with more pomegranate seeds, cranberries, & rosemary to feel festive AF💃🏻

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'PERFEC KE Tü ALMOND BUTTER BRO WNIE KETO BAR No ADDED SUGARS NO SUGAR ALCOHOLS 10 GRAMS OF PROTEIN'
firstComment:
new low-sugar/low-carb protein bar alert🚨
⠀
when im looking for a protein bar, I’m pretty picky. I want it to be low sugar (<4g), low net carb, have enough protein (10-15g), have real, clean ingredients (no soy protein isolates thx), and of course be gluten-free & dairy-free (low maintenance I know💁🏻‍♀️)
⠀
and that is seriously hard to find! most bars out there essentially glorified candy bars. even the “healthy” bars you’ll see all over the gram & in health food stores are often sugar bombs (remember: honey, dates, brown rice syrup, coconut sugar...it all still break downs to blood sugar in your body) ⠀
⠀
I’ve talked about the bars I love before - @bulletproof & @primalkitchenfoods - which are both delicious, low sugar (about 2-3g sugar) & low carb (about 6-10 net carbs), and I’m excited to add a new one to the rotation! ⠀
⠀
these keto bars by @perfectketones are CRAZY CLEAN - like really, I’ve never found a cleaner bar (and you definitely don’t have to be a keto diet to love them)
⠀
these bars have 10g protein, 9g fiber, only 3 net carbs & 1g of sugar! and no sugar alcohols!* LIKE WHAT
⠀
plus all the ingredients are simple, real foods - almond butter, cacao butter, collagen, cacao powder, coconut oil, tapioca fiber, stevia, sea salt💥
⠀
oh and they actually taste good😋 if you’re in the market for a new bar - highly recommend! ⠀
do you have protein bars often? which are your favs?
⠀
**i have sugar alcohols in moderation but they can cause an upset stomach in some people

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, closeup and outdoor
firstComment:
SELF-CARE ✨
•
No, this is not going to be a post offering self-care tips. I’m not going to tell you new ways to use coconut oil 🥥 or offer advice on how to get glowing skin. I’m here to talk about WHY we do self-care in the first place.
•
Self-care does not end with yourself. Read that again.... it DOES NOT end with YOU. It doesn’t mean only rose petal baths and luxurious massages. The purpose of self-care is so you can take all that good energy and help others.
•
In Ayurveda, there is a saying of “As is the microcosm so is the macrocosm”. This means the reason why we heal ourselves is so we can have an impact on the greater global environment 🌎 We are all connected and our souls chose to be here on this planet, at this exact time, to help others and make the world brighter ✨
•
So let that sink in as you do #selfcaresunday or do any type of self-care. Take all that good juju and put it back into the world.
•
Happy Sunday my friends 💕

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, standing, outdoor and nature
firstComment:
reminder: the universe is always bringing you what you need, as long as you stay open to receive it🙌🏼
⠀
story time - last night I stopped by @lululemonsf, and after trying on several pieces, found myself in a baddd head space in the dressing room (you know that feeling when you've been squeezing your body into skin-tight leggings & sports bras under florescent lighting surrounded by mirrors from every angle for 30 minutes? yeah, it'll really test your relationship with your body)
⠀
so suffice it to say, my brain was firing with negative self talk, and I was ready to go home ⠀
⠀
but as I was checking out the (incredibly sweet) cashier mentioned that while the store was about to close, they were staying open for a private meditation event, and invited me to join
⠀
and honestly, in the moment, nothing sounded worse. but i don't believe in coincidences - so when the universe offers you a meditation circle in the middle of your negativity spiral, you say yes
⠀
the meditation was (of course) EXACTLY what i needed. 10 minutes later that knot forming in my stomach was gone, and my racing mind was quiet and happy
⠀
moral of the story - the universe has your back (as @gabbybernstein would say), and is always conspiring to help you, you just have to be open to it✨
⠀
have you ever experienced something similar? let me know! xx

firstComment:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
« no. »
⠀⠀
+ rosa parks, 1955. || 🖤
⠀⠀
⠀⠀
————— ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
a tricky part of growth is, it can be a major trigger for others. i know this from my long history of feeling discomfort around people with strengths i wanted but couldn’t accept as things to work on. that version of me attaches her sense of self-worth to others, thinking everyone's strengths & blessings mean something bad about her. that me is an escapist who‘s really good at avoiding her self when confronted with characteristics she won’t own or disown. until she decided to take ownership of her life, she was never gonna break free with a growth mindset.
⠀⠀
i only talk about self-awareness, willpower, & positivity from personal experience. when i talk about those things, i’m sure people underestimate my struggles with them cuz i catch myself doing the same. (social media, man...) my compassion for living life without them comes from knowing damn well what it's like, & wanting to live in a world where less of us do. i *hate* making others uncomfortable, but realistically, empathy has its downsides, which is why i’ve had to get so selective with what & who i dish my energy out to & when.
⠀⠀
as a dreamer by nature, 
i *have*  to stay grounded by nurture.
⠀⠀
that’s why many of the people i admire & share values with disagree on extending emotional resources to people who can’t match us on self-accountability. i’ve been the person who needs her dysfunctional thoughts & ways validated before she can figure out how to hold herself accountable, so a huge part of me can’t help but root for everyone, even the seemingly hopeless… (i’ve been you.) to them, it’s just not worthwhile.
⠀⠀
even though we think differently on that, i see their point. because now i’m aware of how taxing it is on me to *always* act on my extensive understandings of human nature & sincere love of people. so how do i use those things in the interest of others, without putting their comfort & best interests above my own?... defining my boundaries, homie. the “lines” that mark my limits. Rosa knew hers.
⠀⠀
it’s great to be understanding… it’s destructive to be understanding to the point of self-compromise.
———————

firstComment:
monday meal preppin w lots of veggies & a super easy lemon garlic tanini sauce🍋
⠀
I'm not huge meal prepper, but i've found getting a few things squared away at the beginning of the week really helps make throwing together healthy melas a breeze: ⠀
⠀
🥦VEGGIES - i live for roasted veggies to throw into salads or bowls - not only to add fiber & micronutrients, but also as a low-carb way to add volume to meals (important for keeping you full!) this week I did roasted rainbow carrots & purple cauliflower (coated in avocado oil, s&p, roasted at 375 for ~30 minutes)
⠀
🍗PROTEINS - usually this "prep" for me is as easy as buying a pasture-raised rotisserie chicken from @belcampomeatco, or cooking up a batch of organic ground turkey ⠀
⠀
🥑FATS/ SAUCES - even though I really am I creature of habit when it comes to food, I still get bored from time to time, & sauces are a great way to mix it up. This week I made a super simple (but super good) tahini sauce that is great on roasted veggies, salads, or for dipping raw veggies in directly ⠀
⠀
DO IT👇🏼
combine 2 tbsp tahini, 2 tbsp high-quality extra virgin olive oil (I'm loving @caoliveranch which I get at @wholefoods), squeeze of 1/2 lemon, 1/8 tsp garlic powder, few dashes of pink salt & pepper👌🏼
⠀
what are your staples to get you through the week?

alt: Image may contain: food
firstComment:
easy weeknight dinner alert🚨stuffed delicata squash🙌🏼
⠀
if you haven't tried delicata squash, you really need to get on it
⠀
i've been loving them this fall bc: ⠀
👏🏼they're quick (only about 25 minutes to roast compared to 45+ for other squashes) ⠀
👏🏼they're low(er) carb (~1 cup serving contains ~8g net carbs)
👏🏼they're versatile (you can make sweet or savory versions - check out the sweet version in my fall salad on the blog) ⠀
👏🏼they're cheap ($.99 cents for a whole squash at @traderjoes) ⠀
👏🏼they're SO GOOD ⠀
⠀
👉🏼DO IT
↠slice delicata squash in half length-wise (if it's too hard to cut, place the whole squash in the oven on a broil a couple minutes to soften) ⠀
↠scoop out the seeds with a spoon & discard. coat the squash in avocado oil, and season with garlic powder, pink salt & pepper
↠roast in the oven on 400 degrees for about ~20-25 minutes (until squash is soft) ⠀ ⠀
↠while your squash is roasting - prep your filling. I did a mix of cherry tomatoes, shiitake mushrooms and kale - all sautéed in olive oil over medium heat with more pink salt, pepper, garlic, and my fav black truffle seasoning from @beruna_livingfoods - and some organic chicken sausage
⠀
add filing to your squash and dig in! another great thing about delicata squash is you can even eat the skin👌🏼
⠀
have you tried delicata squash? do you love it as much as i do?

Frack
.
I think the holidays are going to kinda suck again this year. 
I think I’m still in a halfway denial about her passing. Which means I’m still in the first stage of professing grief, or I just keep circling back to it.

The five stages, denial, anger, bargaining, depression and acceptance are a part of the framework that makes up our learning to live with the one we lost. They are tools to help us frame and identify what we may be feeling. But they are not stops on some linear timeline in grief. 
Today was hard. The trigger started when decorations went up this weekend. But HARD today because I’m not sleeping.
.
But, looking at the tree and the lights helps so much- I really do want to keep it up yearround. 💕
.
.
.
.
.

.
You guys this is how I got started. Before the ytt, before the spin motivating, before figuring out my nutrition, before I found my inner fire and confidence.
.
I started with a shake, a streaming app for my workouts, a few great mentors and a burning desire to CHANGE! To stop blaming everyone and everything around me for my situation and take charge. To finally FEEL GOOD in my mind and body. .
