alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'what if ever erything in your life was happening for yora instead af to YOU'
firstComment:
“Life is simple. Everything happens for you, not to you. Everything happens at exactly the right moment, neither too soon nor too late. You don’t have to like it...it’s just easier if you do” - Byron Katie
.
The phrase “everything happens for reason” can be divisive, but what if you focused your energy on looking at why things could be happening for you? What are they teaching you? What skills could you be building? Is this experience setting you up for success in another area of your life? Does something about your experience help others? Does it help you grow?
.
What if you tried shifting your perspective towards  understanding why whatever seemingly negative experience, event, or situation is troubling you right now, could be happening FOR you. The good, the bad, the grief and disappointments, the celebrations and the joys - what if they are *all* a part of your path to get you to where you are supposed to be? Would this make life easier? Even if it doesn’t take the pain away, does it provide some relief?
.
I’m curious about your thoughts on this! Let’s chat in the comments ☺️

firstComment:
breathe & let go💫easier said than done with the air quality in the bay area right now💔
⠀
aside from wearing a mask & staying indoors, infrared saunas can be a great way to help combat the stress the poor air quality is putting on our bodies right now
⠀
I checked out @rebootspa for my first ever infrared sauna sesh, and I loved it🙌🏼
⠀
Unlike traditional saunas that work by heating the air around you, infrared saunas use infrared light to heat the body directly. This not only leads to deeper health benefits, but allows you stay in the sauna much longer & more comfortably (I can only last in a traditional sauna about 5 minutes, but was fine in this 30 minute session) ⠀
⠀
Infrared saunas are great for:
👏🏼 reducing chronic pain & inflammation by increasing circulation & blood flood to the muscles
👏🏼 stimulating the parasympathetic nervous system (aka relaxation & stress-reduction)
👏🏼 improving the skin (!) by stimulating collagen production, improving skin elastin, and reducing signs of photoaging such as hyperprigmentation ⠀
⠀
Are you a fan of saunas? Have you tried infrared saunas?

alt: Image may contain: 1 person
firstComment:
New Year, New Me 😅
How many times have you said this to yourself?
“This year is going to be different.”
“I’m going to get healthy.”
“I’m going to get in shape.”
“I’m going to finally feel good in my own skin!”
🙋🏼‍♀️ I’ve probably said to myself this every year since I was 13 (never out loud of course because that would be too scary and real 🙄).
.
Did I ever follow through? No.
.
Why? Because I had no idea wtf I was doing. I didn’t know how to eat healthy but find balance. I didn’t know how to create a balanced workout that I enjoyed. I didn’t have anyone to hold me accountable to my goals.
.
My dears, nothing magical happens on Jan 1.  You won’t all of a sudden be given the gift of knowing how to lose weight, how to get fit and how to feel amazing in your body. It takes time and effort. You need to have a plan. You need to write down goals and remind yourself of them daily. You need to figure out what your “why” is and it has to be deep and strong (not just I want to look good)!
.
Jan 1 is just another day.
.
Why not make today your new year. Start now. No one ever regrets starting. They regret giving up, not following through, not having a plan, falling off the wagon.
.
Let me keep you accountable. Let me facilitate your transformation. I can guarantee, you won’t regret it!

Today’s Breakfast: 
Gary’s True Grit Einkorn Berries
.
I don’t usually sit to eat something at home, but I was up very early. I was very cold. And I wanted something that would hit the spot.
😋
I try to avoid gluten as much as I can, so this is a nice option because it’s a lower gluten level.
Young Living does sell more than essential oils 😆
And these Einkorn berries have a variety of uses. In the morning, I can eat it like an oatmeal. I’ve used it in dinner platters, replacing rice or quinoa. This can also be milled into a flour- but I haven’t gone that far yet!
I sweetened this with a little bit of local honey and it was perfect 👌
.
Some quick info on the 
Einkorn Berries-
*Unique genetic codes give einkorn a lower gluten content than modern wheat varieties
*Perfect for homes that support traditional farming practices
*Known as one of the oldest grain varieties
*No artificial colors or flavors
*No preservatives
*Non-GMO
*Contains 14 chromosomes, compared to modern wheat with 42 chromosomes
*Can be used in various recipes

I hope you had a hearty and healthy start to your day 🌞

firstComment:
The privilege of a lifetime is being who you are. -Joseph Campbell
———
I heard this quote this morning, and hit rewind -twice- to make sure it was sinking in.
Does the idea of this speak to you in some way?
🍁
For myself, I have never placed value on my own life and the idea that I am important or valuable or have a place in this world is somewhat of a new way of thinking for me.
.

It’s hard to break those old patterns. It takes work to undo the damage or the programming that was done over years, laying a solid foundation of garbage that I’ve been chiseling away bit by bit. .
But, I am doing the work. I have been listening to that inner voice and I am finally waking up.
.
For this new week, I am saying this is me. This is who I am.
.

alt: Photo by Rhonda Kesslering in Assiniboia, Saskatchewan.
firstComment:
Happy Hump Day!
.
A little mid week motivation for you today: Never compared your day 1 to someone else’s day 1000.
.
My journey started years ago. First with weight watchers and losing 20lbs. Then with beachbody and losing 15 ish of those lbs that I had gained back. And then becoming a coach, a spin motivator and a yoga teacher to help hold me to a new level of accountability.
.
Younger me hated exercise. It did not make me feel good. It felt heavy, hard and awkward. I mostly felt like puking after and I thought endorphin high was a myth. I had no idea wtf I was doing. I was so self conscious that I would never dream of setting foot on the weights side of the gym. I stuck firmly to the treadmill or the elliptical because they were easy and safe.
.
I loved pop, sour candy, chips, cheesecake, pie, McDonald’s. (Full disclosure: I still love all those things however I no longer pride myself on how much fair food I can eat and still go on rides w/o throwing up).
.
I changed my life one little step at a time. First I added in some yoga a one day per week. (Eventually I would come to realize yoga was a passion and I wanted to teach!)
.
Then it was trying out different nutrition plans until I found The One. Slowly adding in a veggie here instead of a potato there, a glass of water swapped out for a beer.
.
I was teaching yoga one day per week but I wanted to see more consistent results. So I committed to 80 days of at home workouts. 😳 Honestly I was scared shitless when I started @80dayobsession. But day by day, I got out of bed and did my workout early in the morning. It felt good to keep the promise I had made to myself. And it started to get easier as the weight started to come off and I became stronger.
.
Now I teach yoga, spin, and I coach. I could not be more committed or feel better in my body or mind!
.
Just know that it was a looooong, bumpy road full of road blocks and detours. My mindset shifts and muscles did not happen overnight. It took time. Time exercising, preparing healthy meals, working on my personal development.
.
So keep going, my loves. Don’t give up now! You are on the brink of something beautiful. If I had stopped (or not even started) I hate

alt: Photo by ╰☆☆ Just Judy ☆☆╮ on October 27, 2018.
firstComment:
🎧 Y’all. #Serial Season 3 is so good. So. Good.
.
They’ve taken a different direction this season. And it’s fascinating.
It’s not a sensationalized case. It’s not a single story over the course of the season. They are inside one courthouse in Ohio.
“Serial is heading back to court. This time, in Cleveland. A year inside a typical American courthouse. This season we tell you the extraordinary stories of ordinary cases. One courthouse, told week by week.”
.

If you think you know how it works inside a courtroom, based on television shows or what even the news will tell us about a story. You may be wrong.

There have been a few episodes that I had to rewind and play again, because I was flabbergasted.
Just understanding the traps that are built right into the system in Ohio...wow.
And how these traps target the low income citizens..... another wow. 
Flat out decisions by judges that are unconstitutional. 
Fascinating stuff, friends. *there are some incidents of NSFW language.

alt: Photo by Lupus Health Shop on October 24, 2018.
firstComment:
Most of us are so focused on stopping a flare-up, but what if we shift our focus to prevention instead?⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
There are different types of practices of medicine with different viewpoints. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣Conventional medicine - which is what we use now that is covered by insurance. This is based off of emergency based medicine. They manage symptoms only.
So, when your doctor sees a little bit of blood in your urine or a few kidney stones in a CT, they monitor and wait until your health has severly declined.
⠀⠀
2️⃣Integrative medicine - sees the same as above and starts to dig deeper by ordering an extensive blood panel and tests for things other doctors don't think of to find the cause. Then, they treat it and teach you ways to prevent flare-ups, chronic inflammation, & more. Plus, they still use conventional medicine, just not for every ailment.
🔹Integrative medicine can be practiced among a variety of doctors like MDs, DOs, NPs, & specialists⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔹Medicine, nutrition, stress reduction, supplementation, exercise combined in the right quantities for your illness and body’s needs will improve all of your organs, your entire body and put you into remission safely⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔹Treating lupus and other illnesses are based on the cause of illness or disease rather than symptoms⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔹They thoroughly learn about your life from childhood to current, lifestyle choices & request extensive bloodwork & tests⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔹Use the latest diagnostics and base blood test ranges on optimal ranges rather than “normal values”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🔹Appointments are often 60 minutes (due to above points)
🔹Treatment plans are personalized⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#lupuslifehacks - use our hashtag to share your fav hack on preventing a flareup!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

firstComment:
The past can hurt. But the way I see it, you can either run from it, or learn from it.
🙌
Rafiki has always been one of my favorite characters from “The Lion King” 👑🦁
.
I’ve wasted decades running from the past.  Running from the hurt. Hiding my scars. Living in shame.
It took several serious blows, and one incredible loss, for me to stop running.
.
I was in the best shape of my life, the thinnest I’d ever been. Had fought back and recovered from serious illnesses- and then it happened: mom got sick. Then. And suddenly, Mom passed away. 
I kept going. For almost 3 months, blindly pushing through the days drowning in grief and questions and anger and denial. 
And that’s when I lost my back. Herniated discs. Crushing my L3 nerve. Pain worse than kidney stones. Pain worse than childbirth. 
The Universe slammed me down. In my place. No more running. I had to sit in it, and deal with my -ish.

This is still a work in progress.

I am still a work in progress.

I’ve processed so much, worked on so much, gained too much weight... but I’m still showing up. Every day. I’m exercising again. Eating right again. I miss my mom but I no longer cry myself to sleep (as much)
💕
I’ve learned so much about myself and what I want out of life - I just wish she were still here to walk this journey with me ✨

In losing my mother, I’m finding myself. And 
I’m learning from the past.
No more running. 😘

alt: Image may contain: 2 people
firstComment:
3 days of clean eats, stretching, many hours of sleep, yoga and rest. I had gotten into a cycle of self sabotage where I would see a loss and then my will power would be non existent and I’d gain it back. I was snacking on too many silly treats (and it’s true that your body craves what you feed it), only eating veggies some (not veggies most!) and not tracking well at all!
.
I also needed some gentle movement and stretching. I had been pushing my body too hard in my workouts and it was having trouble recovering. This 3 day reset was so necessary! Plus I feel light, lean, and restored! I’m setting goals and looking at them with a new perspective and a new desire to CRUSH them!
.
Maybe you’re in the same boat as me. Or maybe you know that you’re going to need a reason to eat clean after Halloween. Perhaps you have a hot holiday planned and want to feel great in your bikini! Whatever the case may be, this Refresh can help you hit the reset button and make you feel great for any occasion. Even if that occasion is a Tuesday! Who else needs this in their life?! Let me know, I can give you all the details! #3DAYREFRESHRESULTS

Sundays are for meal prep 💪
Being consistent with our meals has been a game-changer for us. We thought we wouldn’t be able to do this, but once we got into the swing we were able to kick so many cravings and bad habits, save money, and just feel so much better all around.
.
The key is just to commit. Commit to being healthy. Commit to eating right. It is a rough go in the very beginning, but that passes pretty quickly. Drink tons of water, don’t get to the point of being hungry. And if you indulge once in a while- just get back on track. ASAP. No need to punish yourself or feel badly.
.
Just do it 👊
.
.
.

alt: Photo by mamagravy in Canmore, Alberta.
firstComment:
In a moment of reflection and gratitude this weekend, I smiled and chose to turn the counter off. I don’t need it. This month has been excellent for personal observation and learning. I have come to the realization that, for me, this can’t be about tracking the number of days. That is just another method  of control and ego.
I am working on letting go of expectations and holding myself responsible to each choice.  It’s scary. The imaginary critical critter in my head was having a hay-day but I closed my eyes, smiled and kicked him in the imaginary nuts.  The internal dialogue of failure and disappointment are simply not true. Reality is that sometimes, I’ll choose no booze.  It’s just not needed most of the time. I like that a nice cup of tea or a walk is just the thing I need when I’m tired, stressed or frustrated. Other times, I will choose to enjoy a glass of wine with a friend or a cold pint after a long walk w/ my hubby. These moments are just as welcomed by me and I’ll enjoy them fully without guilt or concern.  No tracker needed. My journey continues to lead me to be present and intentional in each moment of choice.  Funny enough, life is all about that. Taking a powerful pause to acknowledge the moment of choice and then doing just that. Choose.  Not for the tracker but for your best life. #wellnessjourney2018 #personalpower

alt: Photo by Marissa on October 05, 2018.
firstComment:
Met my husband for lunch and received a fortune that spoke to me ❤️ “Do not give up, the beginning is always the hardest”

Making the decision to embark on this journey, forced me to choose a different “hard”. My old “hard” thoughts were:
🔺Working out out is too hard.
🔺Having to cook healthy meals every night is too hard. 🔺Meal prepping is too hard. 🔺Balancing, work, being a mom, being a wife, being a friend, heck, just trying to keep my head above water in overall LIFE is too freaking hard! 
Well, honestly those things can still be challenging sometimes, but you know what else is hard? 🔻Being overweight is hard.
🔻Having no energy is hard.
🔻Feeling weak is hard. 🔻Constantly living in a mental fog is hard. 🔻Having my clothes feel too tight is hard. 🔻Feeling like I just want to give up is hard. 
Ultimately, I had to choose my hard. And guess what? As I progress along it gets easier and more like the “norm” to make more positive CHOICES in my life. Always a work in progress😊

I challenge you all to choose your “hard” in life. Don’t make the mistake of letting it choose you💕

If you’d like to join me on this journey of wellness, send me a message💌 I’d love to have you😃

#choices #chooseyourhard #wellnessjourney2018 #wellnessjourney

.
Drink more water! 💧 (Half your weight in lbs is how many oz you should drink per day MINIMUM!)

alt: Photo by Heather Prater on March 10, 2020.
firstComment:
I have become very passionate about replacing cleaning products and health & beauty items with non toxic alternatives in my home.  My latest discovery is hand soap.  I had no idea how inexpensive and easy it is to make my own.  And I appreciate the versatility, I can mix up the scent just by changing the oil that i add!

1 1/2c water
2T Castillo soap
1/2t almond oil
20ish drops essential oil - of course I recommend Young Living 😊 *I love citrus options in the kitchen because they are a natural grease cutter...lemon, orange, tangerine, citrus fresh 🍋 🍊 **I prefer Thieves in our downstairs bathroom which is our main hand washing spot because THIEVES :) I bought the ingredients and a few foaming had soap pumps from Amazon and put them into Mason jars we already had and Voila! ✨

firstComment:
I think the moment we make working out less about body image and more about how it makes us feel, we can truly enjoy it! 💙
.
I choose to work out because I’ve learned to love it— on the days when I feel like it and especially on the days when I don’t. Making wellness a priority even while traveling isn’t easy. In fact, it takes a lot of preparation. But because of how I feel at the end of it— that is what keeps me going! Caring more about my well being and less about my appearance has made working out a no-brainer and a LOT more fun!! 🌴 Embrace your body + then the pressure is off— it’s so easy to overcomplicate the simple things!
.
.
.

Penting bagi kamu untuk memperhatikan pola hidup dan pola makanmu untuk mendapatkan tubuh yang sehat. Nah salah satu cara menjaga kesehatan tubuh ialah dengan menjaga kesehatan hati kita. Ada banyak cara untuk menjaga kesehatan hati, salah satunya dengan menjaganya agar tetap bersih. 7 years ago I was just a 🇨🇴 girl 👩🏻 with a bag full of dreams coming to a new country with the love of my life. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I had no clue about what the future was holding for me.... ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Obviously, I never anticipated being part of this crazy worldwide crisis but despite all this, I can’t help but see all the amazing things/people around me and how far I have become in some aspects in my life.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
In 7 years:⁣⁣
1. Got my US Citizenship 💁🏻‍♀️⁣⁣
2. Had 2 precious girls!⁣⁣
3. I am healthier than ever⁣⁣
4. I have my own wellness business⁣⁣
5. We bought our 1st home⁣⁣
6. Ive met amazing people⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I can’t wait to see what this new year here will bring. I am sure after the storm comes the rainbow! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

alt: Photo by Irina Popa in Riverside South, Manhattan.
firstComment:
Wednesday with dr David Heber  @drdavidheber 
HOPE FOR CURE AND PREVENTION: For now, public health strategies are most important to reduce new cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19). This figure from the National Institutes of Health published in the Wall Street Journal shows what could be the best hope for treatment and prevention prior to developing a vaccine. Humans infected with COVID-19 make proteins called antibodies that bind to the virus about 8 weeks after recovering from an infection. These antibodies can be produced in large amounts from specially engineered cells in a laboratory. They are then infused into patients to see if they work as treatment. For treatment, large amounts are needed, but to prevent spread an injection monthly could provide protection for individuals at high risk like first responders and medical personnel. This treatment has worked for SARS, a closely related Corona Virus. There are many companies and academic labs  working on this now and hoping to have something by August. Be thankful that we have the finest medical research in the world, and remember this crisis the next time that you hear that funding for the National Institutes of Health is threatened. Medical research matters as does all of scientific research and our public health infrastructure worldwide. We are now citizens in a global fishbowl. While we wait for these new weapons against the virus, stay healthy with Balanced Nutrition. Exercise and Sleep to support your Immune System!! #drdavidhber #COVID-19 #Immunity #Nutrition #PublicHealth #Research #drdavidheber to learn more go to www.drdavidheber.com and www.uclahealth.org #coachirina #wellnesscoach #wellnessjourney2020 #wendsdaywithdrheber

BioHacking your immune system
💫Part 2 💫
(If you did not see yesterday’s post read 1st) 🤩 Cinnamon: Known for its benefits in helping to support blood sugar levels it has also antibacterial, anti-fungal and antiviral properties and it protects cells and nerves. 😋 Elderberry Syrup: great antibacterial and antiviral activities 🤪 Vitamin D3: important for your immune system to function optimal. Individuals with lower vitamin D levels (<30 ng/ml) were more likely to suffer from upper respiratory tract infection 😎 Olive Leaf Extract: protects your digestive system, 70-80% of your immune system is located in your digestive system, inhibits microorganisms from growing 🐝 Propolis: antifungal and antibacterial properties 🤗 Vitamin C: supports immune system to fight pathogens, protects organs and blood vessels from pathogens and free radicals, protects skin via collagen synthesis which is very important considering we are now constantly washing and disinfecting our hands 😝 Vitamin E (in nuts and seeds): protects against free radicals, especially in combination with Vitamin C as it helps regenerate used glutathione, your body’s major antioxidant (the one activated by NRF2) 🐝 Manuka Honey: antibacterial and anti-microbial 😊 Throat Coat: great mixture of antiviral and antibacterial herbs and it tastes seriously delish 😉 😳 Garlic: add to any dish for an extra bit of antibacterial and antiviral benefits. Garlic is also great food for the good bacteria in your gut 🤓 Lemon and Ginger: I think we all know how good these two are for our immune system 😀 Selenium, Zinc and Vitamin E containing cashews, brazil nuts, sesame seeds, pumpkin seeds, quinoa and lentils: they are very important co-factors for the immune system, make sure you have plenty of them in your diet 🌿 Thyme, Sage, Rosemary, Clove and Elderberry tea: a serious boost for your immune system and particularly for your respiratory tract 🔥 Chilli and Turmeric: add them to a smoothie, tea or any dish you like for warming extra antioxidants to support your immune system

SOCIAL DISTANCE YOURSELF sis⁣
⁣
You might think this list is someone odd, but it’s me haha personally I love lists and this is something I’ve thrown together to keep myself accountable during this time where it might be more difficult to do so! I hope this inspires you to either make yourself a list of things to get done in the time we have with ourself or gives you something to do today or tomorrow. ⁣
⁣
COMMENT below how you are practicing social distancing. How you are couping.. choirs your have to do. What’s up🍓⁣
⁣
Any Disney plus suggestions also.. I’m obsessed 😅⁣
⁣
With spring coming these are tasks I normally do as the warmer weather rolls in anyway so I’m not too bothered! Now I have more time on my hands. Time I used to make this list to help me stay on track. ⁣
⁣
Yes it can be frustrating not being able to spend time with friends and connect in public places rn but it is a time we can take to ourselves to gather what’s most important. And focus on specific habits or areas of our lives we want to improve. For myself I’ve been taking my dog for a walk, getting fresh air is so nice and makes you forget that you can’t go out, trust me it’s so nice! ⁣
⁣
Amongst this panic, we learns what is really essential to us and what we can live without for a little while. We spend more time with family and in the KITCHEN👌🏼 now that we are not rushing from place to place and are spending more time at home if your bored cook something. Instead of rushing and throwing in a microwave dinner, cook your favourite meal. Nourish your body so that you can stay HEALTHY!⁣
⁣
I hope your all doing well and if you want to chat, your bored, anything message me! We can distract each other from what’s going on around us🙈🤍 I feel like I could go on forever about this and how we need to keep busy with the important things. ⁣
⁣
I am also doing my best to stay on tract with my fitness goals from earlier in the year, aside from the going to the gym part of coarse. ⁣
⁣
Jenn⁣
Xx⁣

Even in such moments of self-isolation from the public places.

We can take advantages of current situation: use this time for good  to slow down OR choose to be miserable and be negative. 
What would you choose friend?

As for me I am going to take 100% advantage of it.

There are so many good things we can do that we wanted to do for a long time but had no time.

Here are the things we can do and make the most of it: . .

alt: Photo by Madalina Coman in Orangetheory Fitness San Jose - Downtown with @orangetheorydtsj.
firstComment:
Not a bad workout today! I am grateful my favorite orangetheoryfitness studio @orangetheorydtsj is still open and that they are taking so many measures to make sure all of us are safe. Today, in order to practice social distancing they allowed half of the regular class side to work out. We were able to work out on machines that were not fully occupied: they alternated so we could always have one empty machine between people. I am planning on continuing to work out with them for as long as it is safe. My family and I are not going out of the house for anything else but last minute shopping trips and we try to leave the house just one person as opposed to the entire family. We take walks around the neighborhood in the evening and the kids use our backyard playground during the day when it is not raining. We are doing our best to be mindful about practicing social distancing as much as possible. I have also cut down my shifts at the National Suicide Line from 4, this coming week I will be doing 2 and my shifts will be evening shifts so that I do not get to interact with any crowds coming into the hospital. 
Stay safe out there, but don’t forget how important it is to get some sort of workout in and not fall into the trap of becoming a couch potato! Sending you all love 😘

firstComment:
Are you getting enough sleep?
.
Sleep stats recommended that an adult aged 26-64y gets about 7-9 hours sleep each night. 🤔*sleepadvisor.org

Nursing an injury, last night I slept for 14 hours. My body went into shut down repair mode. It’s interesting considering I generally sleep so well.
.
So are you getting enough sleep? What are some of your evening tricks to share with those who are not able to drift off so easily?...
.

Here are a few of mine: 
1. If already over stimulated, turn of the iPad, tv or iPhone and read or do a sudoku 
2. Listen to some 528hz sound therapy while you soften the mind and drift off (you will find these on YouTube which contradicts #1 but you don’t watch it, just listen)

3. Listen to a Yoga Nidra guided meditation (also available on YouTube or Spotify or easy to download on itunes) .
So what’s your go to move for sleep? .

Please write in the comments below so we can allow others to try alternatives to see what works for them....🙏🏻 📸 by me. Magnetic Island

alt: Photo by Faith A/M/Y on March 14, 2020.
firstComment:
This list has been one of my go-to anxiety busters and sanity savers for a few decades now.
✏️
In the left column, write everything that’s IN your control, and in the right column write everything that’s OUT of your control.
✏️
Then, acknowledge how much is NOT controllable by you and try to release the weight of it. If it’s out of your control, what good is stressing over something you can’t influence?
✏️
Therein lies the beauty of the list that IS within your control. Anxiety comes from not being in the moment, and for anyone with control issues, fixating on things you can’t influence is another great way to feed the fearful beast.
✏️
If you can seek to only control the controllables, and release everything else, your sense of peace, self confidence and security will start to increase — especially when combined with other self care practices. Onward and upward!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#anxiety #anxietyrelief #anxietyattack #anxietysupport  #control #controlfreak #controlyourmind #controlthecontrollables #wellness #wellnessjourney #wellnessjourney2020 #wellnesscoach

Did you know that Cryotherapy helps boost your Immune System?
.
.
No?  Well here’s why ⬇️⬇️⬇️
.
White blood cells are the cells that help us fight infection and disease, that’s why we call them our Soldier Cells.  Cryotherapy has been shown to increase the amount of these soldier cells, while also elevating anti-inflammatory Cytokines which help reduce systemic inflammation as well as keep more from building up.  This plays a huge role in why cryo helps with athletic recovery, but also why people with inflammatory conditions such as Rheumatoid arthritis, Osteoarthritis, Crohn’s Disease, MS, Fibromyalgia, and many others see such relief and benefit from regular cryotherapy use.  The Cytokines help heal damaged cells while the white blood cells fight infection.
.
.
Now if that doesn’t make you want to include Cryotherapy in your wellness journey, we don’t know what will 😉

Where are my emotional friends at? 😭⁣
⁣
Today has been rough. I literally had to Google if being emotional is a weakness because I definitely FEEL it is. Dang it. 😔⁣
⁣
This is what I found: “While it’s a healthy social skill to be able to behave professionally even when you’re not feeling at the top of your game, letting your guard down at socially appropriate times isn’t a sign of weakness. In fact, being aware of your emotions and making a conscious decision to share those emotions with others – when it’s socially appropriate to do so- can be a sign of strength” - Forbes⁣
⁣
Sometimes I wish I could stand up for myself when someone treats me bad and tell people the things I want without breaking down. But I care too much. 😔⁣
⁣
Tell me... Do you consider yourself an emotional person? What do you do to dont let your emotions show in front of those who don’t deserve it.?⁣
⁣

firstComment:
6 things I learned from my fitness and health journey 💪🏽🌿
-
1️⃣ It’s not just about the physical progress and appearance. Being consistent and disciplined will strengthen patience and self control.
2️⃣ Most suppléments aren’t necessary. Fat burners, BCAAs, créatine, etc. You can gain muscle, and burn fat without any of these things.
3️⃣ There isn’t a one size fits all sort of training plan or diet. We all have individual needs and your plans should align with your lifestyle and requirements.
4️⃣ Consistent work will create consistent results. One bad meal won’t make you gain a bunch of weight and one good meal won’t make you shed a bunch of weight. Be consistent to see results.
5️⃣ Find a type of exercise that you enjoy. You like yoga? Go for it. Runs? Do it. Walks outside? Yes! Anything to include some sort of movement every day.
6️⃣ Dont rely solely on the scale for progress. A lot of progress can be seen by your energy levels, eating habits changes, sleeping schedule & quality, confidence & how you view yourself, and your mood.
-

alt: Photo by Reboot Reflexology on March 10, 2020.
firstComment:
TUESDAY TIP #2

Today’s Tuesday Tip is all about helping relieve headaches and migraines... In our busy world, headaches are really common ranging from tension headaches right through to debilitating migraines...when you feel one coming on try these steps to start a natural healing process in your body...just scroll through the photos and follow the steps below... Step One
Apply pressure and massage the top of each finger including the nail. Then moving in small circles apply pressure up and down your entire thumb front and back. Repeat this for as long as comfortable on each hand. These are our head, brain and sinus reflexes.

Step Two
We massage the spinal reflex to relax the nerves in the neck and down the spine. The spinal reflex runs down the outside of your hand from the base of the nail on the thumb all the way down to the wrist. Massage all the way down (as shown on the photo) using your thumb to apply pressure, do this on both hands several times.

Step Three
A wonderful reflex to finish with is the Adrenal reflex point. Your adrenal glands are very important for natural pain relief and help with inflammation in the body. Find your adrenal reflex point (as show in the photo) and apply pressure with your thumb and massage in small circles for a few minutes at least three times. 
Finish up with a glass of water to rehydrate and help flush any toxins away.

WELL DONE! You have now completed a simple hand reflexology routine to provide natural pain relief whenever you have a headache or migraine coming on.

As always any questions just ask... Keep watching for Tuesday’s Tip #3...more  reflex points to help with stress and anxiety. ♥️love, health and happiness to you all ♥️#reflexologymassage #reflexology #handmassage #handreflexology #healing #naturalremedy #headacherelief #wellbeing #naturalhealthrevolution #loveyourself #loveothers #benefitsofreflexology #timeforyourself#switchoffandreboot#helpeachother #wellnessjourney2020 #nurtureourminds #nurtureourbodies #healthylifestyle #hurstpierpoint #hassocks #haywardsheath #burgesshill #sayerscommon #lindfield #cuckfield #henfield

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, people sitting, living room, shoes and indoor
firstComment:
Here's a statement that punched me right in the face this morning.⁠
⁠
Our excuses are misalignments!⁠
⁠
For so long I'd make excuses for being overweight.⁠
For so long I'd make excuses why I could not stop eating sugar.⁠
For so long I'd make excuses why I had to have that coffee first thing in the morning.⁠
For so long I'd make excuses why I couldn't stick to regular exercise.⁠
⁠
"I was born this way."⁠
"I have no willpower."⁠
"I need coffee to be alert."⁠
"I don't have the motivation."⁠
⁠
Sounds familiar, right?⁠
⁠
We all tell stories for ourselves about why we can't do the things we want to.⁠
We literally talk ourselves out of the life we want to live.⁠
How crazy is that?⁠
⁠
But here's the thing.⁠
As soon as I stopped using my excuses as road blocks, I found that actually I can be healthy weight, I can quit sugar, I don't need coffee first thing, I can exercise regularly.⁠
And I know, if you're sitting here reading this with these same excuses running through your mind, you can realign them too.⁠
⁠
And that is what my next group "March into Wellness" will be about.⁠
⁠
Together we will pick a workout+nutrition plan aligned with your goals and needs.⁠
You will receive daily support+accountability from me AND from my community of like-minded ladies on a similar journey.⁠
PLUS daily motivation and tips on fitness, nutrition and mindset.⁠
⁠
If that sounds like something YOU need, I would be honoured to help you realign your wellness.⁠
⁠
Grab my hand and let's do this!⁠
Let's march into wellness together.

STEP BY STEP [PL ↓]
•
We don’t know each other but for sure we have a lot in common.🙂
•
▫️We want to accept and LOVE ourselves just the way we are.
▫️We want to DECLUTTER OUR MINDS when we have too many negative thoughts.
▫️We want to understand our EMOTIONS better and learn how to deal with them.
▫️We want to know how to TAKE CARE OF ourselves properly.
▫️We want to build our SELF-ESTEEM and SELF-CONFIDENCE.
▫️We want our BOUNDARIES to be respected by others.
▫️We want to develop and FEEL FULFILLED in our relationships, at work, in the everyday life.
•
We have different personalities, interests, needs...
but still we share the same aim – we just want to be HAPPY.☺️
•
@balance.is.art was created to show you how taking SMALL STEPS every day we can bring WELLBEING, PEACE and JOY into our lives.👣🌱✨
•
•
•
•
• 📖DICTIONARY:
• have a lot in common - mieć dużo wspólnego
• declutter - uporządkować
• deal with - radzić sobie z
• self-esteem - poczucie własnej wartości
• self-confidence - pewność siebie
• boundaries - granice
• feel fulfilled - czuć się spełnionym
• aim - cel
• wellbeing - dobre samopoczucie
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
KROK PO KROKU
•
Chociaż jeszcze się nie znamy wiem że mamy wiele wspólnego.🙂
•
▫️Chcemy akceptować i kochać siebie takie jakie jesteśmy.
▫️Chcemy uporządkować nasze umysły gdy mamy zbyt wiele negatywnych myśli.
▫️Chcemy lepiej zrozumieć nasze emocje i nauczyć się jak sobie z nimi radzić.
▫️Chcemy wiedzieć jak właściwie zatroszczyć się o siebie.
▫️Chcemy budować nasze poczucie wartości i pewność siebie.
▫️Chcemy by nasze granice były szanowane przez innych.
▫️Chcemy rozwijać się i czuć się spełnione w związku, w pracy, w życiu.
•
Mamy różne osobowości, zainteresowania, potrzeby… ale mamy ten sam cel – po prostu chcemy być szczęśliwe.☺️
•

“I knew better.” “Why did I?” “I always do this.” ⠀
⠀
STOP SHAMING YOURSELF. This self criticism is the best way to continue on a negative path, and the worst way to to grow and accomplish your goals with joy. ⠀
⠀
Staying on course and maintaining momentum requires forethought and a solid plan of action. You’ve heard me say it before #failtoplanplantofail. ⠀

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, drink
firstComment:
ok oily friends... play along⁣
⁣
... guess the oil⁣
⁣
i’ll give you a hint... it’s blue in colour and is one of my faves! (like most YL fans 😻)⁣
⁣
guess right & I’ll randomly pick someone to receive a little surprise in the post! 🤩⁣
⁣
but for real, this is me in heaven right here. oils are so much more than you smelling pretty or having your house smell amazing. ⁣
⁣
let me throw some science at you for a bit ...⁣
⁣
inhaling essential oils stimulates the olfactory system, the part of the brain connected to smell and of course the entire respiratory system - as the molecules travel into the lungs and transport throughout the body. ⁣
⁣
as the molecules reach the brain, they also impact the limbic system - the emotional control centre of the brain - which is also responsible for your ⁣
🔆 heart rate⁣
🔅 blood pressure⁣
🔆 breathing⁣
🔅 memory⁣
🔆 stress ⁣
🔅 hormone balance ⁣
⁣
this relationship helps explain why smells often trigger emotions and memories. so yes! inhaling essential oils can have some very profound physiological and psychological effects!⁣
⁣
so for the sceptics out there - see for yourself. try an oil. you might just never look back. I know I haven’t. ⁣
⁣
and for the science minded - explore the huge amount of research done on how essential oils benefit the body. it’s out there and available to find. ⁣
⁣
and when you decide it’s time to give these magic little bottles a go give me a hola 🙋🏼‍♀️⁣
I’d love to be your oily guide and show the ropes! 💚☺️⁣
⁣
*** side note - if you’ve tried oils before and they haven’t worked, you may have just tried a poor quality oil. quality matters!

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, eyeglasses and closeup
firstComment:
🌟Don’t use self care as an excuse for lack of discipline🌟⁣
⁣
Now, you all know that I am a huge fan of self care. In fact I took a break from work today to go and get a massage with my sister.⁣
⁣
However, lately I’ve been finding that I’ve been using “self care” as an excuse to not have discipline.⁣
⁣
My alarm goes off in the morning and I don’t feel like going to the gym?⁣
“Oh well,” I’ve been saying “I need the sleep anyway... self care”⁣
⁣
Self care would actually be to hold myself accountable and get up and go to the gym.⁣
Having discipline IS a form of self care.⁣
⁣
Having TOO much discipline and never giving yourself a break can be self-destructive for sure.⁣
⁣
But check yourself and make sure that when you don’t do something you had planned or don’t follow through with things out of self care, it really is to avoid burnout rather than just an excuse to be lazy.

alt: Image may contain: 1 person
firstComment:
Who’s has been to a Salt cave? 
This weekend my husband and I took a mini a getaway to #sojospaclub It was amazing and gave me some time for needed rest, reflection and more importantly recalibration. 
The law of averages predicts that if you strive to be better, you will at some point fail, or at least miss your target. (And it’s a law so who am I to judge

The point is this, those people you see who seemingly have it all together or have what you strive to achieve? They have failed. They have. All of them, at some point fell flat on their face. You just see the highlight reel. You don’t see the down and dirty moments of defeat 
It’s okay to begin again. Try again. Those mistakes you made along the way were lessons, not failures. You were meant to get back up. There is no expiration date to reinventing yourself 
This time you aren’t starting from the beginning, you are starting from experience 🤜🤛 #bigthingscoming

So many times I used to find myself struggling with doing it all....
Getting all of the things crossed off all of the lists all of the time...
.
Lately, while I still want to get it all done, I’ve told myself to step back and look at around. 
Your littles are happy and healthy and want their mommy to be present. Sure, you can be around them all the time but that doesn’t mean you are “there”. You are blessed with a husband who loves and supports you, family and friends that are amazing. Don’t get caught up in the to do lists...look around at your blessings and cherish them! .
Trust me.....The things can wait...
Enjoy the little moments 🧡

📷 #repost @the.wellness.wheel

SPIRITUAL WELLNESS....WHAT IS YOUR MEANING AND PURPOSE? ⠀
⠀
I’m sure many of you would agree this question can be a tough one. Many people spend a life time trying to work it out or find ourselves contemplating during major times in our lives. 
The first thing that comes to mind for many when mentioning Spiritual Wellness is religion, however, it’s only one component of spiritual wellness. ⠀
⠀
More so, it relates to your values and beliefs that help you to find meaning and purpose in your life. ⠀
⠀
Having strong spiritual wellness is said to come from having clear values, having a sense of self confidence and direction as well as a feeling of inner peace. ⠀
⠀
WHY IS SPIRITUAL WELLNESS GOOD FOR YOU?⠀
⠀
Because it has the power to help making decisions and choices easier.  It keeps us staying in our own lane being our authentic selves, it keeps us grounded during times of change and hardship, helps build our resilience and to find inner peace and healing.
⠀
PRACTICING SPIRITUAL WELLNESS⠀
⠀
This is a personal approach so it’s good idea to find one or some that work for you. Late last I started gratitude journaling and quick meditation and it’s been wonderful for my mindset. ⠀
⠀
Here are some ways that you might find helpful⠀
⠀
• Meditation or yoga⠀
• Spending quiet time contemplating life and how you want to show up in your life⠀
• Journaling your thoughts or what your are grateful for ⠀
• Serving your community volunteering, making and impact helping others, appreciating music, the arts or spending time in nature⠀
• Self care⠀
⠀
Have an amazing day! X⠀

{The 3 Lessons About Weight Loss You Need To Know To Be Successful} ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣If you're like me {want to lose 10lbs & have tried EVERYTHING to achieve it}, you probably already know you can get a gym membership and STILL not get to your goal.⁣
⁣
I struggled for years with unsuccessful attempts at various gyms {childcare, class times, ACTUALLY going} and finally DISCOVERED the solution was actually REALLY simple.⁣
⁣
Working out at home made me the MOST consistent for these 3 reasons...⁣
⁣
✌🏽Childcare Is Built In⁣
When I changed my routine and was able to workout from home, I no longer needed childcare so it meant MORE workouts MORE often #winning⁣
⁣
✌🏽Variety Is The Spice Of Life⁣
I would often get bored at the gym and end up not going as consistently as I planned. With my new program, I have 100’s of options to choose from and I NEVER get bored. Yoga or HIIT training? I can decide 30 seconds before my workout! #gamechanger⁣
⁣
✌🏽Now Or Later?⁣
Rather than feeling like the gym is a "now or never" time of the day, I can do my workout before the kids get up or after they go to bed or when they go to school. I can CHOOSE whatever works best for me THAT day with no SWEAT! #flexibilityrules⁣
⁣
So if your intuition is going off {**you've been WAITING for a program that doesn't have you signing up for a gym membership you won't use}, drop an emoji and let's chat. ⁣

alt: Photo by Dietetian Meenu in Singapore. Image may contain: possible text that says 'Liver Subcutaneous fat Kidney Stomach Gall bladder Abdominal cavity Colon Viseral fat mall intestine'
firstComment:
Why pot bellies are dangerous 
The fat impact on our body

Most of us think that fat is relatively harmless and that we need to get rid of it to look good and feel better. Certain fats that are stored around our organs can impact our heart and also cause dementia, cancer, mood issues, sexual dysfunction, arthritis and other diseases. 
Stored excess fat is downright dangerous. 
Visceral fat is one of them. It’s a deep fat that’s stored further underneath the skin than the belly fat. It’s a fat that is actually wrapped around major organs, including the liver, pancreas and kidneys. 
If you have large protruding belly and large waist then it’s a clear sign that we are storing dangerous visceral fat.

When there is too much glucose in our bloodstreams and our glycogen stores are full, glucose is stored as fat. This happens more faster when we consume more processed carbohydrates and sugary foods. 
Visceral fat reduction needs a conscious effort to eat healthy, exercise and be disciplined. 
Meenu Agarwal works with clients with customized programs targeted at reducing body fat.  # #nutritioncoach #fat #eatinghabits #nutritional #wellnessjourney2019🧘🏾‍♀️

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

S’y retrouver dans la jungle des conseils anti-burn-out.
En fait, il n’y en a qu’1: « Se faire confiance ».
.
Quand ça semble trop: c’est que c’est trop.
Quand ça semble sans queue ni tête , c’est que c’est probablement insensé.
Quand c’est inacceptable, c’est juste inacceptable!.
.
Pourtant la plupart de nous s’acharne, s’agrippe, tient encore un peu plus.
On résiste au lieu de se faire confiance et on accepte le trop, le non sens et l’inacceptable jusqu’à disjoncter.
.
Comment trouvez vous votre situation aujourd’hui? Vous la connaissez mieux que quiconque, et vous seule pouvez la juger.
.
✨Écoutez vous, au fond, vous savez déjà ce qu’il faut changer pour éviter la chute.
.
.
.

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

This exercise takes less than five minutes and helps you to unstick from negative thinking!⁣
⁣
No matter who you are, periodically we all struggle with negative thoughts, worries, fears, and second-guessing ourselves. And thoughts occur at such a rapid frequency throughout the day that they can lead us to feeling overwhelmed, Especially if we find ourselves tethered to a particular thought, analyzing it over and over and thinking about what it might mean for our identity in our lives.⁣
⁣
The brief mindfulness exercise that I will take you through in this video is going to help you to release stress, feel better, and reduce the impact that negative thoughts can have on you. In just under five minutes, you can learn an evidence-based techniques to manage your thoughts and to recognize them as they are, just mental events and nothing more. This technique teaches you that you do not need to act on a troublesome thought, and you can continue to do the things that are most important to you that day and be at peace.⁣
⁣
Come along with me for day 11 of the wellness challenge and try this out! No supplies needed, just an open mind and willing heart. Let me know what you think in the comments below.⁣

This was just a couple weeks post partum.
I was so happy and proud of my journey. 
Pregnancy was easy. 
I already fit into my regular clothes.
How hard could this be? 
I ate my words.
Post partum does not discriminate.  It affects every woman in different ways.
Some women deal with depression.  I did not.
Some women deal with physical pain and leaking.  I did. 
It didn’t seem like much of a big deal at the time.  I think I just plowed through it.  I was good at that.
But I think I forgot to really stop, listen to my body and FEEL what I was expereincing. 
I am strong.  And I think I believed everyone expected me to be strong, so I did.  And I did it well.
But sometimes we don’t have to be strong.  It’s ok.

I’ve learned to savor the moment.  Feel my pain.  Listen to what I need, what my body needs.  It sounded hard at first.  But once I develped a system, it became who I am, and it’s not hard anymore.

Are you tired of running and hiding?  Are you tired of HAVING to be strong all the time?  Are you tired of health being hard?  It doesn’t have to be.  My online program with @bejourneystrong is designed to take the HARD out of Hardwiring your Health….FOR GOOD.

When we’re working towards creating something extraordinary with our lives, we need to make good use of our high-energy moments whenever we have them. For some people this is easy — they have naturally high levels of energy the majority of the time. Unfortunately, that’s not the case for everyone.

Just as we all have different levels of energy to work with, we all have unique energy patterns too. There are a number of things that can affect these levels and patterns, including our hormones, sleep, nutrition, and activity levels.

Since most of those factors can be adjusted by our behaviors, it’s possible for us to tweak our habits so that our energy levels and patterns are positively affected. It doesn’t mean overhauling your whole life, though. Often, simply observing your energy patterns will be enough to help you manage your highs and lows throughout the work day.

alt: Image may contain: 2 people
firstComment:
These are the 3 half marathons I ran pregnant with my first baby. 
When I found out I was pregnant, I had already registered for the races. The first OBGYN I saw told me I was done running as of that day. 🤔

I quickly changed doctors to one who was going to safely support me through my goals. I was ready to quit running if needed. 
Why did I keep running?  Honestly it felt better than walking. Walking 🚶‍♀️ hurt, running 🏃‍♀️ didn’t 🤷🏻‍♀️ Every body is different. At every stage. 
I got a lot of “you are amazing.” I got a lot of “why would you do that to yourself and your baby.” Neither is right or wrong. It’s just where I was. 
We can all be successful in our movement through each transition. It’s just going to look different. 
I was slow. I trotted and rested. I listened to my body. That is the key to success in health, and life: meet your body, meet yourself where you are each and every day with grace. 🔥

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'What is balance?'
firstComment:
Everyone talks about achieving balance. But what is it? Can it be achieved?

Yesterday I talked to my FB community about how balance is more than standing on one leg. True balance is about being able to move and navigate through the world without falling over. Step on unpredictable surfaces, reach out of your comfort zone, catch yourself if you do find yourself falling. 
Isn’t that life balance?  Moving through the changes of life, sustaining through unpredictability, transitions and even chaos?

It’s not about staying still. Balance is about movement with strength and control ✔️ What is balance to you? Is it static or dynamic?

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, standing
firstComment:
𝓦𝓱𝓪𝓽’𝓼 𝓾𝓹 𝓰𝓵𝓸𝔀 𝓾𝓹? ✨

I remember looking at myself in the mirror about six months after my son was born and feeling so torn. I was so grateful and my spirit was so full of joy with my son and my new title as a mom. I was so amazed at what my body had been able to do and create. 
But my body was also unrecognizable to me. I was the heaviest I had ever been aside from pregnancy. My clothes didn’t fit well. I was so self conscious and fatigued all the time.

I was convinced that this was just...ya know motherhood. I began settling for fatigue, pain, shame.

Then I became consumed with the thought of getting my “old body back.” What if...just what IF I could look like that again? That super fit high school/early college version of my body (swipe left). I could have that back right? Then I would feel worthy again, beautiful again, right? Nice try. ✨

𝓓𝓪𝓻𝓵𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓭𝓲𝓭𝓷’𝓽 𝔂𝓸𝓾 𝓴𝓷𝓸𝔀? 𝓨𝓸𝓾 𝓪𝓻𝓮 𝓼𝓸 𝓶𝓾𝓬𝓱 𝓶𝓸𝓻𝓮 𝓲𝓷𝓽𝓮𝓻𝓮𝓼𝓽𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓽𝓱𝓪𝓷 𝔂𝓸𝓾𝓻 𝓯𝓵𝓮𝓮𝓽𝓲𝓷𝓰 𝓹𝓱𝔂𝓼𝓲𝓬𝓪𝓵 𝓫𝓮𝓪𝓾𝓽𝔂. ✨

Why would I want to go back? Why would I seek something which “once was” when right in front of me I had a reason to fight for a body AND soul that were holistically well. Why would I want to go back when it was THIS body that created life? THIS body and mind that now had gained inner strength and wisdom. I didn’t need to fight for what “once was.” I needed to fight for every present moment, to live purposefully, to honor my breath and choose wellness. Because my best is yet to come and no day is promised.

So bring on that mama glow. That heart full of wisdom, that fiery soul. Chains are broken. Life is beautiful. And I’m here 🙌🏻 for 🙌🏻 it🙌🏻.
If you could have health,look and feel good in your body, happiness and success without more pain, hustle and exhaustion, would you take it?

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'YOUR BELIEF ABOUT YOUR BODY LEADS το HOW YOU TREAT YOUR BODY'
firstComment:
We are what we believe we are:  C.S. Lewis
What you believe to be true about your body, your abilities, your health dictates your ability to actually achieve any health and physical goals you want. 
What I have frequently seen as a Physical Therapist is that everyone want to BE healthy, pain free, someone who loves their body, happy….But most people don’t actually believe it is possible.

You may not outright say “I’m not good enough/worthy,” but have you ever caught yourself saying, “I could never…, I’m just not….I’m not like those people…,it is not possible to…”?
Those thoughts have haunted each and every one of us at some point.  Those thoughts repeated become a belief. And that belief dictates what action you will take.  And your brain doesn’t know the difference if it is truth or not!‼️ 💥The Good News?! You can change these thoughts!  You don’t have to stay stuck!
Recognize next time you catch yourself in these negative thoughts, write them down and refute them!  Then replace them with a new story!  For strategies like this and more to Hardwire Your Healthy Habits to finally believe and make the results happen, join the Healthy Habit Challenge that starts this upcoming Monday!

Like everyone else I ate the Standard American Diet (S.A.D) of foods high in sugar, gluten, dairy, and soda. All which were fueling inflammation and creating disturbances in my metabolic pathways. ⁠
As a holistic health coach, using an evidence-based approach holds promise for reversing autoimmune conditions. ⁠
⁠
If we can change our environment and our behavior, we can change the way our genes perform. A central piece of the “environment” is a person’s chosen lifestyle. An increasing amount of research shows the therapeutic effects lifestyle changes have in treating many chronic diseases. ⁠
⁠
That’s why I believe lifestyle changes should be prioritized not only for their lower cost, but because of their long term role in restoring health and preventing disease. ⁠

alt: Image may contain: text
firstComment:
Protect your mental health and well-being.⁠
⁠
When you create boundaries and can preserve them with assertion, this gives you confidence you need to just say NO and move on. ⁠
⁠
𝐈𝐭'𝐬 𝐧𝐨𝐭 𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟𝐢𝐬𝐡, 𝐢𝐭'𝐬 𝐣𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐬𝐞𝐥𝐟-𝐜𝐚𝐫𝐞! ⁠
⁠
Here are my TOP 5 ways on just how to do that!⁠
⁠
1. Name your limits.⁠
⁠
You can’t set good boundaries if you’re unsure of where you stand. So identify your limits (physical, emotional, mental and spiritual).⁠
⁠
2. Be direct.⁠
⁠
There will be times you might need to be direct. For instance, in a romantic relationship, might need to talk about how much time they need to maintain their sense of self and how much time to spend together.⁠
⁠
3. Make self-care a priority.⁠
⁠
Your feelings serve as important cues about your wellbeing and about what makes you happy and unhappy. Self-care also means recognizing the importance of your feelings and honoring them. ⁠
⁠
4. Seek support.⁠
⁠
If you’re having a hard time with boundaries, seek some support (maybe an assertive friend 😉) and make it a priority with each other to practice setting boundaries together and hold each other accountable.⁠
⁠
5. Be assertive.⁠
⁠
No one can read your mind and therefore people don't always know what hurts you. So, it’s important to assertively communicate with them when they’ve crossed a boundary.⁠
⁠
In a respectful way, let the other person know what in particular is bothersome to you and that you can work together to address it.⁠
⁠
⁠
𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗯𝗲𝗹𝗼𝘄 𝘁𝗼 𝘁𝗲𝗹𝗹 𝗺𝗲 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗯𝗼𝘂𝗻𝗱𝗮𝗿𝗶𝗲𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗱 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗻𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗼 𝘀𝗲𝘁 𝗼𝗿 𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗲⁠

firstComment:
Do you believe Health is a Choice?

It’s easy to look at someone who is overweight or severly limited physically and say they made a choice to be like that. ⁉️But really, does anyone wake up and say “I choose to be too heavy to move…I choose to have chronic pain and sit in isolation because of it?” Doubtful
Instead, the choice really comes from the choice of a habit.  THE HABIT starts in the mind.  Which develops the program to stick with it. ✅Health isn’t always easy.  So if the habit isn’t formed first when you choose to change your health status, it’s real easy to fall off course when it gets challenging…when you’re tired…when you are too busy….
✅Start with a choice to PROGRAM those habits for good so you can stay consistent and go stronger longer!

🌿There is no greater connection when it comes to your health than the mind-body connection.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
One of the questions I get asked the most when talking about my healing journey is 🤷🏻‍♀️“how do you do it?” How do you stop eating gluten? How do you find the energy? How are you not angry?⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
➡️And my answer? It’s all about mindset.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Our health is influenced drastically by our thought processes🧠. Negative thoughts and self-loathing have no place in your healing journey. Why?⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
𝐀 𝐧𝐞𝐠𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐞 𝐨𝐮𝐭𝐥𝐨𝐨𝐤 𝐰𝐨𝐧’𝐭 𝐜𝐡𝐚𝐧𝐠𝐞 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐝𝐢𝐚𝐠𝐧𝐨𝐬𝐢𝐬.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It’s not going to change the fact that you have A chronic illness.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
In fact, a negative mindset is more likely to produce adverse health effects than anything. Chronic stress leads to inflammation and activates the adrenal glands to disproportionately release cortisol and adrenaline, the stress hormones.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
•⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
In order to be well, you need to put yourself in a mindset that allows for healing to occur.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

This means:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

firstComment:
Regaining Control of Your Health…Day 8
HOW KIND YOU ARE TO YOUR BODY
Do you make it a point to show kindness to your body each day, or do you waste time beating up on yourself?
Kindness to your body could look different each day…..some days it may mean a purposeful intense workout, other days it might be a nap or a slice of cake.
Kindness to your body means going stronger longer.
Health is not about hustling more and pushing yourself to the death each day.  It’s about meeting your body each day where it is with kindness and giving it the movement, recovery, encouragement, fuel it may need each day.
If you haven’t yet already, head over to @bejourneystrong where we go live daily to bring you 5 minutes of purposeful movement to feel and live better!

alt: Image may contain: food
firstComment:
Regaining Control of Your Health….Day 7
WHAT YOU EAT

The only one who gets the final say in what you eat is YOU!

Start being intentional about how and what you eat.  Listen to how it makes you feel when you eat certain foods.  When you start listening to this story, you start noticing what foods are worth it or not worth it to put into your body.

If you don’t like how you feel after eating a certain food, then start making choices to eat alternatives, eat sparingly, or avoid all-together.

It’s not about depriving and judging yourself.  It’s about learning how your body responds to what you eat and make choices accordingly about who you want to be and how you want to feel.
Make sure to check out our community where we are building something big to simplify the way we do health and take the complexity and struggle out of it!  https://www.facebook.com/groups/394680181240520/

WHO YOU SPEND YOUR TIME WITH

Ever heard the saying “you are the sum of the 5 people you spend the most time with”?

firstComment:
Regaining Control of Your Health….Day 1

There’s a lot in life you can’t control.  That may make you feel anxious or overwhelmed. 
For the control freaks out there, I have assuring news:  there is SO much you can control when it comes to your health and success! ‼️YOUR ATTITUDE

Yep, you’ve heard it before: attitude is everything.  What your attitude is about your body, your health, your ability to be healthy, how you feel about the word exercise will affect everything about your ability to be healthy. 
Shifting what you say to yourself is the first thing you can control in making an impact on your health.  When you start believing you can make adjustments in your life to a positve healthy outlook, you will start becomming intentional about actually doing it.  If you have a negative attitude about exercise, find an activity that you do enjoy that involves moving your body and doing good to it.
Let’s start taking back some of the control and make a transformation in your health!

As I look at these pictures side by side, I am in absolute awe of God’s goodness and His promises.
⠀⠀
The picture on the left was taken about 6 months in to our wellness journey we started as a couple in 2019. Our wellness journey actually didn’t start solely as a physical wellness journey. We knew we both wanted to be more active, but our consistent actions to physical wellness didn’t start until right after that pic on the left was taken.
⠀⠀
In January 2019 our wellness journey actually started with Dave Ramsey’s Financial Peace course. 9 Sunday evenings we met with couples just like us who were sick and tired of being sick and tired. And we made a decision to change our mindset, change our habits, and change our legacy.

In the left pic, we felt overwhelmingly blessed. Josh had just started a new job, we were gaining momentum (FINALLY) in our debt snowball, and we were gaining confidence in our journey. We had no idea that just 5 months later we would take the pic on the left and we would be celebrating some awesome things.
.

1️⃣ the successful start of physical wellness journeys that turned into another source of income.
.

2️⃣ almost $25k of debt paid off (we hit that by Dec 2019! And most of it was done between these two pics).
.

3️⃣ regained confidence, spiritual wellness, and joy found in our willingness to say yes to opportunities the Lord placed at our feet (worship leaders, wellness coaches, social media advisors) and so much more.

You see...what we didn’t realize in Jan 2019 and even at the time the pic on the left was taken...is that when you say YES to wellness in one area of your life, the Lord does a pretty amazing job at revealing paths to wellness in ALL areas of our lives.
.

What areas of wellness are ready to say YES to this year? What areas of your life are you ready to see transformed by Lord’s grace and goodness? If you’re ready to #choosejoy this year, I’d love to chat with you mire about my own journey and help you find joy in yours!

Are you ready to be transformed? Say yes babe.

🧘🏻‍♀️HEALTH GOALS
Dinner tonight was grass-fed beef with Monterey Jack cheese; baby spinach cooked with coconut oil, onions and garlic; and a few orange slices for a vitamin c boost to enhance iron absorption.🍊
.
🥕One of my health goals for the New Year (and beyond 😍) is eating more real food, especially veggies. 🍅🥑🍳🥦🥬🥥🍓🥒🥝🥕My eating habits were relaxed and out of whack during the holidays and now my body is feeling the strain of inflammation and toxicity. Maybe you can relate? 🤷🏼‍♀️ If I hadn't done intermittent fasting I'm not sure where I would be right now.🙋🏽‍♀️
.
🥕Also working on some nutritional imbalances, healing leaky gut, autoimmune and ongoing chronic Lyme (which sparked some of the other issues)
. 🥕Moving my body more consistently every day... even if it doesn't seem like enough to me. Doing something is healthy and better than doing nothing.
. 🥕 Intermittent fasting - I've been doing this for a few years now and my body is loving it so much! I've gone from doing 16:8  to 18:6, OMAD and a 30+ hour fast. I'm ready for a new challenge in this area and plan to do a couple of longer fasts this year.
. 🥕 Gratitude and Kindness. Continue to focus on gratitude by journaling, sharing, etc. ✳️Kindness is my word for the year. I have a lot of work to do but I really want my actions to reflect kindness to others. It may be an underrated quality but I believe everyone can benefit from kindness.. I added this to my health goals because these can impact your mental health and well-being 🤗
.
I made myself write some of these goals down here to keep me accountable. It's not always easy for me to share things like this because I think things like *will anyone read this 😅 and *if they do will they care or find something useful here? 💖 But I guess this is part of being vulnerable... 😂So here's to our best year yet!

⏲️Just an update, for those of you who have asked... Intermittent fasting continues to play a huge role in my wellness regimen. I've been fasting for several years now regularly and it has improved my health in many ways including healing my severe reactive hypoglycemia, eliminating cravings for sweets and carbs, reducing inflammation and pain caused by chronic Lyme and so much more.
.
Many people ask what eating plan I'm following and overall I stick with a Paleo eating plan, mostly low-carb and low-sugar. I have been strictly keto in the past because of lots of food allergies due to Lyme and autoimmune but as things calm down I'm not as strict with the keto as I once was... Out of necessity. Definitely  low carb and low sugar as much as possible but allow myself occasional treats. I don't do deprivation mindset. 😜My focus is definitely on eating real, micronutrient-dense food and staying away from processed foods as much as possible. Basically I'm trying to follow the research and listen to what my body needs (not into denying food groups) at this point in my health journey. So thankful for the healing that has occurred thus far but still much work to be done! I'm so grateful for the supportive health and Lyme communities on Insta! There are so many quality people here on similar wellness journeys. Happy to connect! 🙏💚🌱 .

alt: Image may contain: text
firstComment:
Your Pain does Not Define You…
I’ve heard every reason and justification for pain over the years as a Physical Therapist.  I get it:  You have a history.  You have legitimate things that have happened.  You have genetics.  But no matter what TYPE of pain you have, it does not get to dictate WHO YOU ARE.

When you allow that to happen, you get trapped in your pain.  You’re too focussed on your pain that you don’t know what life looks like without it.  The stories of “I can’t” begin to take over and you start looking for alternatives to sooth your pain, but not resolve it.

Yet I know you don’t want to hurt.  I like to ask people, “What does pain free look like?  What would it give you the freedom to do with a solution to the pain?”
Typically people don’t have an answer to that. 
I hear you.  You have pains, but I know you want to be well.  I want it for you.  I know it’s more than a bunch of band-aid numbing agents to solve it.  It’s going to take a course of transforming the mind, to transform the body and the spirit.  And then, you will feel free.  No longer trapped in your pain.  No longer letting your pain decide who you are and how you live. 👊🏼
Does that kind of life sound like one you want to live?  I’m here, waiting for you.  With the solution to transform your life through movement of not just your body, but your brain. 🧠
Join me now for the opportunity to live a life you love through the body you love!

alt: Image may contain: food, possible text that says 'TAVERN Food for fuel? Food for PICUCOLLAGE thought'
firstComment:
Is your mental diet sabotaging your physical diet?

Have you ever felt your stomach feel bloated or unsettled during a time of stress?
Or after feeling guilty for eating so”bad?”
Or perhaps you’re just stressed out about your restricted diet.

These negative emotions can be sending signals to your gut.  The vagus nerve is the longest cranial nerve and travels from brain stem to the lower part of your small intestine.

So when your brain perceives stress about what you’re eating or stress in general, it can be transferred to the gut.

When your gut feels your emotional tension your food won’t digest the way it should. So now your diet is not as successful as you hoped because of the limited blood flow to the gut.

Stress shuts down digestion!
This is why training the brain and calming the system is just as important as training the rest of your body. 
Check out my IGTV episode on this matter to hear more!

Plantar fasciitis?  Achilles pain? Heel pain?

The worst!  As a runner I know this first hand. Worst injury I’ve ever experienced!  As a physical therapist I know how nagging and debilitating it can be in every day life. It’s hard to rest your feet. 🦶🏽 And a runner needs to run, right @runnersworldmag !? Usually these pains are stemming from a source outside the foot and they need to be addressed three dimensionally because of how the foot works. 
There’s usually a component at the hip. 
This is why I love this stretch. Shifting 3 ways, moving at the ankle and hip. Preparing your body to move how it’s designed.

I came across this picture of me 5 months post partum with my first baby (I'm the one in the middle). I don't look like I recently had a baby .

I made milk like a champ (so much that I got the gift of giving milk to mamas who didn't make any.

The weight poured off.

I was told how great I looked.  How lucky I was to have my body back .

What they didn't know was:
✔️ I hated that my pants were literally falling off me because I lost my butt
✔️ I counted calories to put weight on and hated it
✔️I felt guilty eating ice cream every night when so many women struggled to lose weight
✔️ I had agonizing painful sex
✔️ I probably peed myself at this race
✔️I couldn't talk to anyone about it because I'd just get a snarky comment of, "oh that must be so hard 🙄" I look at this picture and it kills me.  I think I look sickly and unwell.  Yet I was being told how lucky I was to be skinny.

You see, skinny is not all it's cracked up to be.  Skinny doesn't mean healthy. 
Being healthy and happy in the body you have is what matters.

Are you struggling to have a body you feel good in, look good in and feel good about?  Where do you struggle with your body?

Rest is not applauded in our society.

We are all about the go, go, go 🙋‍♀️Me too....I’m a do-er. I forget sometimes to stop.

For me, I don’t really do a lot of activities I don’t like doing.  I keep busy with things I love with people I love.  But just because they’re good, fun, productive activities doesn’t mean I have to do them all the time.

Rest is not lazy.

I used to struggle with missing a day at the gym or missing a run.  I felt guilty like I had to “make up for it.”
Have you ever felt like you’re fat and lazy for taking a rest day and skipping a workout? 🤔

As I have grown, I have learned the power of honoring myself, my body and my health with a day of rest. ✅Actually noticing that with a rest period, I come back stronger.

This is SO freeing!
💥To know that you don’t have to hustle all the time.  That giving yourself the gift of rest could actually strengthen not just your body, but your mind and spirit!

Have you ever pushed so hard (even if it was something you enjoyed) and ended up being completely destroyed afterwards?  Either sick, burnt out, mentally or emotionally drained, or physically injured?

I can think about so many times when I have.
❌No more (ok well, I’m still a work in progress). I am giving my health the gift and honor of rest.  To rest, recover and restore, ✅So in the end you can move, feel, live and BEcome the best version you were created to be!

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'OPTIMIZING HEALTH OUR REWARD YOURSELF'
firstComment:
Your brain is wired for rewards.

You get little hits of Dopamine (which is a feel good chemical) when you experience something new or exciting.  When you succeed.

What happens though, is that you go around with an endless to-do list that is not complete at the end of the day.  You feel worthless.  Unsuccessful.

You set lofty goals of exercising, losing weight and eating well.

You want to hustle through and “make it happen.” But the list goes on, the hustle drive wears off.  You end back up where you started.

Instead, set little goals each day.  To help achieve little successes.  To get that Dopamine hit which will keep you going, especially when it gets hard and exhausting.  When the hustle doesn’t work anymore.  I set my big 3 goals of the day..... and can accomplish 3 things.  Then, I reward when I complete them.

The reward can be small like a little treat or quick walk, or something bigger.  But when you give that reward, your brain wants to keep going. ✅That is what will keep you moving on your health, wellness, healing journey, and your journey to BEcoming your best self.

firstComment:
It used to be believed that you couldn’t change or reprogram your brain. 
Neuroscience has done some amazing stuff to prove otherwise.

I remember going through Physical Therapy school and it was just being discovered that stroke patients could actually regenerate the weak side.  They could reprogram those neural connections and make a change!  That’s amazing.

But it isn’t easy.  It takes repetition and time.

Hardwiring the automated programs in your brain is the same.
Some of the stories come from childhood and are mostly programmed to keep you safe. 👊🏼Safe doesn’t heal you.  Safe doesn’t progress you.  Safe doesn’t allow you to fulfill your greatest potential, whether that is physical, emotional, career, mental. ✅Hardwiring your brain means refuting the stories that tell you “can’t, not good enough, unworthy, unable....”
✅Hardwiring means replacing those stories with the truth (seriously, you don’t know you can’t if you’ve never tried)
✅Hardwiring means being consistent with the new program and trusting the long journey 
Creating this new program can change your life.  It can change how you move and feel in your body.  How you show up in the world.  How you change your health.  How you move forward and rock your greatest self.
