alt: Image may contain: one or more people and outdoor
firstComment:
Transition is a major struggle point.  It is a stopping point to so many to grow, heal, progress, enjoy and live. ❗️WHY?

Transition leads to discomfort.  It is the brain perceiving something unfamiliar and scary!  It is a place the brain has never been and you don’t know how to navigate through it.  So then the excuses and procrastination begins.

But this isn’t your fault!  The brain goes into protection mode to keep you safe!

What kinds of transitions are there.
✔️Career ✔️Marriage ✔️Kids
✔️Aging
✔️Injuries ✔️Divorce ✔️Aging parents ✔️Death
✔️Empty nesting

What happens is we often get lost in transition.  We get lost in the newness and the destination.

Frequently what I’ve heard as a Physical Therapist has been, “I can’t take care of my health because.... I have a demanding job...I have the kids...I’m injured right now.....”
The “I can’t “ takes over❗️ Then I hear, “When I get through....I will start taking care of myself.....” No you won’t!
Because it’s destination seeking rather than looking inside.  It is allowing the transition to define you to believe the destination matters. ❌No more!

How do we shape that transition to be successful through it?  How do you meet your body/life where you’re at?  It might look different during the transition, but it’s about the process, not the destination.

I am here to facilitate you committing to you.  Empowering you to be successful through your transitions!

I do

I met @journeywarrior8 before going to physical therapy schedule, now nearly 20 years ago.

Since then, we have realized our brains and hearts are so in line with each other (it's scary sometimes). And now we twin on occasion without planning.

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'OPTIMIZING OUR HEALTH: AVOID SOCIAL MEDIA FIRST THING IN THE MORNING'
firstComment:
What is the first thing you do when you get up in the morning? 
If you’re like me, you use your phone as an alarm clock.  Nothing wrong with that.

But, do you immediately check your socials, check your email?
That starts your day reactively and already on someone else’s agenda.

Do you know it actually does something to your brain? 🧠 ✅you get a Dopamine hit
✅So, your brain is filled with Dopamine, which means Serotonin is less effective (serotonin helps you think and concentrate)

Serotonin is highest in the morning, so now if you start your day suppressing it, you will not be able to be your most focused, productive and deepest thinking for the day! 🤯

I find this fascinating!

Limiting the socials first thing can make me more productive and focused? Sign me up! 🙋‍♀️ What are your strategies for avoiding social media first thing?  Why do you struggle with it?  Let me know what you think 🤔

In my weakness, I am strong 
Strength is not about how much weight you can push around.
I workout with some pretty bad ass women who are totally stronger than me.
But that does not mean I’m weak.
It means my body is different from theirs.
I don’t have to keep up with anyone but myself.

I show up each day, meeting my body and my brain where it is each day.  To be my best.

Strength is about ✔️resilience ✔️being fierce
✔️standing up for who you are and what you believe ✔️putting your best effort each day
✔️not letting anyone define you
✔️trusting the journey 
Have you ever felt weak? Or been told you’re weak or not good enough?
I’ve been told “I can’t tell you anything because you can’t handle it “ because I cry.  It’s ok to cry!  It’s ok to have a meltdown (in fact they feel good!)
Your weakness is part of your strength.  It’s the part that rises up from the storm.

It’s the strength that pushes you toward your best version, showing up each day to yourself and those who matter; moving, feeling and living well.  No matter what your journey.

So have your meltdown, process through, then heal.

So even though my crew might be stronger and faster most days, I’m pretty damn strong and am ready to shine light and create a place where people can move their physical bodies, but their hearts and spirits to be healthy and strong 💪🏼 #medicinewomanrising

firstComment:
Health is not just what you eat.  It’s not just about exercise.

It’s also about who you spend time with, what you watch, what you listen to.

When you listen to failure, you bring failure.
When you only hear no hope, your life is hopeless.
When you only hear the negative stories, that is what will come.

What you focus on grows.  Your brain automates to make things easy and conserve energy.  So when the negative thoughts is all you hear, the brain will store them and you will become them.

When you listen to stories of hope, joy, momentum, peace, love, those things grow.

When you listen to the fact that you can be healthy, you can move pain free, you can feel good in your body, they will start to be re-programmed in your brain. 
What are you listening to?  Do you believe you can be healthy, happy, successful? 
Drop a comment below on what you do to help stop listening to the negative talk?

Nobody has a problem taking about going to the gym and conditioning the body.

But we squirm a little when we talk about conditioning our minds. 
It is interpreted as some weird spiritually thing, mystical meditative thing.  It’s made for “those” people, not me, ❗️Spoiler alert! We ALL have a mind.

And it could all need work.

It could be spiritual or meditative.  It could just being quiet and listening to your body, mind and heart. ✔️Listening is the first step.
✔️Then, decide if those beliefs are really true, or is it just a story in your head.
✔️Then replace them

Without this conditioning, you will continue to struggle with your physical conditioning.  You will get motivated and hustle and push.....that only lasts so long....
Then you get the urge again.....and the cycle continues. 
Until your mind is strong and well, your physical endeavors will continue to struggle.  This is truly where the conditioning needs to start, yet it’s usually the last.

firstComment:
Conditioning your body is more than just having a physical appearance.

While we all want to look good in our body, more important is when we feel good in our body.  When we feel good in our body, we feel good about our body, and the external physical shines.

Conditioning the inside out is vital to health as well. 
We don’t have any trouble talking about our conditioning of our body in the gym.  But we struggle to talk about the conditioning and healing of our emotional and mental well-being.  We fear looking like we have “issues “ if we do that.....That’s for the other people, we say.

But truthfully, we all have issues.  And we certainly all have a heart and mind.  And it is just as important to take care of and condition as your physical body. 
What is unwell on the inside will eventually show on the outside and even manifest in physical symptoms, pain or illness.

So remember, with conditioning, it requires:
✔️Variety (stimulates the body and brain)
✔️All aspects of the body inside and out
✔️Shining your best self to give your best self ✔️Moving forward each day to learn grow and heal 
Do you struggle with any of these aspects?
What types of things do you condition and how?
Where do you need support in this?

I am ready to shine my best self and condition in order to facilitate a space for you to do the same.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, pool, closeup and outdoor
firstComment:
Give yourself permission to dream

I struggle with this sometimes. I’m a realist. I’m practical. I don’t want all the “fluff.” I just want to know what I have to do and do it. 
That doesn’t always serve us. It doesn’t always shine our best version. 
We don’t dream about the potential of our health and physical bodies in the same way we don’t dream about our life and goals. 
I had a dream one time of running a marathon. The first time I said it out loud, I didn’t know how far that was. 😂
When I learned, fear kicked in of “I could never run that far”

But my crazy dream tugged at me and little by little, I added miles. ✅What I didn’t know was that I’d end up running 6. ✅I didn’t know how much it would impact my career ✅I didn’t know the friends I would make (runners are a special kind of fun and crazy)

Had I ignored a crazy dream, I would have missed out on so much fun, growth and challenge in my life. 
Dare to dream. Don’t let fear have all the fun. For your physical body, health and life. 
That dream, broken down in small chunks will come to life. 💥And through it, you will move, feel, live and be the best expression of yourself!
@journeywarrior8 @drshannonirvine

alt: Photo by LUCERO| Health + Fitness🌱🍃🌿 on March 12, 2020.
firstComment:
Hydration 💦 🥥 ⁣
⁣
⁣
There are tons of different sport drinks on the market that promise to replenish lost electrolytes after working out. Many of those drinks do have electrolytes but they also have tons of chemicals to make them look appealing to they eye with the brightest colors of the rainbow. Those unatural florescent colors effect the PH level of the drink, and most of them are very acidic! Let's take it back to the PH scale from our chemistry class... The scale goes from 1-14: 1 being very acidic, 14 being Alkaline, and 7, the half way between the acidity and alkalinity, being neutral. The neutral and alkalinity state is where our body thrives. Coconut water is the best sport drink to replenish lost electrolytes, and water is what gives us energy to keep moving. If you find it difficult to make up your mind on what sports drink to indulge in after your workout, choose water first or coconut water if you need electrolyte replenishment. ⁣
⁣
#coconutwater #h2o #alkaline ⁣

alt: Photo by LUCERO| Health + Fitness🌱🍃🌿 on March 09, 2020. Image may contain: 1 person, child, sky, tree and outdoor
firstComment:
‪The most important thing I've learned about fitness is that the most crucial  muscle to strengthen is the mind. Many times we focus so much on our external appearance that we forget to nourish our inner being. Throughout our lives we encounter many different events that are life-changing; The first wall of defense that all those changes attack is our mind, and that causes us to have constant battles in our mind that are beyond our control. External appearance is important, but personally, tranquility in my mind will always be the most important part of my wellness journey. 💕🌱‬⁣
⁣
🌿⁣
⁣
Lo más importante que he aprendido sobre el estado físico es que el músculo más crucial que hay que fortalecer, es la mente. Muchas veces nos enfocamos tanto en nuestra apariencia externa que nos olvidamos de nutrir nuestro ser interior. A lo largo de nuestras vidas nos encontramos con muchos eventos diferentes que cambian la vida; El primer muro de defensa que atacan todos esos cambios es nuestra mente, y eso nos hace tener batallas constantes en nuestra mente que están fuera de nuestro control. La apariencia externa es importante, pero personalmente, la tranquilidad en mi mente siempre será la parte más importante de mi viaje de bienestar. 💕🌱⁣
⁣
⁣

alt: Photo by LUCERO| Health + Fitness🌱🍃🌿 on March 04, 2020. Image may contain: 2 people, shoes and indoor
firstComment:
Full body workout/ warmup ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Yesterday was my first time exercising in a little over a week due to me being sick. My body was aching and needed some rest. Usually when I get sick, I layer up and workout to sweat out the sickness... but this time my body just couldn’t do that, so I listened to it and rested. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
When I go a full week without exercising my muscles, I feel tired and lazy- so I usually do a full body warmup/workout to awaken all the muscles before I start isolating muscles or doing high intensity workouts. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you go for a long period of time without exercising, or if you are just beginning to exercise, always check in with your body to see if your body is ready to go. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I did 5 rounds of 12 repetitions for the leg exercises. Do all three lunge variation exercises consecutive for each set of the leg exercises. For the upper body exercises, I did 4 rounds of 10 repetitions. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you’re feeling adventurous try the wall core exercise. I did 4 Sets of 12 repetitions. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣

firstComment:
Arm workout 💪🏼⁣
⁣
⁣
✨10 rounds of 10 repetitions for each exercise. ⁣
⁣
These exercises do not require the use of heavy dumbbells; I’m using two 2 lb dumbbells. You can use water bottles if dumbbells are not available to you. ⁣
⁣
*Make sure the end of both dumbbells are touching at all times during each exercise. ⁣
⁣
🌱⁣
⁣
⁣
Entrenamiento del brazo 💪🏼⁣
⁣
⁣
✨10 rondas de 10 repeticiones para cada ejercicio.⁣
⁣
Estos ejercicios no requieren el uso de pesas pesadas; Estoy usando dos pesas de 2 lb. Puede usar botellas de agua si no tiene pesas disponibles.⁣
⁣
* Asegúrese de que el final de ambas pesas se toque en todo momento durante cada ejercicio⁣

firstComment:
#veggietacos 🌱⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Obviously I love tacos- so when I made the decision to become vegetarian, Tacos were the ONE thing I was going to miss the most! I used to eat Carne Asada tacos at least twice a week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Now that I have different food preferences, I'm still able to enjoy my favorite food, Tacos! I just enjoy them in the #vegeterian version, which are amazing! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
@bartacolife has some unique and delicious vegetarian taco options.
⁣⁣
I had the Cauliflower, the Portobello with queso fresco and the Falafel tacos; All of them were amazing. And the best part is that all their ingredients are made in-house. They definitely have a different take on the real street tacos, pero si tienen su delicia única 😋 🌱⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣

firstComment:
Lower Body Workout🏋🏻‍♀️⁣
⁣
 5 rounds of 12 repetitions for each exercise. Make sure to keep the core engaged for every single one of the exercises. ⁣
⁣
✨Stationary Lunge with knee to the ground (hands are only resting on the leg, all the weight should be on the front leg).⁣
⁣
✨Side Lunge (you don’t have to go as deep, do what feels comfortable for your hips).⁣
⁣
✨Squat Walk (the length of the mat one way count as 1 repetition). ⁣
⁣
⁣
🌱💕⁣
⁣
⁣
Entrenamiento para piernas 🏋🏻‍♀️⁣
⁣ ⁣
5 rondas de 12 repeticiones para cada ejercicio. Asegúrese de mantener el núcleo comprometido para cada uno de los ejercicios.⁣
⁣
✨ Estocada estacionaria con la rodilla en el suelo (las manos solo descansan sobre la pierna, todo el peso debe estar sobre la pierna delantera).⁣
⁣
✨ Side Lunge (no tienes que ir tan profundo, haz lo que sea cómodo para tus caderas).⁣
⁣
✨Squat Walk (la longitud del tapete unidireccional cuenta como 1 repetición).⁣
⁣
⁣

⁣
7 Rounds of  20/15/10/5 /15/10/5 repetitions ⁣
for each of the exercises. If you have never done this amount of repetitions or it’s your first time working out, do the first 3 rounds: 20/15/10 , or as many as that your body can handle! ⁣

⁣
✨Foward dive burpee (this  exercise isolates the shoulders and triceps) ⁣

alt: Photo by LUCERO| Health + Fitness🌱🍃🌿 in Cooper's Hawk Winery & Restaurant. Image may contain: food
firstComment:
#foodiefriday 🌱⁣
⁣
@chwinery has a delicious Red Vegetable Burger made in-house; made out of red quinoa, black beans, and toasted rolled oats. It's served with arugula, hummus, and cucumber feta cream; it also comes with a side of a tasty fennel quinoa salad. ⁣
⁣
⁣
More and more restaurants are respecting that some people just don’t want to eat meat; so they are expanding their Vegetarian and Vegan menu options. One of the popular items that restaurants are now turning to is “impossible meat” to create more 'meat-like' options. ⁣
⁣
People that are looking to limit their meat consumption and are in search  of healthier food alternatives must be cautious of the foods that they eat when they go out. A plant-based burger sounds “healthy", when in reality, at the end of the day it is still a burger: High in calories, cooked in tons of oil and not the healthiest for you. Also, most places don’t make the impossible meat in-house, so that means that it’s pre-made, pre-packaged and Yes... It has TONS of preservatives! So no, it might still not be healthy even though it’s considered plant-based. Every now and then it’s okay to eat it, but don’t think of it as a healthier alternative- think of it as a  day meal. ⁣
⁣
Happy Friday!🌞🌱💕
⁣

firstComment:
If you’re always on-the-go, you’re most likely to snack on “foods” that are not the healthiest for you. ⁣
⁣
When I was younger, my go-to snacks were protein bars- until I learned that some of them are LOADED with chemicals and do more harm than good. Now when I know I’m going to be running errands all day, I make protein pancakes in the morning or eat a meal that I know is going to keep me full for most of the day. Doing this helps me avoid “foods” that have zero nourishment for my body. ⁣
⁣
Like I mentioned before, I use a plant-based protein. @drinkorgain is a protein that I’ve been using for a while; I like the quality ⁣of its ingredients and I love the flavors that they offer. Also, this is one of the few proteins that does not upset my stomach. ⁣
⁣
If anyone is interested, ⁣
use the code BEJEWELED to get 30% off your first purchase. ⁣
⁣
Protein pancakes 🥞 ⁣
⁣
✨1 banana, mashed ⁣
✨1 Tbsp of coconut milk ⁣
✨2 scoops of @drinkorgain vanilla bean protein powder ⁣
✨1/2 cup egg whites ⁣
✨1 tsp of ground cinnamon ⁣
✨1 tsp of vanilla extract⁣
⁣
In a bowl, mash the banana and coconut milk together, then add the rest of the ingredients. Cook over medium- low. Cook until you see bubbles rising. Flip and cook the other side and 💥 Delicious protein pancakes. ⁣
⁣
enjoy with @vermont.organic.maple syrup ⁣
⁣
⁣

#Quadriceps ✨
⁣
My exercises are a little different than what you might be used to seeing, but I promise, the results speak for themselves! Trust the process and explore what works specifically for YOUR body as well. ⁣
⁣
Whenever you do an exercise, keep track of how many repetitions and sets that you do and also write how your body feels the next day. Write if you were sore and if so, specifically what area(s). Keep track of everything so you can go back and see what did and what didn’t work for you. ⁣
⁣
⁣
4 round of 10 repetitions for each of the exercises. ⁣
⁣
✨1stvideo-5 minute warmup ⁣
✨2ndvideo- seated leg raises (control the movement) ⁣
✨3rd video- lying kneebacks ⁣
✨4th video - standing knee-ups (*use a broom stick if you need to modified it ) ⁣
⁣
⁣
*You can do them with or without the resistance band- but if it’s your first time doing exercises like these, don’t use resistant bands. Also as usual you can also modify the exercises to your level.⁣

firstComment:
Yes, I am HUMAN, I do crave foods that are not the healthiest nor the most nourishing for my body. I have one and, sometimes, two “cheat days” each week where I have foods that I like but wouldn’t eat on a daily basis. ⁣
⁣
I also do go out to eat, but not often. I am very picky with my food and I would rather cook it myself to avoid the disappointment of no liking it. ⁣
⁣
If you’re on this wellness journey, don’t think that it means that you can never have the foods that you eat now, it only means that you cannot have them as often. It’ll definitely be tough at the beginning to cut those foods from your daily diet, but once your body gets used to your new eating habits, It’ll definitely get easier to let go of such foods and only eat them every now and then...⁣
⁣
If you do go out to eat on your “cheat day”, I would recommend trying @wildberrypancakesandcafe They have the fluffiest pancakes with toppings that are out of this world! ⁣
Happy Saturday 🧡⁣
⁣
#foodie #foodphotography #igfoodies #wellnessjourneywithlucero #pancakes #cheatmeal #cheatday #nutriton #fitmom #followformoreposts

Hamstrings 🦵🏼⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We don’t really realize how much we use our hamstring muscles on the daily basis, until we feel the soreness the next day after a hamstring workout. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The hamstring muscle is a muscle that must be treated with delicacy because it’s prone to injury if you stretch it too fast or try to use too much weight when doing hamstring exercises. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I did 100 low impact butt kicks to warm up. (lean slightly forward when doing the butt kicks) ⁣⁣
3 rounds of 20 repetitions( 3x20) for each of the three exercises ⁣⁣
⁣
Remember to control the movement and to move at your own pace. ⁣⁣
***For the last exercise you can hold onto a chair or the wall for support if needed. ⁣⁣
⁣

firstComment:
The stockings with sexy embroidery, the green bikini and red hat decorated with colorful feathers gifted by macaws were all together hanging out in the jungle.
How welcome my spirt feels in this Magical place, one of my favourite scenarios for Sexy Wellness. The mirror is the cenote and the freedom to BE who you are is amazing!!! Play time!!! The only "rule" is to let go the mind ... coming from "The busy world" that takes a second.. or a couple of days. At least to me ... I have to do stuff with my body to let go the mind. Diving head to water always helps .. feeling the water , seeing the tree under and the heart above . It is truly magic.
Alone or with my lover this is a Two Day minimal experience.  Surrounded by jungle, bathed by millions of stars at night and cleaning cenote waters. Off the beaten path, just us (and Eufemia de dog) 
The luxury to be as close to nature as possible. Sexy starts when one is capable to feel to breathe deep naked soul and body if you wish!!!! Ahhhhhh!!!!! How liberating !!!! ❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤❤Las medias del bordado sexy, el bikini verde y el sombrero rojo con plumas regaladas por guacamayas. Ese dia salieron juntos a jugar. Bienvenida!! Así me sentí en La Torre Magica, uno de mis escenarios favoritos para Sexy Wellness. "Aquí el espejo es el mismo cenote, y uno puede jugar a Ser quien quiera Ser" con ropa, sin ropa.. sola o con mi amante , el único requisito es la honestidad del alma, las ganas del corazón a soltar a fluir , el deseo en la piel de Sentir de conectar.. de Amar. Cuando uno viene del mundo ocupado toma un día o dos.. o más... pero después de varios clavados de cabeza al agua, la mente canija va abriendo paso al corazón.

Esta experiencia es de dos noches mínimo.  Rodeada de selva , bañada de estrellas y aguas mágicas que reconectan espíritus confundidos con la verdad de la vida . Solo SER. (Y que delicia andar como Adán y Eva!!) ❤🔥❤🔥❤🔥❤🔥❤🔥❤🔥❤🔥❤

🌟I AM IRRESISTIBLE🌟

When I R I S E into my confidence I attract positive people and opportunities. 
I’m working on eliminating toxic people and environments from my life. I’ve made some changes already and it’s amazing how these little changes have made such a huge impact. That’s why I love this community so much because I’m surrounded by positive humans all day. We’ve all got our shit but we’re here for each other and we’re all just trying to live our lives as healthy and happy as possible.

We show up for ourselves so we can show up for YOU! 
I’ve got the positive people. As for the opportunities.... Well, ever since I started coaching it’s given me the opportunity to hold myself even more accountable. Help others and even help me financially. 
Sounds like a pretty positive life to me. I can help you start to remove the toxicity in your life. But it starts with you!!! If you’re ready to do that, I’m here for you.

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and eyeglasses
firstComment:
HAPPY 😊 JOYOUS 🤗 FREE 👊🏽 That’s how I want to live my life. I take action everyday, whether you see it or not to be those things. And it’s hard. Really hard. Some days I feel like I’m on top of the world 🌎 and everything is coming along just so effortlessly. Most days it’s a fucking shit show 😂 And it’s not really external but internal. I struggle. And I have to work on it, on MYSELF EVERY 👏🏼SINGLE 👏🏼DAMN 👏🏼 DAY👏🏼 If you can’t relate to that... cool 😎 you got it all figured out sister. But are you growing? Do you challenge yourself? Do you get uncomfortable 😣 Or are you perfectly fine with things? Content. If so, awesome. But I don’t want to be just fine. I want to get uncomfortable. I want to challenge myself. I want continue to work on myself everyday. For the rest of my life. Because if I don’t, there’s no growth. And to me that’s not cool. Sure, I get complacent. We all do. But then something needs to change. Maybe a new hobby. Maybe a new recipe. New workout. New vegetable 🌶 SOMETHING! Change it up. Get uncomfortable. Start small. I challenge you to do something that makes you uncomfortable this weekend!! Share below!! Blow up the comments! What makes you uncomfortable 😣

When I started hearing about essential oils the word “oily person” would always come up. Personally I thought it was kind of a silly thing to call yourself, but hear I am. 💁🏼‍♀️ Since entering into this world of holistic living + essential oils, I have learned what the true meaning of these words “oily person” really is. I have become so proud to stand behind it + feel incredibly privileged to be apart of this growing community because there is so much power behind it.

It’s not just about having a shelf of essential oils of all different scents displayed in your house or the many pretty diffusers that you can now purchase online to express your personality.

It’s about the ability to take control over your health + body and regaining that power that you feel you may have lost over the years to make a change for you and your loved ones future self.

It’s about learning to go back + use plants to boost our immune systems like we use to way back when until our culture started introducing products that are filled with toxins + chemicals that now harm us without us even knowing. And the biggest thing is, its about living your life to the fullest.

Our health can bog us down, make us feel like there are no other options when unknowingly there is a whole other way of living that for some is yet to be explored.

Learning to live without chemicals has made a huge impact in my life and a lot of others who I personally know + others who I just have the privilege of hearing about, so it can for you too.

alt: Image may contain: plant, grass, outdoor and nature
firstComment:
11th Day of the Moon!!
🌓✨💫
A couple of supportive activities to consider on this special day to maximize its healing benefits:
It’s al about balance. Your body is calibrating. Go easy on yourself. Practice self-romance. Get flowers for yourself and arrange them beautifully. Take time to smell them. Sun gaze in the morning. Try Tree Pose in Nature. Feel your physical body shifting to balance against the elements of earth, wind and sun.
Take time in the shower to perform hydrotherapy and stimulate your glands. Spend 2-3 minutes allowing very hot water to hit your throat. This massages and soothes the thyroid. Then brave it up and blast the cold water for about 3-4 minutes. Use your hands to gently massage behind your ears, your armpits, and boobies while you face the cold water. Then turn around and as the cold water runs down your spine, use your hands to massage your adrenal glands (mid back) and your kidneys (lower back). You are reducing inflammation with this process and signaling the glands to harmonize and take command of your moods.
You can repair so much tissue with these simple techniques. This is for vitality!! When your glands work properly you don’t just live longer…you live YOUNGER!

@WebMD notes that deer antler velvet is used to increase #libido, treat male erectile dysfunction, and improve fertility. Traditionally, deer antler velvet was used to remedy sexual disorders in men such as premature ejaculation, watery semen and impotence.⠀
⠀

firstComment:
HAPPY WORLD SMILE DAY 😀

This pic was taken a few years ago but still makes me smile 😊 Plus you all know I love Christmas so now it’s October I’m allowed to post a Christmas picture right?! 🤣🤣 In all seriousness tho, I love to make people around me smile. We should never underestimate the power of a smile, not just to those we love, but to everyone we come into contact with in our everyday lives. A gesture as simple as smiling at a stranger could make their day. Today I made a lady smile in aldi by letting her go in front of me to pay. She had a toddler who was crying and trying to get out of the trolley and looked totally worn out (I’ve been there🙈) A smile or a random act of kindness takes us just a few minutes, but can honestly brighten someone’s day more than we realise. 
So who will you make smile today? 😀😊😄🙂😃

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and people sitting
firstComment:
Life is so much about perception and wielding energy. When you are “in the moment” it actually expands. “Time stands still.” You have the opportunity to enjoy it immensely. You have the capacity to open up that moment as opposed to drowning in the energy of resentment that you have dragged from the past and the worry you choose to hold from the future. 
I went back to that point this week when I chose anger and frustration as a victim stance in my divorce experience and take that energy back. I let it heal me instead of drain me. The truth is that I am still here. I still exist. I cannot control him or any outcome. I can pay attention to myself. What do I want? To be free, to be present with Ceili and to move on. I give that to myself by clearing the anger, control and frustration. 
I AM free in this moment, being fully present with her and YESSSS, expanding the joy in it.

alt: Image may contain: food
firstComment:
We’re pretty much always in the mood for mangos. They’re loaded with nutrients like vitamin C, copper and carotenoids and can help improve digestion. This Mango Madness smoothie recipe from our very own Health Coach @katrinevanwyk does not disappoint. #NationalWellnessMonth
🥭
1 cup water
1 tbsp coconut manna (a mix of coconut oil and meat) 
1 mango
1 cup greens (romaine, spinach or kale) 
¼ bunch cilantro
4 ice cubes
🥭
Blend everything except ice together in a blender. Let it get nice and smooth. Add in the ice and blend a few more seconds. Drink up!
📸: @realandvibrant

Here’s me super stoked to be working out of my new little office at @hotyogawellington 🥰. It’s still a little bare (but I’ve got the essentials, like plants 🌿 and crystals!). Creating a high-vibe space was top priority!

The BEST thing about this sweet spot is that in between connecting people to amazing yoga & wellness experiences, I also get to practice and teach yoga daily 🙌🏼 -
Three years ago I had a vision for a business that would help spread the power of yoga, so people could live happier and more enriched lives. It’s been a long (and often scary) journey, but moving into my own office definitely feels like a milestone moment 🎉

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, people standing and outdoor
firstComment:
Chaotic, bamboozling, intoxicating, crazy, exasperating, wonderful, squalid, beautiful, daunting and overwhelming. A country that tosses up the unexpected at every turn - India is all these things, and more.
-
Our advice for India first-timers when feeling overwhelmed: mandatory chai stop! This sweet silky tea with a hit of aromatic spices is literally comfort in a cup ☕️
-
Crafted by the street-side chai wallahs, you can find this delicious tea India-wide. From busy urban street corners to hidden alleyways, remote villages to mountain tops. The one constant in India is chai - sure to soothe the soul and calm the senses 🙌🏼
-
📸 @dear_gypsy

firstComment:
✧✧ THE CHILLHOUSE, BALI

8-Night Yoga & Chill Getaway, Tropical Bali from NZD$2399 per person*

Retreat Dates: 13 October - 21 October 2019 
Hit the paradise town of Canggu, Bali, for a chilled-out yoga getaway like no other. Led by Megan and Dave, from @onerenegadeyoga, this retreat promises a fun-filled combination of Rocket Yoga (athletic vinyasa), massages, surfing, healthy eats, and good times.

Retreat inclusions & highlights:
✧ 8 nights at The Chillhouse
✧ Daily breakfast & dinner
✧ Morning Rocket Yoga (athletic vinyasa)
✧ 1:1 posture consultations
✧ Chill Squad” sessions (stretch)
✧ 2 x massages
✧ Handstand and arm balance workshops
✧ 1 x “Get on Board” surf lesson
✧ Sundowner Sessions (beersies and chats by the pool)
✧ Cooking class and Tanah Lot temple tour

Get in quick to book your spot now [link in our bio]. Plus save an additional NZD$200 if booked and paid in full by 1 August 2019.
-
*Prices are per person based on twin-share. Single occupancy packages available. Other T&C’s apply.

alt: Image may contain: sky, ocean, cloud, table, outdoor, nature and water
firstComment:
The ‘Gu’ as it’s affectionately known, is more a state of mind than a place. With its cool alternative undercurrent and surf shack vibe, Bali’s hippest town offers an experience like no other 🧘‍♀️🏄‍♀️
-
Located on Bali’s southern coast, where black sand beaches meet lush green rice fields, this bohemian hideaway is set to inspire. Whole food cafes, yoga studios, artsy shops and hang-out spots line the uncrowded streets.

But it’s the yin-yang union of surf meets yoga, that gives Canggu it’s true irresistible charm. With sunshine, surf and soul, the ‘Gu’ offers a fun, yet relaxed setting to unwind ✌🏼
-
Watch this space: Gu retreat dropping this weekend 👀@onerenegadeyoga 💫

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, people standing and people sitting
firstComment:
Photos are in from our launch shindig (which feels like many moons ago now 🌒🌓🌔). As I look back over the photos from the evening, I'm reminded of all the love and support around me. I'm so thankful for community and for connection.

Over the last month, I've stepped into the Yoga Travel Co. full-time and the feelings of excitement, passion, joy and happiness have been flowing. And at the same time, fear, uncertainty and vulnerability are present too. And you know what, I wouldn't have it any other way.

As Brene Brown said “Vulnerability is the birthplace of love, belonging, joy, courage, empathy, and creativity. If we want greater clarity in our purpose or deeper and more meaningful spiritual lives, vulnerability is the path.”
-
My purpose is clear - to enhance the wellbeing of individuals and communities through the power of yoga. And I'm fully prepared to shed my existing reality and be present in vulnerability so I can achieve this purpose.

Much love to my friends, yoga community, valued yoga and travel partners and our early customers for believing in my vision. The journey has well and truly begun!

B x

P.S. Check out the J O Y that is present for me in each of these photos.

alt: Image may contain: possible text that says 'TRANSFORM WITH ME QUIT THE EXCUSES. MAKE LASTING CHANGES TEST YOURSELF. SET GOALS. ACHIEVE THEM. WHAT'S POSSIBLE. BUST YOUR SLUMP. FIND YOUR GROOVE. You're invited: 21 days of movement & nourishing habits streaming programs nutrition all levels support e accountability my coaching'
firstComment:
I remember a friend, whom I admire, once said, "I'm so sick of people posting about their fitness journeys." That stuck with me because I was on one. So I felt cheesy about sharing it. I still do sometimes, because I've had my own opinions, here and there, about people sharing personal stuff too. Who cares about my life? Most importantly why would I want to make anything like that public? 
Straight up, because I've felt like crap for years, physically, emotionally. My closest friends know all about it. I've decided it's important to share things that have helped me, if I can help others. Also, the process gives me a voice when I don't always feel I have one.

My spiritual core has always pulled me through tough times, thankfully...my fierce love of life. I think our lives are truly a miracle every moment, to be explored, cherished, nourished, and paid forward. 
So the culmination of my passion for learning, trying new things to feel better, & living each day in gratitude for the gifts along the way is to share and inspire living with vitality. 
Sure, I still have some of the same problems, but every moment is full of choices. Do I stay in my same patterns and continue to complain? Or do I shake things up and go outside of my comfort zone to maybe reinvent myself & change the tapes I keep replaying? 
Gratitudes: 
@radiantbalancelife plant-based, feast of vitality @arcatacorepilates & @porchiavollmers for mentorship, rehab, workshops,  long-time support @kayakzaks for my early days of sup-fit guiding @kayaktrinidad for building my skills and opps @arbonne (@hollymillslove ) for a great reset @edognite for introducing me to foundation training. my dad for ♥️ of the body's magic. Surf buddy for frequent frothing. Husband for being there! 
Be well and share your light! Extra perks for first 3 victims (hah!) who want to start on Monday with me. Comment, emoji, DM, or email to chat goals

#idesofmarch #idesofmarch2018 #optimizeyourhealth #optimizeyourhealth #lindenbotanicals #pursuehealth #stopchasingsickness #pursuehealth #marchwellness #medicinaltea #medicinaltea #mindbodysoul #mindbodysouljourney #mindbodysoulspirit #holisticliving #holisticlivingnutrition #holistictea #nourishyourself #justbreathe #wellnessjourney2016 #mindbodyspirit #healthyhappylife

Mama Mavy and sweet man are sick! Not a surprise with this terrible flu season and all of the poor folks out there getting sick. So we are doing our best to remedy the situation and one of my favorite natural cures is bone broth. Normally, I make my own because it’s much more cost efficient. But y’all know when you’re sick and have zero energy, convenience takes the lead!
Our local co-op has this amazing pre made bone broth that you heat in a mug and sip. What’s bone broth y’all may be wondering? And why should you turn to it in your time of need? Let Mama tell you a little secret, it is SO good for you whether you’re sick or not. 
The number one reason to drink it if you’re sick is because it supports a healthy immune system. It is super concentrated in minerals and amino acids, which help to get that immune system working harder and to also assist in bumping up your energy.
It’s also good for your digestive system! The gelatin found in bone broth helps to heal your gut by repairing the intestinal lining and reducing inflammation. 
These are only two of many reasons you should sip on some of this liquid superfood. It’s also great for joint health, combats mental illness, protects your heart, boosts brain health, helps the body detoxify, and helps to keep your skin looking healthy and young (collagen for the win!)
Here’s to hoping all of y’all are staying healthy, or if you’re sick, on your way to recovery. I’m thinking of ya and am along for the ride to feeling better myself.
Xo, Mama Mavy ❤️

firstComment:
I am motivated after a great workout to share this post...I just did 36 minutes of power sculpt from the Core De Force program...It takes a bit of work to get me to sweat, & I am drenched...to think in 36 minutes I got that much a workout out, and I managed to have fun too-bonus!

I am excited for this Thursday, since I'll be 1/2 way through my 1st round of Core De Force, and because my coaching team will be hosting a sneak peek into what coaching is all about...people often ask about what this coachign thing is (and a there's a lot of misconceptions about it)...so this group will be a great chance to share what we do & why we love it.

If I hadn't started coaching a year ago this month, I would not still be as healthy as I am, it's because of the support of a coach, & a challenge group (others on the journey with me) that I am able to stick to my goals. 
So in short I get to:
-drink yummy shakes, that taste like dessert 🍦
-workout with programs that give results💪🏼
-eat food my body loves🍎🍌🍆
-share my journey of wellness (the ups & downs)👍🏽
-encourage others to do the same😍

It sometimes was hard for me to share about my coaching because I was so fearful of what others might think, but then I think about where my health would be in my coach hadn't invited me...so I no longer carry that fear with me, I prefer to carry weights instead... No committment, just information & fun included! Join us this Thursday!
---

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, bicycle, outdoor and nature
firstComment: I've read that getting back into a fitness routine can be compared to riding a bike. Once learned, it can never be forgotten. Well, I decided to take it literally by actually getting back on a bike. So I bought one! 😄 I haven't owned a bike since I was a child. What is most suprising is that my body not only experienced muscle memory (I was able to ride the bike with ease), but my mind has been recalling  loads of happy & adventurous bike rides I had as a child. With each new ride comes a new fantastic memory of my childhood feelings of wonder, freedom, carelessness, enthusiasm, small pleasures, sense of wonder, and curiosity. These rides have helped remind me that those qualities are still in me. My adulthood has sort of compartmentalized those experiences into stuff I don't have time for. However, biking and everything it reminds me of makes me happy. Happiness snuck in a door I did not think was open. This wellness journey I've been on keeps getting better and better 😄 #wellnesswednesday #paulafayfit #bike #bicycle #well #wellness #mentality #positivevibes #wellnessjourney2016 #fitnessjourney2016 #lifeisgood #living #livingwell #healthylifestyle #healthymind #powerofpositivity #positivequotes ##loveyourself #love #outdoors #giantbike #hybridbike #activeliving #fitmom #mommylife #momlife #mood #selfie #adventurebabe

firstComment: Day 21: tday i wanted more food not because i didnt have my share but i just wanted to have a burger 🍔 or sushi 🍣 or a ice cold soda. I had already had dinner of crusty delicious fish 🐟 with a side of fresh mushroom 🍄 bell pepper and onion stir fry in chilli sauce. I did end up having a sweet from diwali leftovers.  I think old habits die hard and th mindless eating is smething whih will be a struggle for me to conquer because it comes back once in a while😋 in the last few days i have learnt the importance of healthy clean eating and being mindful. I dont want to deprive myself; at the same time i want to honor my body... i havent treated it well in last couple of years. After downing the sweet i dnt feel that well... may be bcoz i have stopped the sugar intake for a while now. So i am just going to stop talking and head to bed😴 i think our most healthy version of iurselves are as kids when our parents treat us to the healthiest food and take care to ensure we are just happy 😊. I have more to learn from this kid... only if i can emulate him i wd be much more healthier and happier 😁😎 #diaries #mylife #thisislifestylechannel #wellnessjourney2017 #october #simplicity #lifegoals #happiness #foodie #cleaneating #mumlife #kidstagram

alt: Photo by Krista E. on October 09, 2017.
firstComment:
Day 1 of Keto was pretty good & surprisingly easy! I definitely have a lot to learn, but I feel good about the path I've set myself upon. The cooking & ingredients are going to take some getting used to. Besides breakfast, my meals were:
•Greek yogurt with frozen berries •Chicken Cordon Bleu (my first time ever having it. The hubby LOVED it!) with a side of steamed broccoli with butter
•Snickerdoodle cookies (that I did NOT make correctly, so they didn't turn out that great), with a tiny bit of Cool Whip to help them go down.

Things I learned:
•I need to watch the dairy intake (lactose intolerant)
•Cooking might take a little longer
•Relearning what foods are "good" & "bad" on this diet will be interesting •Staying under 20g of carbs a day is TRICKY!
#keto #ketodiet #wellnessjourney2017 #ketojourney #day1

alt: Photo by Brandi Sigouin in Saskatchewan.
firstComment:
Your "gym" doesn't have to be perfect ⭐️ You don't have to have all the fancy brand name equipment, the big mirrors, the lululemon mats, or the boss sound system.

My gym:
🏋🏻‍♀️A mirror that I have had since I was 15 and is falling apart
🏋🏻‍♀️Colorful weights from Walmart 🏋🏻‍♀️I use a brown squishy bath mat that I've had forever too
🏋🏻‍♀️My computer 💻 sits on the black box of other weights I hope to work up to! 🏋🏻‍♀️A window to help me focus or even use as a distraction. 🌲 🏋🏻‍♀️Printed off program schedules tacked to my wall
🏋🏻‍♀️My Emerald Coach 💚 certificate to keep me focused, motivated, and remind me of my goals! 🏆 💪 🏋🏻‍♀️My washer and dryer in the background to multitask 👍🏻😉 I only need enough space to do lunges and that's about it! 🏃 
Best part about my gym... no fees, payments 💰 or other people's nasty sweat 💦 on everything! 🤢 And I can wear what I want and act how I want! 😝 
You don't need to go out and buy a bunch of stuff to get started ya'll! Just use what you have and make it work 🙂 And I promise you that it will!

alt: Photo by Zenobia on August 13, 2017.
firstComment:
The long short of it is: No. This myth originates in a 1928 study that showed caffeine has a diuretic effect which is science speak for causes you to pee more. 
Logically any consumption of fluid causes you to pee more. Think drinking a litre of water won't fill the tank the same way? It does...but it doesn't mean water is bad for you right?
In 2005 a new study tested 59 men over the course of 11 days by dividing them into a groups one with caffeine supplements and the other with a placebo. They checked 20 biological markers including loss of electrolytes and fluid (pee) output to see if this 1928 yarn had any real string to it. The final conclusions showed there wasn't much difference between both groups... so have your morning coffee before you workout or hit the road. I know I will. 
Lots of love
Your friendly fit chef.

I hadn't been walking for weeks. July's activities kept me eating, sleeping, and running the road. Plus, I hadn't heard "Go walking" in my spirit. Well today, as soon as I opened my eyes, I heard, "Going walking. I have something to tell you." It turned out the words He had for me were actually there be shared with other people. I was able to enjoy my walk and offer words of comfort and encouragement that others. God is awesome!

Today's lesson: always be obedient to His promptings. Your blessing will always come, even if it is blessing others with your presence or words......

#backatit
#obediencebringsblessings

alt: Photo by Rita Beynon on May 27, 2017.
firstComment:
Last week I spent time in this place, my original stomping grounds, Philly!!! I did NOT tell anyone I was coming. See after 3 years it was time for me to go to my childhood home and see my Step father, a term I dislike as he chose to help raise me. 
My moms house has not changed one single bit....you'd think that could be refreshing but it was eerily 😭. My step father has done ✅ nothing in 3 years. I spent a few days bagging and donating or trashing my moms belongings. It was surreal. Handing the bags off to a woman's shelter made me know my mom is thankful BUT made me feel emotions I can not even begin to explain. 
3 years is a long time to hold onto anything. Emotions will eat you up on the inside and tear you down without you even realizing it. Grief is inexplainable. Grief fucking sucks. It hits you without any warning at anytime in anyplace. Honestly I haven't even realized most of the time that it was grief. I've had excuses. I've ignored my ❤️, my soul, my mind, my body! 
Coming home my daughters seemed crazier then ever. Maybe it's the time of year, or maybe it's them feeding off my grief. I have felt angrier then ever. I have felt sadder then ever. It has taken 3 years, but I think I've found the rock at the bottom and I know that for the sake of my family, my ❤️, my soul, my body, I need to start swimming back up to the top. Maybe then can I go home, back to Philly, and be able to have a drink with friends and just love the place and people that raised me up with my mom to be Awesome! Philly I ❤️ U! (Not enough to event move there though😜)

firstComment:
Our Aurora Winter Wellness Challenge is now open for registration! 
Make 2017 your year by joining in on this wellness journey and build a regular practice. Don't let the stories we tell ourselves be the excuse to stay off the mat, let these be your reasons to get on your mat this year! We have a variety classes from beginners, meditation, candlelit yin to Vinyasa flow with a range of times. 
You have two price options to choose from- an unlimited pass giving you the flexibilty to choose your week from morning, daytime and evening classes or our Noon hour option- Sneak into our Flex Yoga Classes starting January. These classes will allow you to hit your mat for 20-30-45-90 minutes! Encouraging you to #getonyourmat even if its only for 20 minutes 3 times a week. Worry less about running 5 minutes late, or having a meeting right after lunch and sneak us into your schedule. 
There will be a "We did it!!!" Completion Package and Party for everyone who gets on their mat at least 3x a week for the duration of the 12 weeks as well as a Grand Prize for the person who does the most classes.

alt: Photo by 👑Regina on November 18, 2015.
firstComment:
Nope..I was not always into health & fitness..In fact I failed gym in high school😞 lol
It was not until I was mandated to summer school where I fell in love with that weight room.. I had never seen it before but I will tell you I was one fearful, anxiety ridden, confused girl. 
I was on a downward spiral to NOWHERE! 
Any dream or vision for my future was stolen from me by some noise in my head.
So to drown out that negativity (my choice at the time) and fear I did like i "thought" everyone else did which was "anything" that took me out of my own head.
I don't need to go further than that. It was not pretty trust me.

I fought through decades of battling my own mind.
I always had a very strong faith but my connection was disconnected because of my desire to fulfill a hole in my soul with any ol crap. 
Many years later always knowing I had a burning passion to live healthy and fit I sought out God with all my heart and starting down a path and journey that was beyond my wildest dreams! I changed all my habits, worked out regularly and ate only what fed my body the way it needed to be fed because food contributes greatly to how we think & act.

Not that the torture & life's tribulations ended there, no I wish I could tell you differently but after tragic events and failed marriages "circumstances out of my control" I clung tightly,stayed focused and true to God, myself and my children.
I dove deeper into fitness which helped greatly with anxiety & depression.

My passion is to help others live a heathy lifestyle;pass my love for the health & fitness industry on to anyone seeking change one day at a time! Challenges are forever..take care of your body, mind and soul!
Connect with me I would love to help you😊 #letsgetfittogether #igmotivationwednesday #wellnessjourney2015 #cleaneatingchallenge #believeinyou #strongmoms #familyfirst #JesusStrong #knowyourworth #eatforhealth #nostresszone #faithandfitness #foodmatters #foodporn #proteinshakes #superfood #fitnesscoach #grouptraining #coachwithme #peanutbutter

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and people standing
firstComment:
PROGRESS  OVER  PERFECTION 📈
Okay, so not entirely fair to do a side by side of how pregnant I was the week before LuLu was born compared to today but it felt really fitting for how I’m feeling!
.
In the photo on the left, I was so excited when I bought this pink dress but when it came down to wearing it in front of a camera while forcing myself to smile, I cringe at the thought now. I was so uncomfortable, self-conscious, and just wanted to cover up, eeek!
.
Obviously I went through with it for the beautiful memory with my first baby before his little sister arrived. In other ways, I’m really happy I took this picture because I reflect and really see how far I’ve come!
.
What would I tell my past self? I would say,
“Hey, within the next 10 months, you’ll choose to become the best version of yourself for you and your kids”
“You’ll put some house chores on hold for less than an hour so you can squeeze in your daily workouts”
“You’ll also find ways to make clean eating easy for the whole family and inexpensive”
“Most importantly, the love for yourself will be unmeasurable”
.
I’m a day closer to my goals and I ain’t turning back!
.
.
Why not you? 💗

alt: Image may contain: people smiling, one or more people and child
firstComment:
My “WHY” + Big Bird 
I’ve always known I wanted to be a mom. Specifically, one boy and one girl before I turned 30. You would think these two babes were planned but I often call them my happy little accidents.
.
Though it’s challenging most days where I feel “touched” out by night’s end and feel like I’m one itty bitty nerve away from losing it- I wouldn’t change it for the world.
.
.
There are seasons of HUSTLE and seasons of REST. Right now, I’m in a season of hustle just so these little minions will always be in mine or Michael’s care. Coaching will be what gets me there!!

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and indoor
firstComment:
Before pictures for the next transformation of my life! I used to hate taking these. Not that I necessarily enjoy or love taking them now.
.
Same girl 👧🏻
The mean girl thoughts crowd my mind that I’m not good enough. Not good enough to even share my journey. Would anyone even care? Watch? Listen?
.
Same woman 👩🏻
The woman in me knows I can I do it. The woman in me knows I’m fully CAPABLE of what successful women have accomplished (+ failing forward) and that it’s all a learning process.
.
Same mama 🤱🏻
The mama in me knows that if I can carry children inside my body TWICE to full term, work to the very last day before maternity leave, and have shown up for ME first these last 152 days, I know I can commit to the next 100 days!!
.
Day one starts this Monday!! So excited for the structure and routine. It gives me so much life and sanity 💯 Why not you?!

alt: Image may contain: one or more people, selfie and closeup
firstComment:
Meet my workout buddy! 👩‍👦
After I get his sister down for her morning nap, I chase him around and/or have an epic dance party to give him some one on one time. Mainly because at the 30 minute mark of my workout, he gets restless i.e. puts toys at my feet, sings loud, or helps by “spotting” me while lifting weights.
.
I wouldn’t have it any other way❗️
.
Lino will be 3 in October and stands 3 feet tall. He has the sweetest heart and loves to learn about everything! I am beyond grateful that the time I choose for me is at home because time is too precious and yeah, babes will be your babes forever but they will only be little for so long. 💗

alt: Image may contain: one or more people and closeup
firstComment:
Lately I’ve been in my head about EVERYTHING. And I’ll be fully honest with you! I’ve been eating with my FEELINGS.
.
The control freak, mean girl self sometimes can’t handle any reality and it’s EASY to eat all the things in sight. I really have no self control when it comes to anything crunchy and savory!! 🥨
.
The things in my head have just been about telling me I’m INADEQUATE and feeling like I have to do everything at once because if not me, who and when will it all get done? Then I go down this spiral of, are people even noticing my efforts? When was the last time I was THANKED?I get overwhelmed and I think of SNACKS and eat, eat, and EAT. You with me? 🍔
.
.
Being an online coach is teaching me a lot about myself. It’s also teaching me that it’s not always about ME either.
🌟 Heck yeah it has taught me to be the most accountable I could ever be.
🌟 Heck yeah it has taught me what a balanced, portion control based diet should be.
🌟 And Heck Fricken yah, it has helped me get rid of 30lbs but it has also helped me be honest with myself. It’s a work in progress!!!
.
.
If this vibed with you at all, shoot me a DM or comment a 💗 below! And let’s please chat if you’re struggling too! 😘

There came a day when I simply had had enough. I had been overweight for about 10 years, had high blood pressure, was disabled at times with fibromyalgia, was diagnosed with Crohns and the meds were not working.  Add to that the fact that I constantly thought about being overweight and was a tad consumed by it...I truly didn't see myself as a heavy person but the picture and scale simply didn't lie.  I had done Arbonne's 30 days to Healthy living a few times and ALWAYS felt great while doing it and then slipped back into old habits. When I received an ultimatum with regards to my Crohns a friend/nutritionist recommended I do the program that  I literally coached but just do it longer...she was right!  Everyone thinks they will lose weight and get healthy but in fact it it is the opposite.  I need to get my gut reset, get healthy and then the weight came off. It took me about 5-6 months but along with 45 pounds I also lost my aches and pains, fatigue, inflammation, stomach issues, mood swings, stress and more.  We determined that my fibromyalgia and Crohns were both triggered by FOOD CHOICES and i remain symptom free. My blood pressure returned to normal and I have maintained a healthy weight with this new lifestyle. I found that dairy, sugar and wheat are not the best for me and my response is always...there are worse things than having to eat healthy to get healthy.  I've tried other paths...they didn't work.  I’m telling you... you want to join us in this next 30 days to Healthy Living group!!!

I started Arbonne’s 30 day detox plan to clean up my diet in the summer of 2017. Each month I continued to avoid gluten, dairy, refined sugar, processed foods, and replaced daily meals with protein shakes/whole foods and sodas with fizz sticks! 18 months later and I’m down 87 pounds and 8 pants sizes! (Size 22w to size 6). I FEEL amazing! People ask me, don’t you miss cheese and bread?? I don’t! Because what I’ve traded those things for are energy, health, and life! I’m a better mom to my 3 boys because I have so much energy to run around and play with them! I actually want to workout now because I feel so good. I actually feel better than when I was a teenager, and am currently training for a half marathon! The weight and pain are no longer holding me back from living my life! I didn’t know how bad I felt before, until I realized how good I could feel today! The potential of this program is amazing! Jump in and join us! You won’t regret it! 
And I said to my body, "I want to be your friend." It took a long breath and replied, "I have been waiting my whole life for this." -anonymous”

My journey with Arbonne began in April 2017. Two years prior, I had been diagnosed with breast cancer.  I ended up going through lumpectomy and had 36 rounds of radiation.  On top of that, I also suffered from reflux, IBS, headaches, and joint pain. My energy was at zero, and I basically felt awful all the time because of all the inflammation in my body.  I thought I was eating a healthy diet, but I was so wrong! 
The extreme fatigue led to a sedentary lifestyle which led to weight gain, low self-esteem, and even depression.  I was a mess.  I couldn’t walk up a flight of stairs without pain, I was going to bed at 7:30pm but never could get enough rest.  I developed high blood pressure.  My stomach issues got so bad I went to the doctor who ended up removing my gall bladder.  I was given medications and sent on my way.  But nothing changed.  I was still suffering with constant nausea, pain, and fatigue. 
If it hadn't been for my sweet daughter, a nurse practitioner, and her encouraging me to try the Arbonne30, I would still be in that awful state I was in. Surround yourself with people who are better at the things you want to be good at! Allow them to look you in the eye, ask you why you did less than you could, and call out your excuses. No matter what position, cert or skill you have, there is ALWAYS someone better than you. Let go of your insecurity and spend time with them! Get comfortable being uncomfortable. The more time you spend with people like this, the more you will grow and develop the skills they have. I recognize things easier in areas I have more experience in. However, being a novice requires uncovering those subconscious barriers holding you back from growth.

alt: Photo by Lindsay Sargent on September 07, 2018.
firstComment:
In case you guys didn't notice, gut health is extremely important to me. In 2013, after a rough major appendectomy surgery, I was diagnosed with IBS. It was a losing battle, everything made me sick, and my quality of life was miserable. Fast forward a few years, taking FIVE pills daily (two of those pills were to counter the side effects of the other pills!) And throwing Chronic Fatigue Syndrome on top of it - I was miserable and constantly in pain. Que Arbonne! @eamaloy introduced me, and within a week of detoxing (not dieting) my symptoms were greatly diminished, and eventually non existent. So here's what i learned that has CHANGED MY LIFE:
· Lactose is the sugar found in dairy. Our bodies aren't designed to process that after infancy. · Dairy is a know inflammatory substance that can also lead to bloating, digestive discomfort and pain.
· It can elevate blood sugar levels!
· Dr Joe Gata wrote, "Irritable bowel syndrome is a painful abdominal condition characterized by changes in the patterns of bowel movements... Many patients with IBS report feeling less pain and discomfort when they stop consuming food with dairy."
· Milk is on the high pesticide list! · A study found that casein, aka milk protein, has been linked to multiple forms of cancer.
· Dairy can cause muscle and joint pain (including in those who don't suffer from IBS)
· Dairy can cause skin conditions like eczema and acne.
· Dairy is an acid - that means when you consume it, it lowers your pH (alkaline) levels. 
Whew. There's a ton of info out there, and that's all im dishing out today. A promise for happier health news is coming in future days! Thank you for reading and helping me spread awareness! 
#dairyfree #saynototoxins #IBS #inflammation #wellnessjourneyfor30 #autoimmunedisease #prevention #arbonne #lifestyle

alt: Photo by Lindsay Sargent on September 06, 2018.
firstComment:
Coffeeology: The Good, the Bad, and the Added Chemicals
This info hit me right where it hurts. I love coffee. I can eat sleep and breathe coffee. But coffee doesn't love me back. I know every coffee lover did a little dance when studies showed health benefits and longevity for coffee drinkers, BUT that allowed us to overlook the catch 22 of coffee. · Coffee is 5 on the pH scale - not that bad (our bodies should straddle a 7 to maintain the balance between alkaline and acidic) but Coffee causes your body to  gastric acid which ups the acid content of your digestive track. · Cold Brew (the most popluar form at the moment) is actually more acidic than other brewing methods. · Here's where it hurts - there are more than 1000 chemicals in a single cup of coffee. Only 26 of those have been tested and of those HALF of those caused cancer in lab rats 😭😱 · Coffee is one of the most sprayed (pesticides) crop. "Normally coffee grows on bushes in naturally shaded areas. But to increase production, most large coffee makers cut down large swaths of rain forest and douse the beans with chemicals to grow them more quickly." · Organically grown coffee is on the rise, but you still have to be careful about where you're getting your coffee from. I'm currently researching Logevity Coffee on their authenticity. If anyone uses their stuff, i'd love to hear your thoughts! 
#wellnessjourneyfor30 #loveyourgut #guthealth #coffeemugobsession #coffee #longevitycoffee #healthyisthenewhappy

Surround yourself with people who are better at the things you want to be good at! Allow them to look you in the eye, ask you why you did less than you could, and call out your excuses. Did you know that due to factors like soil depletion, the vitamin and nutrient content of our fruits and vegetables has significantly diminished over the years? 
One study showed that you would have to eat over eight oranges to get the same amount of Vitamin C as our grandparents did with ONE! 
Another fun fact! One cup of red bell pepper has 190 mg of Vitamin C whereas an orange only had 67 mg. 
Our entire body thrives off of nutrients we feed it. The Greens Balance offers an easy way to consume a proprietary blend of green, yellow, red, and blue whole foods that help balance phytonutrients (used to help fight disease and illness) in our body.

firstComment:
Detox Day 4 ••• HERE’S A TIP! ••• Joint pain, acne/skin probs, depression...this one might be for you! ☺️ Y’all know I’ve been battling joint pain and for the next 30 days, I’m ridding my body of inflammation by eating clean and supporting my immune system (aka focusing on Gut Health). If you didn’t know, a big portion of your immune system is in your gut, so if you want to get well or stay well, start here. 
SO LET’s talk about TURMERIC! The best part about turmeric? Not only is it well-researched, incredibly potent and historically significant, it’s also safe. Turmeric has very few known side effects, and the ones that exist are incredibly rare and generally mild. Imagine saying that about most medications!

Turmeric is one of the most widely mentioned medicinal herbs in all of science (basically the Mac Daddy) and here are some benefits: ✅ It’s a potent ANTI-INFLAMMATORY 💪🏻 Turmeric fights inflammation, which is the ROOT of many diseases. Increasingly common diseases today — such as cancer, ulcerative colitis, arthritis, high cholesterol and chronic pain — are all associated with inflammation. •
•
✅ In some studies it was especially effective in reducing DEPRESSION. These results seem to be connected to the way curcumin impacts neurotransmitter function through the brain-derived neurotrophic factor. •
•
✅ IMPROVED SKIN HEALTH! Think HEALTHY GLOW! Turmeric benefits include anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties that have proven effective — benefits for skin include increasing “glow and luster” of the skin, speeding up wound healing, calming the pores to decrease and acne scarring and controlling flares.
•
•
HAPPY THURSDAY, Y’ALL!

alt: Image may contain: 2 people
firstComment:
I just found this picture from January 30th, 2015. Ryker was born August 1st, 2014 and I was a busy mom of two (no big deal) juggling many hats. Looking back I remember not feeling my best. Just two weeks later on my 27th birthday I got a phone call from my doctor- she said I had #HashimotosDisease. It’s an #autoimmunedisease in which your thyroid attacks itself and the treatment is synthroid for the rest of your life. Well, I just wasn’t ready for that so I did a 180° change in my diet and have been managing it since with those changes. BUT NOW, I’m struggling with something called #adrenalfatigue Turns out, chronic stress (among other things) taxes your adrenal glands and leads to low energy and a variety of other fun things like acne when you’re 30 😒🙄 The reason I shared this picture, is because from another’s perspective I was fine. #health is really about how you feel on the inside. It’s not just numbers on a scale or average lab results. Today is day 1 of my #wellnessjourneyfor30 !  I’m believing that these lifestyle changes and some prayer will help me fight back and soon I’ll feel 💯! Autoimmune disease is on the rise but the good news is, you have some control. The only thing you really can control is you, so why not make the best of it! 
#healthylife #detox #cleaneating #goals #vision #healthyeating #healthyfood #fightforhealth #healthychoices #glutenfree #eattherainbow #plantbased #dairyfree #againstallgrain

alt: Image may contain: 8 people
firstComment: ***Vulnerable post alert with a low-level rant thrown in.*** There’s a reason that my social media profile picture isn’t myself in the early 90s, with a perm. (Oh wait... look what I just found in my mom’s photos!  Thanks Mom, and you’re welcome, Cuzins! 😜🤪🙄😂). Because like all of us, I (usually) put my best foot forward on social, but on the eve of joining hundreds of people across the world for a #30daystohealthyliving journey together, I thought I’d pull back the profile pic off for a moment and share why I’m so fired up and thankful for healthy living. Yes, I like to keep trim and fit, but it’s more than that.  Our family has a history of autoimmune disease, which is one of the FASTEST GROWING diagnoses in our country right now, and I deal with one myself (even though in my own mind I’m waayyyy too young 🤯🤔). It’s Hashimoto’s, and it’s an autoimmune disease of the thyroid.  The most common medication is Synthroid (incidentally, one of the top prescriptions in the United States), but the issue for me is this... Synthroid replaces what you’re not getting from your thryoid. lt doesn’t deal with the PROBLEM, and if the AUTOIMMUNE problem isn’t solved, it tends to pop up over and over, in multiple diagnoses.  What lots of folks don’t realize, though, is that there is this whole world of nutritional healing/integrative medicine where the goal is to find the PROBLEM and HEAL it.  That’s what I wanted. That’s what I need, and THAT is why I had to find a way to make healthy living 🍊🥝🥦🥑 a lifestlye that I could love. 💚💚💚 So I’ll be focusing on my health the next 30 days, giving you some great ideas I’ve found along the way, laughing at myself, having fun, and loving life.  Because hey.... that’s what this thing is all about right?  #wellnessjourneyfor30 #healthy #health #detox #thyroid #hashimotos #healthyliving #healthyeating #sharethelove #pure #safe #beneficial

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

firstComment: Fresh guava bliss balls. Take a cup full of guava fruit  and blitz in the food processor. As in a cup of almonds , 1 tbsp cacao powder  and 2 tbsp chia seeds. Blitz until formed into a ball. Roll and refrigerate. No sugar required. You can add coat with melted coconut oil and cacao to give a chocolate coating. Healthy alternative to chocolate eater eggs. I'm going to try with the feijoa which are the green grenades in the bowl. This was this mornings harvest.  #betterliving #wellness #wellnesscoach #blissballs #lifeisbliss #lifecoachjourney #happyhealthyeaster #yleo #healthymondandbody #easter #happyeaster🌻#easterbunny #wellnessjourneycentre

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, outdoor
firstComment:
I honestly can’t go a day without wanting to feel like Superwoman 💥
The powder inside this packet has everything my body needs to get fueled and ready for whatever I make of the day.  It literally has helped me create a life that I’m excited for!! 💕We all need some kind of tool or vehicle to get us where we want to go.  Ketones are my catalyst!!! Ketones have made me smile again 😊🙏 For all my new followers.  Here’s how I began my personal wellness journey.  It was almost a year ago that I made the decision to start living. I didn’t want to be dead while I was still alive.  After having my 3rd child, my health started to deteriorate both physically and mentally.  I wanted to sleep all the time.  I was in pain from fibroids and other hormonal issues.  I gained weight. Anxiety was high.  I slowly closed myself off from family and friends.  It was easier to suffer in silence.  I  wasn’t being a good mom/wife/friend/daughter/sister!!! I was tired, grumpy, irritable, bitter, sad and broken.  Sometimes all the shit that gets dumped on you gets heavy and it’s hard to get out!! 💩

On paper, I shouldn’t have been struggling with eating well and being healthy (2 university degrees in science and food/nutrition)!!! But life happened 🤷‍♀️ Fast forward to today and my journey to find health and wellness has inspired me to help others.  I know there are many women like myself who put their needs last and only when they become broken down machines do they get help for themselves.  Been there! I know!! It’s  easier for us to go without or struggle than for our kids. 
Nothing comes easy!! Yes, my ketones are magical and make me happy.  But you need to work at wanting better everyday. 
I don’t know what’s headed down the path I’m on right now, but I’m enjoying the journey!  Don’t stand by and let your life slip away!
Be the advocate for your own health! 
You too, can be BETTER everyday.
Let me show you how!!😎 #makethemostofeveryday #justpruviteveryday #changecomesfromaction #wellnessjourney💚 #ketoishmom #healthymommeanshealthykids #askanisha #momfueledbyketones #selfcareisnotselfishness

I think it would be so cute to put a bunch of items together to make a breakfast pack! You could put them in a fun metal tub, fabric bin, or rope basket. ⁣

They even have a Gluten Free Pancake and Waffle mix available! If you want to add a little extra you could find cute spatulas, dish towels, or a fun pancake flipper to add to your basket.⁣
⁣
If you’re not familiar with Einkorn, let me tell you a little about it.  Einkorn is the original “staff of life” and is one of the OLDEST varieties of wheat known to man. It has a primitive genetic code of 14 chromosomes - compared to modern hybridized wheat which has 42 chromosomes!! Einkorn is SO MUCH more compatible with the human body. Many people with gluten sensitivity can tolerate Einkorn.⁣
⁣

alt: Photo by Luna Essential Oils 🌱 dōTERRA on May 10, 2018.
firstComment:
Why use a foot mask? 👣 Since our feet have the most pores per square inch than any other area of the body, it is important to remember to treat the feet too! What you put on the feet will absorb into the rest of the body, so do your best to gather high quality, organic ingredients for this foot mask.

Ingredients:
½ cup organic Greek yogurt
2 tablespoons organic raw honey
2 splashes doTERRA Fractionated Coconut Oil
1 stalk organic celery
6 drops Bergamot #doterra #essentialoil 
Notes:
🌱 The probiotics in Greek yogurt help deliver beneficial proteins and the lactic acid it contains rids the surface of old cells, making way for radiant, fresh skin.
🌱 Celery is rich in zinc, which helps to repair dry, cracked skin. Celery also carries vitamins and is cleansing and detoxifying.
🌱 Raw honey 🐝 is a natural humectant, contains beneficial enzymes and antioxidants, and has antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties.
🌱 Bergamot essential oil is calming and soothing to the skin.
Instructions:
🌿 Grate stalk of celery and drain excess moisture in strainer or with paper towel.
🌿 Add celery and remaining ingredients to food processor or blender. Blend until smooth.
🌿 Ready a wet washcloth or sit by tub.
🌿 Apply mask immediately to entire foot with fingers or brush. Let sit 15–20 minutes while enjoying mask’s cooling sensation ❄️ and the calming effects of Bergamot essential oil.
🌿 Rinse off and enjoy your nourished and moisturized feet 😊
