alt: Photo by chelsey ☽ health + wellness in Toronto C•A•N•A•D•A with @amybunnage, @mindfulmagazine, @wholisticallyhannah_, @mindfullymae, @livingwellwithanna, @healwithkailin, @livelife_ontheveg, @_mindfullyfresh, and @wellnessbyliv. Image may contain: one or more people, phone, selfie, closeup and indoor
firstComment:
STOP✨ .
.
Stop what you are doing right now and take a deep breath. Fill your belly up with air, hold it ... and let it go. How did it feel? Like you haven’t taken a breath like that all day? Yeah .. me too. .
.
That my friends, is called mindful breathing. Being aware of your breath and how much better you feel afterwards. It reminds us that we ignore ourselves, we ignore our habitual patterns because we are too focused on the busy simulation in front of our eyes. Take a breath. Listen to your body. Let go of worry. Understand that your time will come. Everything happens for a reason. You have so much time to get your goals done. Worry about yourself first
.
.

𝔾𝕚𝕧𝕖 𝕐𝕠𝕦𝕣𝕤𝕖𝕝𝕗 𝕋𝕚𝕞𝕖 🦋
.
.
#mindfulnesspractice #mindfulbreathing #positiveselftalk #nurtureyourself

alt: Photo by chelsey ☽ health + wellness in Waterloo, Ontario. Image may contain: one or more people, phone, shorts and indoor
firstComment:
Hello beautiful souls💜 .
.
The winter can be tough. Especially when your stuck inside all day, the sun doesn’t come out as much and comfort food is extremely tempting. We all go through this. Your not alone. I’ve learned some things that can be helpful to get out of the cloudy, lazy, depressive state we can often find ourselves slipping into. Very simple things that can be done daily to make sure you give yourself love and treat yourself with respect. Here’s a list of things you can do TODAY to make sure you still have a successful day (even if you do just one) 🌻 remember: your soul purpose is to simply exist. It’s okay if a day is spent in bed. It’s okay to just exist💭 your in control of how you live your life .
.
↠ make your bed
↠ open the curtains
↠ wash your face/brush your teeth
↠ drink a glass of water
. ↠ meditate for 10minutes
↠ step outside the door and take 10 deep breaths .
↠ take a bath
↠ eat frozen grapes or blueberries and watch Netflix with a bottle of water .
↠ if your feeling up to it, do a workout
↠ make a smoothie .
↠ write in your journal
.
.
These are just a few of many things you can do to help yourself defeat winter depression and anxiety or just all year round depression and anxiety🌞 I personally struggle with bad anxiety daily and I find that just doing any of these things to make your day feel the slightest bit productive really makes a difference💜 .
.
What do you like to do to make your day productive?🥰 .
.
#anxietyhealing #winterdepression #selfcaresunday #selfcareideas #mentalillnesssupport #overcomedepressionandanxiety

alt: Photo by Ashleigh on June 02, 2019. Image may contain: one or more people, drink and indoor
firstComment:
🚨weight loss update!
_____
About 9 weeks ago I shared that I was participating in “The Biggest Loser” at work. I initially shared some losses but forgot to continue the updates. It’s been over for a week and in total I’m -1️⃣0️⃣.8️⃣lbs. (with a couple small gains mixed in). I didn’t do as well as I had planned but that’s on me. I’m still super excited about the loss, especially being down another 1lb. this week since the competition has ended!💪🏻
_____
Weight loss is a funny thing. If you strictly focusing on changing your nutrition & eating habits, tracking weight loss will show your progress, but with exercise & weight training the scale will not capture what’s happening with your body! I’m learning this and finding different ways to measure my progress:
- In some cases I have clothes fitting better👗
- Taking measurements📏
- Before & after pictures📸
Although I still check the scale and like to see the number going down, I know that it’s not the full picture and I’m working on being okay with that!
_____
What is your go-to way to track your weight loss progress?
_____

alt: Photo shared by Ashleigh on January 26, 2019 tagging @the_whimsical_teacher, @teacherspayteachers, @miss5th, @teachersforteachers, @givethatgirlasnack, @abbydosen, and @teach.sweat.repeat. Image may contain: 1 person, drink and indoor
firstComment:
🍎Let’s talk teacher life for a second
.
we’ve heard it all before:
•teachers make plenty of money (stop complaining)
•teachers get summers off
•teachers have the easiest hours
•teachers have it so easy, they hang out with kids all day
•teachers just give a test and hang out
•etc.
.
It’s so easy for anyone who doesn’t know reality about teaching to judge and think they know what teachers do (because they were a student at one time🙄). But let’s talk reality.
.
I took this picture at 7:30 this morning☕️ (that’s right - Saturday morning). I was at work to teach a writing academy. Sure - I’m getting paid extra for this, but let’s talk about why I couldn’t say no to the opportunity:
•teachers spend their own $$$ on materials and supplies (my school in particular limits us to one case of paper per teacher, per term)
•teachers are paid significantly below the average for the level of degree we hold
•teachers (at least myself and MOST that I know) have insane student loans to pay off
•teachers often need to work 2 and sometimes three jobs to live and pay bills
•teachers don’t get paid for all of the work they do OUTSIDE school hours like staying late, grading papers, responding to parents, lesson planning, etc.
.
So yes, like ALL jobs there are benefits, I am not complaining about being a teacher or about the job, simply sharing a little reality into what it’s really like. It can be such a rewarding job and such an thankless job at the same time, please remember that it’s not just arts & crafts and field trips.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

alt: Photo shared by Ashleigh on January 12, 2019 tagging @nike, and @oldnavy. Image may contain: drink
firstComment:
🍓
.
Later this afternoon my husband and I are going out to eat with his parents for a little celebration. 🎉
.
I’m hungry now but I know I’ll probably have some unhealthy options when we go out, so I decided on one of my favorite superfood shakes.🌱🍓
.
Today I decided on:
•frozen strawberries
•frozen raspberries
•handful of spinach
•almond milk
•strawberry flavored superfoods.
.
This is a yummy and healthy way to keep me full for the meantime & not feel guilty about eating crap (like I would have done 5 months ago).
.
Life is all about balance, and while I’m going to let myself indulge later, it doesn’t need to be a full day “wasted” because I’ll “do better tomorrow”. I am staying on track today, while allowing myself to LIVE, and ENJOY, and not feel like I should deprive myself.
.
That’s what it’s all about right?
.

.
What a year it’s been. It hasn’t even been a full year since I’ve started my blog, and even less then since starting this Instagram.
.
With it has brought inclusion into such an amazing, supportive & rewarding community.💗
.
Whether it be the weight loss🍕 & wellness community🧘🏻‍♀️, other teachers🍎, brides to be 👰🏻and newlyweds, lifestyle curators📸, etc. I’ve felt so much personal growth over the past year.
.
💍Of course getting married this year was my biggest and most rewarding accomplishment.
.
It hasn’t been the most perfect year, especially these last few months, but it has been a pivotal one. This has been a year of learning, success, and change for the better.
.
I was so proud to see these photos as my “top 9” of 2018 because it really reflects a well/rounded version of what I share - after all being human there are so many sides of us & sharing that on social media is so important when it comes to being authentic.
.
Thanks to everyone for supporting me, encouraging me to be myself & liking my photos.😉
.
Here’s to 2019 and more 🥞food, 💍ring, 🏃🏻‍♀️weight loss, 🏋🏻‍♀️workout, 🗒planning, 🍎teaching, ☕️coffee & real life 📸photos!
.

alt: Photo by Ashleigh on December 17, 2018. Image may contain: food
firstComment:
⚠️real life coming up⬇️
.
.
.
Monday. The week before Christmas. Teacher tired is REAL.
.
I spent the day at work, worked the after school program, got home at 6, changed clothes, ran errands, went grocery shopping & got home all at 8:30.
.
🍕What does that have to do with pizza? Getting home at 8:30 on a Monday (when I’ve usually fallen asleep on the couch by now) called for a frozen pizza in the oven while I unpacked groceries and made lunch for tomorrow.
.
Now it’s 9:10, I’m sitting down, finally eating dinner. I didn’t get a workout in today - which I’m disappointed in. Not eating the healthiest dinner, also disappointing, and I try my best to avoid eating dinner this late, fail. But today I’ve drank a ton of water, stayed on track all day, prepped a healthy lunch for tomorrow, & took care of things I NEEDED to get done. This was good for my mental health. This has set up my week feeling optimistic. I feel like although I didn’t hit all of my goals for the day, I had a productive day & I’m set up to have another one tomorrow, and that is a win.
.
Life, and in particular - weight loss & health journeys aren’t always pretty. They sure as hell aren’t easy & they’re not always fun, but they’re important. It’s important to recognize that you’re not going to be “ON” every day and THAT’S OKAY! I’m here to show you that I’m DEFINITELY not perfect, but I’m definitely not quitting either.
.
.
.
.
.

.
Do you know someone who might enjoy Beachbody?
.
Do you know someone who might want to give Beachbody a try?
.
Do you know someone who might want more info on Beachbody? .

.

.

.

.
.

alt: Photo by Ashleigh on December 09, 2018.
firstComment:
Goals.
.
.
I’m the type of person that needs small, attainable goals in order to see progress (maybe that’s just the special ed teacher in me🤷🏻‍♀️).
.
.
Making goals for the week gives me something I can look back on, work towards and improve on. Setting small goals that are meant to have larger more meaningful outcomes is the way to be successful at something & see real results.
.
.
💪🏻My workout goal is to allow me to stay on track/pace with my current exercise program.
.
.
💦My water goal is to increase my intake in order to increase it next week to 95+ oz. per day.
.
.
⏰My wake up goal is likely my hardest. I can sometimes get myself up to work out before work - but it’s hard and I’m very inconsistent. If I can get into the routine of waking up and not hitting snooze then I can work towards getting up a little earlier in order to work out in the AM.
.
.
What is one goal you want to work towards this week?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

firstComment:
I remember looking forward to the end of the workday because I knew I could go home and rest. You see, around 2:30 pm/3:00 pm I was ready for a nap, right there on my desk. 😴
Often that feeling lingered after the workday ended and I’d be too tired to do the things I loved to do. AND who wants to figure out what to eat when you’re tired, so I’d just run through a Drive-Thru.
🍔
If there was ever a choice between eating or going to sleep, sleep would win every. time.  What about you? 🚴🏽‍♀️
Are you ready to increase your energy and end that afternoon slump? 🕝
I have the solution for you. ✨
Join my FREE Challenge, 5 Days to Increase Your Energy & End That Afternoon Slump!  This is were I began my wellness journey and ended that afternoon slump!  Check out the details and sign up at bit.ly/MoreEnergyChallenge (link in bio).

A life of energy.  A life of promise.  A life of hope.  I can never thank that Marine's family enough for thinking of someone else as they were grieving the loss of their loved one. alt: Photo by Sharon Barnes on June 03, 2018.
firstComment:
What’s your ultimate refreshment? 🍹
There’s nothing quite like a cool drink on a hot day like this, so I’m indulging in my all time favorite beverage. A super thick, ice cold, mixed fruit smoothie!
. 
It’s my favorite. Not only is it refreshing, delicious, filling, and causes the occasional brain-freeze, it’s good for me, too! It contains:
• Unsweetened Vanilla Almond Milk - which boosts energy without spiking your blood sugar, reduces blood pressure, improves kidney health, and strengthens your bones, just to name a few benefits. • Baby Spinach -  it’s low in calories but high in fiber to help you feel full, high in iron to carry oxygen from the lungs to every cell in your body, just to name a few benefits. • Avocado - not only does it make my smoothie creamy it’s also a healthy fat! This Superfood has many health benefits but let’s talk about the fat. This healthy fat has been known to decrease LDL (lousy) cholesterol and increase HDL (healthy) cholesterol. (I hear my friends saying, “Sharon, you don’t like Avocados.” They’re right, but a little in my smoothie and I get all the benefits without the taste!)
• Frozen Mixed Fruit (Strawberry, Mango, Peach, Pineapple) - As plant food intake goes up, the risk of heart disease, diabetes, and cancer goes down. (medicalnewstoday.com) Fruit is also loaded with water to keep you hydrated. • Greek Yogurt - Packed with Protein for your muscles and Probiotics for gut health. It also makes the smoothie creamy. • Superfood Dense Nutrition base - there’s so much healthy goodness in this one scoop, I don’t need the other ingredients. But, the other items makes it FUN! 
I was gone for a long time today, and this kept me full until I returned home. .
So, what’s your ultimate refreshment? .
#WellnessJourneySolutions #HealthyFoods #CoachSharon #30DaysOfSC #Enjoy

alt: Image may contain: drink
firstComment:
I have become very passionate about replacing cleaning products and health & beauty items with non toxic alternatives in my home.  My latest discovery is hand soap.  I had no idea how inexpensive and easy it is to make my own.  And I appreciate the versatility, I can mix up the scent just by changing the oil that i add!

1 1/2c water
2T Castillo soap
1/2t almond oil
20ish drops essential oil *I love citrus options in the kitchen because they are a natural grease cutter...lemon, orange, tangerine, citrus fresh 🍋 🍊 *I prefer Thieves in our downstairs bathroom which is our main hand washing spot because THIEVES :) I bought the ingredients and a few foaming had soap pumps from Amazon and put them onto Mason jars we already had and Voila! ✨ 
#yleo #youngliving #essentialoils #laundry #younglivingessentialoils #younglivingoil #younglivingmember #essentialoils #oils #yleo #ylessentialoils #younglivingeo #myoilyday #ihavemyoilsnowwhat #whatsinmyER #oilyjourney #wellness #sustainableliving #drinkyourgreens #paleo #selfcare #seedtoseel #wellnessjourneyinparadise

Snack on the go! Hoy no tuve tiempo de alistar mi merienda de la tarde, así que busqué una opción saludable! Yogurt con marañón, agua alcalina y probióticos! 🔝🔝Existen determinadas cepas de probióticos que pueden ayudarnos a regular el peso corporal, al influir en las funciones metabólicas, neuroendocrinas e inmunológicas 🙌🏼✔️. Además, el agua alcalina nos puede beneficiar el la eliminación de toxinas, y evitar ciertas enfermedades y envejecimiento prematuro ya que combate los radicales libres💪🏼👊🏼
Fuente: Andrew, P et al. El papel de los probióticos en el manejo de la obesidad. Nutrición Hospitalaria (2015).

alt: Photo by Ivonne Ackerman on July 21, 2017. Image may contain: 1 person
firstComment:
I ❤️ summer, hot weather, refreshing drinks, outdoor activities. But most of the time I feel like I overextend myself and say yes to everything. I want to do it all! Parties, work, side hustle, drinks on that roof, brunch on that patio, beach trip with those friends, family vacay. But yoga teaches us balance, on the mat as well as off, effortless effort. Which is what classical ballet also portrays, make the difficult appear natural and easy. So I have to remind myself to slow down and enjoy myself. Stop thinking of what I have to do next. Cultivate steadiness, a little more ease. Now that the weekend is here I can practice balance and take it easy. After working all week, I get to enjoy the time off. My flows this weekend will be slower and easier movement with longer forward folds and slower breath counts. -

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

Andrés 💛💚💙🐶#Repost @gisshealthy (@get_repost)

Путь к здоровью начинается на работе!

Сотрудники – это высшая ценность компании. Забота об их благополучии является неотъемлемой частью корпоративной культуры. 
Большинство работников не успевает заниматься спортом и ведёт малоподвижный образ жизни. Это приводит к ослаблению иммунитета, апатии, снижению работоспособности и недостаточной концентрации внимания. Вследствие чего увеличивается количество больничных листов, падает эффективность работы, что в целом приводит к снижению общего результата компании. 
Международные исследования показали, что физически и психически здоровые работники более внимательны и собраны на рабочем месте, они меньше ошибаются, более креативны, способны быстрее принимать решения и реализовывать их. 
Преимущества корпоративного велнеса первыми оценили американские руководители крупных компаний, которые решили инвестировать в здоровье работников с целью снижения стресса и заболеваемости, повышения продуктивности труда и удовлетворенности работой, привлечения лучших специалистов. В результате прибыльность и престижность компаний возросла, резко сократилась текучесть кадров. 
Corporate Wellness – эффективная корпоративная оздоровительная программа, которая поможет снизить совокупные затраты, повысит производительность и привлечет новых талантливых сотрудников! Мы сделаем занятия спортом частью корпоративной культуры. 
Предлагаем индивидуальные решения для оснащения офисов лучшим спортивным оборудованием TECHNOGYM. Обустроим любое помещение, даже площадью в 1 м2.

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

firstComment:
ˢᵉʳⁱᵒᵘˢˡʸ ᵗʰᵒᵘᵍʰ

When you view yourself, as the you you want to be. What do you look like? And I'm not just talking physical appearance I'm talking, how you want to be? The you that you would love to be. How would you feel on a daily basis? 
That calm, collected, compassionate, healthy, happy, hydrated, easy breezy you.

If you struggle with this, think of a movie character that you admire.... Who is that? What are their qualities that you admire?

And then think, what would it take to get me there? And what is it worth? What work would I have to put in, and what would I be willing to invest in it?

If it is truly worth it to you to reach those goals: whether it be to lose weight, put on weight, get your nutrition in check, tone up, feel fitter and able to run around after your kids and not get out of breath. To feel confident to get in the pool with your kids rather than avoid it altogether.

You will set aside your excuses, I don't have the money, I don't have the time, I'm too busy, I have too much on. And I say excuses with kindness. Before I saw mine as reasons, and actually over time I've seen some of them as excuses and some as reasons. We can work with all of it. You can do it. I believe in you mama sitting and reading this. 
If you don't know where to start just message. I am happy to help, even if it's just pointing you in the direction of some awesome personal development. X

I’m not a fan of the phrase New Year, New You. None of us needs to toss out our whole selves and start over. We’ve all got some good stuff to work with and most of us can benefit from a little more self love and appreciation.⁣
⁣
I’m working on my goals for 2020.  I find if I set a resolution, it feels sort of all or nothing.  If you fail at it in the first month (or week...or day) then it feels all is lost. I’ve got a couple in mind for my business, a few health-related goals, and something in mind for family.  This year is rapidly coming to an end so I need to get my act together and get my list narrowed down. ⁣

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

alt: Image may contain: 1 person, hat, outdoor and closeup
firstComment:
✨ L E S S O N S from L I F E✨⁣
⁣
I’m currently 4 weeks in with my half marathon training and as the KM have started to increase, I’ve been having some musings. A lot of these I’ve come across before, but perhaps through my training it’s all finally sinking in 🤔⁣
⁣
Musings as follows:⁣
⁣
📍 Setting a goal is easy; achieving it takes focus, determination, strength, practice and planning.⁣
⁣
📍 Breaking the goal down into smaller, incremental, more manageable steps helps, but within that, focusing ONLY on the one step at a time.⁣
⁣
📍 On that note, scheduling the smaller steps in so there are no excuses! If it’s important, there’s time for it.⁣
⁣
📍 The only person I’m competing against is myself.⁣
⁣
📍 Big goals can be scary - feel the fear, do it anyway 👊🏼⁣
⁣
📍 Working on a personal goal can be a lonely road at times. It’s just me, myself and I out there. If I want it done, I need to do the work.⁣
⁣
📍Looking after my body and my health is actually so important to see out the long term goal.⁣
⁣
📍 Be kind to myself and recognise how far I’ve come.⁣
⁣
📍 Trying something different can be better than you expect (in this case, listening to podcasts on my runs as opposed to music - thanks to the bestie @vzywong for the inspo!)⁣
⁣
📍 Don’t (over) think, just DO!⁣
⁣
📍 Mindset matters!!! Oh my word does it. Flood those thoughts with positivity and the results will come.⁣
⁣
📍 Endorphins are actually the best.⁣
⁣
📍 Getting out in nature is SOOO good for the soul. I’ve been running along the river pathways and it’s been all sorts of serene.⁣
⁣
📍 Essential oils are helping me, A LOT!⁣
⁣
Snap of me stretching this morning, feeling fab and stoked with life post-run. Sunday sessions are my longer runs, the ones where it’s just about getting in the distance and practicing endurance. I’m up to 9.5km and I seriously procrastinated before I went out... But I did it and it went by in a flash. The pace I kept is the best I’ve done yet and today, for the first time, I FELT confident about achieving my goal of running 21km at the end of May. I’ve run one before, but it was 10 years ago when I was a fearless 21 year old 😆 I think 31 year old me is learning so much more.⁣

alt: Photo by doTERRA - Tamara Wootton on March 24, 2019.
firstComment:
🙋 If you have heard of the gut-brain connection? 
There's lots of research happening now which is showing evidence that the bacteria in our guts affect how our brain functions. 
Our gut is the front line for our immune system, around 70-80% of the body's immune cells are found in the gut. 
An unhealthy gut effects every part of our being  from our moods to physical symptoms. 
After the stress of a traumatic long labour where I lost a lot of blood then throw in a newborn with colic, that we didn't know at the time had sleep apnea..... The reason he never slept. 
My body shut down.... It was all too much.

I hadn't really taken care of it. 
I ate what I wanted...
I partied hard in the years leading up to kids. 
At one point I was drinking 4-5 Vs a day! 
So the stress of birth & sheer exhaustion from having a newborn depleted what was left and it shut down... I couldn't eat anything. 
My body reacted to EVERY food. 
I seen all the specialist, done the colonoscopy & they came back with IBS.... I JUST HAD TO GET USED TO IT..... I was literally eating boiled chicken, plain rice & sometimes a little carrot. 
I didn't leave the house because I needed to use the toilet so much, then the anxiety kicked in..... What if I'm out and there is no toilet? 
I popped Immodium like lollies & they stopped working. 
I didn't leave my house for almost a year. 
Eventually I stumbled on gut health and the importance of having a healthy gut. 
Slowly but surely I started making progress. 
It took me years to heal.... Now I can eat freely with few restrictions.
We tend to stick to good wholesome foods. 
I don't really drink much other than water & my morning coffee. 
Plus I now teach people how to overcome their own anxiety! 
Life hands us many challenges, 
It's up to us if we take the word of one. 
Or fight for something better!

✨DIY Recipe + a March Special ✨
.
That’s right you guys, you’re gettin’ 2-for-1 in this post 😏 I’m sharing one of my fave and oh-so-easy DIY recipes, plus the alternative that @doterraaunz has taken 10% for March 🤗 woo!
.
Let’s see if I can keep this as short, sharp and shiny as the recipe is!
.
Team, it has 4 ingredients! And you just pop ‘em all in a foaming soap dispenser (like this one that you can get from dōTERRA, but you can always buy the pretty amber glass ones from an online store, or even reuse an old one like I did when I first started making this way back when).
.
✔️ 1/3 cup unscented liquid castille soap (can buy from health food stores)
✔️ 1 tsp carrier oil (I use Fractionated Coconut Oil, and usually just guesstimate with a squirt!)
✔️ 20 drops dōTERRA On Guard essential oil
✔️ 2/3 cup water
.
That’s it. Give it a little swirl around once the pump top is on and you’re away laughing. Told you it was easy!
.
And the alternative? Order this trio pack in the second photo (10% off this month), and simply pour the hand wash solution into the dispensers. Nothing else. Either way, super simple.
.
I usually opt for my DIY recipe, but have found it useful having the pre-mixed solution on hand for the odd occasion I’ve run out of my liquid castille.
.
There we have it my friends, a simple Sunday solution for you all. And some alliteration. I do love a bit of that as well 😌.
.
.
.
.

It was this aspect of what these oils can do - support emotions - that really grabbed my attention from the get go. In fact, it was what I needed most from these oils without actually realising it. They’re my absolute go-to now for all kinds of emotional feels we humans get to experience.

If you’re into this kinda thing (like I am 🙋🏼‍♀️), it turns out there’s an emotional meaning attached to each individual oil and blend. They say the oils we feel really drawn to are what our bodies need the most, and it can be interesting to look up these meanings in the Emotions and Essential Oils reference guide, especially if it feels quite random.

An example: at the end of 2017, I was in the lead up to my wedding in NZ whilst also finishing up with my job at the time. Life was pretty full and I found myself loving on the Basil oil 🤷🏼‍♀️ I was stumped, it came out of nowhere. I didn’t own this book at the time (nor had I had the time to stop and think about finding out more), so when I got to NZ a few weeks out from the wedding, I looked up Basil in my sister’s book and blow me down, it’s referred to as the Oil of Renewal. The whole written speal was basically me the few months prior, but can be summed up with this sentence - “Basil oil supports those who are under a great deal of mental strain” ✔️✔️✔️ umm, yip.

It’s important to note that essential oils won’t do the work for you, but they are for sure a great tool in helping to become more in tune with how you’re feeling so you can work through any emotion, rather than crush it on down and avoid it.

Game changer in my books. Keen to see for yourself? X

firstComment:
Introducing Lace & Co. Essentials 🤗

For a good many years now, health and wellness have played a key role in how I do life. As with most things, it started off pretty simple, but as the years have passed (+ different life situations have come and gone) it has become increasingly apparent how important it is to take control of my own health, wellness and overall wellbeing.

For this reason, I am forever researching new health hacks and love coming across new tips and tricks that are effective in keeping me feeling vital, energetic and well. Two and a half years ago, along came dōTERRA’s essential oils and WHOA, were they a game-changer!! What started off as a simple way to reduce the toxic load in my home (+ provide “some nice smells”) then started to slowly and unexpectedly weave their magic into other areas of my life. They have now become such a staple part of my day that I sometimes stop to wonder what I did before I discovered them. From providing natural solutions to support sleep and stress (seriously, much needed support 😌) to reducing the chemicals in my cleaning products and skincare - you name it, I’ve probably found an oil for it (and if I haven’t, I’m more than happy to try 😉). For a long time I’ve I thought this was just ‘my thing’, something I dabbled in quietly in the comfort of my own home. Sometimes I’ve shared about them, though I think more often I’ve not for fear of being different to the ‘norm’... whatever that may be. The thing is, these oils (+ many of the other incredible dōTERRA products) have become such a big part of my wellness journey that all I want to do is share how effective they are for me, in the hopes that perhaps others who are seeking natural solutions like I was will find just that.

Take note, I am not a qualified medical practitioner, nor do I pretend to be an expert in this area. I am merely someone who is committed to feeling my absolute best, takes great interest in my own health and well-being, and wishes to share what has had such a big impact on me.

If any of this has peaked an interest or sparked a curiosity in you, stay tuned for how and why dōTERRA’s essential oils are a staple in my life and home.

Lace x
